    (168, 'AGC3100', 4, '# of affordable homeownership sales facilitated', 'Output', 'Number of affordable Homeownership sales facilitated', 'CDBG form 2', 'Tommy Williams', 'Assistant Commissioner of Homeownership and Housing Preservation', 'Quarterly  - will revise in change to monthly reporting in FY 27', 'N/A', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'What defines an affordable homeownership sale?', false, NULL, 'Homeownership CDBG reports', 'Quarterly reporting for CDBG', 'Qualifies the number of affordable homes sold in the quarter', NULL, 'Quarterly reports to CDBG', 'The metric is vague on what it means to "facilitate" and what counts as an "affordable homeownership sale." Additionally, consideration should be given to the monetary value of each sale.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (169, 'AGC3100', 4, '# of loans serviced', 'Output', 'The number of loans serviced', 'Neighborly and monthly loan report by staff from Neighborly', 'Tommy Williams', 'Assistant Commissioner of Homeownership and Housing Preservation', 'Data is currently calculated monthly by the team.', 'N/A', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Homeownership loan service on the shared drive and Neighborly', 'Monthly reporting', 'To meet yearly goals', NULL, 'N/A', 'The metric should be scaled by the monetary value of the loans.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (170, 'AGC3100', 4, '% of incentives provided to Low and Moderate Income homebuyers', 'Outcome', 'Percentage of homebuyer incentives provided to low to moderate homebuyers', 'CDBG Form 2 / number of low to moderate buyers/ by the total of FTHIP homebuyers', 'Tommy Williams', 'Assistance Commissioner of Homeownership and Housing', 'Quarterly', 'the numerator represented the number of Low to Moderate income homes sales facilitated and the denominator represents the total number of affordable homes sales', 'Not Applicable', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'Which homebuyer incentives are included in this metric collection?', false, NULL, 'Homeownership CDBG Reports', 'Quarterly', 'Used to determine if we are on target of year end goal of % of incentives provided to low to moderate income homebuyers', NULL, 'We haven’t been capturing this data monthly because we do it went the CDBG reporting is due.  We will attempt to change the gathering of the information to monthly for FY 27.', 'The metric should be scaled by the monetary value of incentives rather than just a simple proportion. If 10 incentives are provided to LMI homebuyers out of 20 but it''s 65% of total money spent, the metric gives a skewed view.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (171, 'AGC3100', 4, '# of property maintenance code enforcement inspections', 'Output', 'The total number of property maintenance code enforcement inspections', 'CHIP', 'Eric Booker and Erick Yates', 'Deputy Commissioner and Assistant Commissioner Code Enforcement and Property Maintenance', 'LIVE', 'Count', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Computerize Housing Inspection Program (CHIP)', 'Report creation', 'The service is dedicated to maintaining safe and attractive neighborhoods by conducting effective investigations and enforcing the building, fire, and related codes. DHCD’s Code Enforcement Division carries out these responsibilities across the city.', NULL, NULL, 'Please provide specifications of which inspections are included in this count.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (172, 'AGC3100', 4, '% of service requests closed on time', 'Efficiency', 'Service request closed before the service level agreement', '311', 'Ericka Yates', 'Assistant Commissioner for Code Enforcement', 'LIVE', '# closed on time/# closed', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'Which SRs are included in this metric collection?', false, NULL, 'Salesforce (311 system)', 'Report creation', 'The service is dedicated to maintaining safe and attractive neighborhoods by conducting effective investigations and enforcing building, fire, and related codes, while monitoring performance to ensure committed response and resolution timelines are met.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (173, 'AGC3100', 4, '% of vacates of illegal occupants in vacant buildings within 7 days', 'Outcome', 'Our key measure is of the percentage of removing illegal occupants from vacant properties (referred to as vacates) in seven calendar days or less.', 'The sources of data collection for this workload are as follows: Computerize Housing Inspection Program (CHIP); 311 requests, referrals by Property Maintenance Superintendents, DPW, the Agency Commissioner, City Council persons, and the Mayor’s Office.', 'Erick Booker or Nancy R Goldring', 'Deputy Commissioner and Assistant Commissioner of Emergency Management and Special Operations', 'Vacate data is collected live, weekly, monthly, and annually.', 'Daily entries into the CHIP system by inspectors, a daily calendar, an excel spreadsheet, daily written logs and monthly reports are maintained on all vacate operations and their outcomes. A SharePoint is currently being developed to allow for the sharing', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'Why is the target 7 calendar days?', true, NULL, 'The Computerize Housing Inspection Program (CHIP) system is the primary platform for data storage on this metric.', 'Daily entries into the CHIP system by inspectors, a daily calendar, an excel spreadsheet, daily written logs and monthly reports are maintained on all vacate operations and their outcomes. A SharePoint is currently being developed to allow for the sharing', 'This data measures the escalation in the number of occupants in vacant buildings throughout the city. Our schedule of vacates has expanded from occasional to almost daily. The need for our services has climbed from 71 vacates in FY23/24 to 186 in FY24/25. The number of vacates for the first and second quarter of FY25/26 total 102.', NULL, 'Not applicable', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (174, 'AGC3100', 4, '# of contractors registered', 'Output', 'Number of Building and Trade Contractors Licensed to perform work in Baltimore City', 'Accela Licensing Database', 'Jason Hessler', 'Deputy Commissioner', 'Live', 'N/A', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Accela', 'Pull Ad hoc report for time period to get count of active (not expired) licenses.', 'Indicator along with permit activity on economic standing of the local housing market.', NULL, 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (175, 'AGC3100', 4, 'Number of properties registered', 'Output', 'Measure number of non-owner-occupied properties registered.', 'Open Gov Property Registration and Licensing Database', 'Jason Hessler', 'Deputy Commissioner', 'Live', 'N/A', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'How does DHCD track compliance with this statute? How is "owner-occupied" housing determined and tracked?', true, NULL, 'Open GOV', 'Open report titled Registration Reports 2024. Modify report to collect records submitted December 1, 2024 – November 30, 2025 (for FY 26 Q1 and 2 reporting). Export report to excel. Separate data so you only have registration or registration and licensing', 'Monitor effectiveness of outreach, education and enforcement activities.', NULL, 'N/A', 'Could this metric be re-written as a proportion of properties registered out of an (estimated?) total number of properties eligible for registration?', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (176, 'AGC3100', 4, 'Percent of rental properties licensed', 'Outcome', 'Increase in compliance with the rental licensing laws.', 'OpenGov', 'Jason Hessler', 'Deputy Commissioner', 'Live', 'Total rental units licensed / US Census Community Survey number for rental units in Baltimore City', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'How often are licenses renewed? How often is the census count for the total number of units provided?', true, NULL, 'Opengov', 'Download rental licensing data. Sort for properties licensed during timeframe. Divide total units licensed by US Census Community Survey number for rental units in Baltimore City. Currently 127,100', 'Track progress toward increasing number of properties licensed.', NULL, 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (177, 'AGC3100', 4, 'City dollars contributed per affordable rental and homeownership housing units created', 'Outcome', 'This measure captures the number of city dollars contributed per affordable rental and homeownership housing units created which is described as housing units (homeownership + rental) supported by AHTF investments during the reporting period.   Includes other funding for Affordable Housing.', 'Data is sourced from the Neighborly application and data management system. Funding information is collected directly from applicants and grantees during the application process and updated throughout project development. Data is supplemented and validat', 'Kelvin Appiah / Wendi Redfern', 'Program Analyst / DC', 'Data is available on a rolling basis and updated continuously as projects progress. For reporting purposes, data is reviewed and finalized quarterly', 'Development Division', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Currency', NULL, 'How often are projects using AHTF dollars required to update their financial records?', false, NULL, 'Neighborly application and data management system', 'Data is collected via: 
· Direct entry by applicants during the AHTF application process 
· Ongoing updates submitted by grantees as projects progress 
· Data entry and verification by AHTF staff as part of project management and 
compliance monitoring', 'Data is used to help inform budgeting/fiscal forecasting, to assess program effectiveness, and communicate the return on City investment to stakeholders, leadership, and the public.', NULL, 'roxy isn’t necessary; Neighborly system + internal project management processes
provide valid and consistent method for capturing data.', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
