    (256, 'AGC4301', 4, 'Success Ratio of Implemented Contracting Process Improvement Recommendations', 'Output', 'Projects and.or workgroups that have ongoing work.', 'Report that has been published.', 'Jarek Hardy', 'Procurement Officer I', 'It''s self-reporting data', 'Report that was published.', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'More information is needed to understand how the measure is calculated and where the numbers used to calculate it come from. Description is lacking.', false, NULL, 'Via manual work by personnel', 'Manual', 'It''s not operations per se; it helps see that initiatives have begun and are ongoing to improve the capital project delivery/ecosystem.', NULL, 'Manual tracking.', 'Don’t understand this', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (257, 'AGC4301', 4, 'Attendance at Informative/Resource Events', 'Effectiveness', 'The total number of individuals who attend an event, (counted once per event).
 Measures overall reach and interest
Quantitative Data (Numbers MOAAA Can Measure)Survey responses are counted as data because they provide measurable information—both numerical and narrative—that can be analyzed to understand needs, evaluate programs, and track progress.', 'Event Registration logs and surveys', 'Ondoria Harmon
Danielle Reynolds', 'Director, MOAAA
Exective Assistant', 'Monthly ,Quarterly and Annually.', 'Event Registration logs and surveys', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'MOAAA transfers  the information  onto excel spreadsheets , we have the data stored on TEAMS Channel in a folders and we also have paper copies filed', 'create google doc and or microsoft forms for older adults to register online ( QR code and url for the larger events, use sign in sheet for smaller events.  provide the office phone #, register indivduals who are unable, survey is given and collected.', 'informs operations by showing how effectively  MOAAA is reaching older adults, especially in underserved neighborhoods/ communites . Attendance data helps guide outreach strategies, event planning, staffing, and resource needed . It is meaningful because it reflects real engagement, demonstrates access to services, and serves as a proxy for awareness, equity, and community connection.', NULL, 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (258, 'AGC4301', 4, 'Inquires for assistance or support for services', 'Outcome', 'MOAAA measures the number of times older adults, caregivers, or partners contact our office seeking help, information, or connection to services. This metric captures demand, need, and awareness of city services and or programs.', 'Phone calls, emails, and agency requests', 'Ondoria Harmon
Danielle Reynolds', 'Director
Exective Assistant', 'Daily, weekly, monthy , annually', 'Inquiries are collected through multiple intake channels, including phone calls, emails, walk‑ins, and referrals from partner organizations.', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'Would be great to understand how data is collected. Reads as if they count the number of emails, calls, etc. informally', false, NULL, 'we have the data stored on TEAMS Channel in a folders and we also print paper copies filed', 'Staff record each inquiry in a log excel, capturing the date, source of inquiry, type of request, and any follow‑up actions.', 'MOAAA uses the data collected from inquiries / support attendance, to advocay for improvement to city/ agemcies  programs and  services, strengthen outreach, and guide strategic decisions. The data is not just counted — it actively shapes how the office operates.', NULL, 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (259, 'AGC4301', 4, 'Number of agencies assessed for equity, accessibility and inclusiveness', 'Output', 'MOAAA staff document each agency assessment using a checklist.', 'Data is sourced from MOAAA’s internal assessment checklists,   and documentation maintained by staff.”', 'Ondoria Harmon
