This helps MOAAA improve coordination and reduce fragmentation in services for older adults.', NULL, 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (260, 'AGC4303', 4, '# of Cameras Replaced', 'Output', 'Counts the number of cameras replaced, supporting maintenance tracking and system reliability monitoring.', 'Genetec', 'Arthur Ray', 'Director, Public Safety Technology', 'Monthly', 'Total number of cameras replaced in the environment, if applicable.', 'Not Applicable', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'BCIT Stat Power Apps', 'The data pulled from the video management system.', 'Data on the number of cameras replaced is used to monitor and manage maintenance activities across the environment. It helps teams track hardware lifecycle, identify trends in camera failures, plan replacements proactively, and ensure continuous system reliability.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify the time period being measured i.e. # of cameras replaced in a FY', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (261, 'AGC4303', 4, 'CitiWatch camera availability', 'Effectiveness', 'Tracks the uptime of all CitiWatch cameras, excluding planned or scheduled maintenance. This metric monitors system reliability and helps ensure cameras are consistently operational for security and monitoring purposes.', 'Genetec', 'Arthur Ray', 'Director, Public Safety Technology', 'Monthly', 'Camera Availability (%) = (Operational Time ÷ Total Expected Time) × 100, excluding scheduled maintenance periods.', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Stored in BCIT Stat Power Apps & Genetec Excel sheet', 'Availability is sent through Email Daily from Genetec.', 'This data is used to monitor the reliability of the CitiWatch camera network. It helps identify outages or recurring issues, prioritize maintenance or repairs, and ensure the system meets service level expectations.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify how to exclude scheduled maintenance in calculation, recommend switching to efficiency metric type', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (262, 'AGC4303', 4, 'Total Number of Cameras', 'Output', 'Total number of cameras we have in the environment that we track each month', 'Genetec', 'Arthur Ray', 'Director, Public Safety Technology', 'Monthly', 'Total number of cameras exported daily, with availability verified', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Stored in BCIT Stat Power Apps & Genetec Excel sheet', 'Emailed Report from Genetec', 'Tracking the total number of cameras in the environment provides a comprehensive view of system coverage and deployment.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify in measure name whether this is available/operational cameras or all cameras', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (263, 'AGC4303', 4, 'Customer payment portal availability (excludes scheduled maintenance)', 'Effectiveness', 'A measure of the uptime for the BCIT managed payment sites', 'BCIT Database', 'Arnold Jackson', 'Director, DevOps', 'Monthly', 'BCIT Database', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Database - BCIT, BCIT Power Apps', 'collected after a script is ran each month from the Database - BCIT', 'Measuring the uptime of BCIT-managed payment sites is meaningful because it reflects the reliability and availability of critical services that residents and customers depend on to complete payments without interruption.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify calculation formula and database, recommend switching to efficiency metric type', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (264, 'AGC4303', 4, '# of Calls Received in 311', 'Output', 'Total number of incoming calls to 311 during the reporting period. Tracks the volume of service requests handled by the call center.', 'Mitel', 'Crosby, Jacqueline', 'Director, 311 Call Center', 'Monthly', '# of Calls Received = Count of all calls logged in 311 during the period', 'Not Applicable', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Mitel & BCIT Power Apps', 'Email is sent with the monthly outcome from Mitel.', 'Helps assess workload, staff allocation, and call center capacity. Identifies trends in demand and informs resource planning.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify Mitel report name', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (265, 'AGC4303', 4, '% of calls answered within 60 seconds at 311', 'Effectiveness', 'Percentage of calls answered within 60 seconds of being placed, indicating responsiveness to callers.', 'Mitel', 'Crosby, Jacqueline', 'Director, 311 Call Center', 'Monthly', 'Number of calls answered within 60 seconds​/Total calls recieved x 100', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Mitel & BCIT Power Apps', 'Email is Sent monthly with the reporting from Mitel.', 'Evaluates call center responsiveness, identifies performance gaps, and supports staffing or process adjustments to improve service levels.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify Mitel report name', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (266, 'AGC4303', 4, 'Average Handling Time (in minutes and seconds)', 'Efficiency', 'Average total time an agent spends handling a call, from answer to completion, including talk time and post-call wrap-up.', 'Mitel', 'Crosby, Jacqueline', 'Director, 311 Call Center', 'Monthly', 'Total talk + wrap-up time for all calls​/Total calls handled', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', 'in minutes', 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Mitel & BCIT Power Apps', 'Email is sent from Mitel with the monthly reporting.', 'Helps assess agent productivity, efficiency of processes, and workload management. Supports staffing and process improvement decisions.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify Mitel report name', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (267, 'AGC4303', 4, 'Average time to answer a call in 311 (seconds)', 'Effectiveness', 'Average duration (in seconds) that callers wait before their call is answered by a 311 agent.', 'Mitel', 'Crosby, Jacqueline', 'Director, 311 Call Center', 'Monthly', 'Sum of all call wait time/Total Answered Calls', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Mitel & BCIT Power Apps', 'Email s sent with the monthly reporting from Mitel.', 'Tracks service efficiency and responsiveness, helping management identify delays, optimize staffing, and improve customer satisfaction.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify Mitel report name', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (268, 'AGC4303', 4, 'Overall Customer Service Experience Score (scale of 1-5)', 'Outcome', 'Average score provided by callers on their overall experience with 311, using a scale from 1 (lowest) to 5 (highest).', 'Mitel', 'Crosby, Jacqueline', 'Director, 311 Call Center', 'Monthly', 'Sum of all caller ratings/Total number of responses', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Mitel & BCIT Power Apps', 'Mitel sends an email for the monthly reporting.', 'Evaluates customer satisfaction and service quality. Highlights areas for improvement, informs training, and measures the effectiveness of 311 services in meeting public expectations.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify Mitel report name', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (269, 'AGC4303', 4, 'Critical tickets resolved within service level', 'Effectiveness', 'Counts the number of high-priority (critical) tickets resolved within the defined service level agreement (SLA) timeframe.', 'SolarWinds, incidents tab', 'Bruce Gibbons', 'Director, Infrastructure', 'Monthly', 'Number of critical tickets resolved within SLA/Total critial tickets', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'BCIT Power Apps,', 'Solarwinds', 'Measures IT responsiveness, supports SLA compliance, identifies process bottlenecks, and ensures critical issues are addressed promptly.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify count or %', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (270, 'AGC4303', 4, 'Email Availability (excludes scheduled maintenance)', 'Effectiveness', 'Tracks the uptime of the email system, excluding planned maintenance periods. Indicates whether users can reliably send and receive emails.', 'SolarWinds', 'Bruce Gibbons', 'Director, Infrastructure', 'Monthly', 'Time email system was operational/Total time system was expected to be operational x 100', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'SolarWinds & BCIT Power Apps', 'Extract report from Solarwinds.', 'Ensures reliable communication, identifies system issues, supports IT maintenance planning, and measures the effectiveness of email service delivery.', NULL, NULL, 'Clarify SolarWinds report name', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
