    (280, 'AGC4309', 4, 'Average # of youth engaged at youth programming events', 'Output', 'Youth attendance at youth-centered events hosted or organized by MOCFS', 'MOCFS Event Attendance Tracker SharePoint List
https://bmore.sharepoint.com/sites/MOCFS-ChildrenandFamilySuccess/Lists/Event%20Attendance%20Tracker/AllItems.aspx', 'Kristina Gilchrist', 'Director of Communications and Engagement', 'Monthly', 'sum of Attended column where Event Date between quarterly reporting period start and end dates', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'SharePoint

https://bmore.sharepoint.com/sites/MOCFS-ChildrenandFamilySuccess/Lists/Event%20Attendance%20Tracker

This list will likely be migrated this year to the following site:

https://bmore.sharepoint.com/sites/MOCFSAdmin', 'Admin Team uses a palm tally counter at event entrance, then enters the count in the SharePoint list.', 'Attendance data are used to inform outreach, gaps in equitable access and planning efforts. Eventbrite registration is compared with on-site registration data to identify unique attendees. This analysis helps measure event reach, evaluate the effectiveness of outreach, and guide future youth programming.', NULL, 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (281, 'AGC4309', 4, '% of 3 year old children that have achieved age appropriate proficiency for school readiness at the end of the school year', 'Outcome', 'Evaluate 3 year old children''s developmental level and progress in outcomes aligned to the goals for three year olds as described in the Head Start Early Learning Child Outcomes Framework: Ages Birth to Five.', 'Teaching Strategies Gold Assessment Tool', 'Shannon Burroughs-Campbell', 'Executive Director, Baltimore City Head Start', 'Annually', '% of 3 year olds enrolled for the entire school year that are deemed "ready".', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Online', 'Teachers individualize and assess children throughout the year using the Head Start Early Learning Child Outcomes Framework: Ages Birth to Five.', 'To meet the federal requirement to conduct standardized and structured assessments, which may be observation-based or direct, for each enrolled child that provide information to evaluate the child’s developmental level and progress in outcomes aligned to Head Start Early Learning Child Outcomes Framework: Ages Birth to Five.', NULL, 'n/a', 'Identify the speciifc reports  and locations for pulling the data in the Teaching Strategies Gold Assessment Tool. I would also add the numerator (# of 3 yr olds deemed "Ready") and denominator (Total # of 3 tyr olds)', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (282, 'AGC4309', 4, '% of enrollment during school year', 'Outcome', 'Enrollment', 'COPA Database', 'Shannon Burroughs-Campbell', 'Executive Director, Baltimore City Head Start', 'Annually', '# of children enrolled/# of federal funded slotsfor the year', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Online', 'Data inputted from Head Start programs regarding enrollments.', 'The program reports this data to the Office of Head Start who uses this information to report to Congress regarding the provision of Head Start services nationally.', NULL, 'n/a', 'Identify the speciifc reports  and locations for pulling the data in the COPA database.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (283, 'AGC4309', 4, '# of energy applications processed', 'Output', 'Total Applications (Unduplicated) for the reporting period', 'OHEP Database
https://landing.mdthink.maryland.gov/OHEP/Report/FormReportViewer?reportName=AgencyManagementReportViewer', 'Samuel Helmey', 'Agency IT Manager', 'Live', 'N/A', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'OHEP Database', 'Run Agency Management Report in the OHEP Portal with date filter set to reporting period. Copy the amount for Total Applications YTD (Unduplicated)', 'These data are reviewed to monitor the seasonal and year-to-year trends in application volume.', NULL, 'N/A', 'As noted in the submission, the number of applications process is not equal to the number of applications received.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (284, 'AGC4309', 4, '# of participants enrolled in case management', 'Output', 'The number of families with an active case management case at any time during the reporting period', 'MOCFS BCCAP CAP 60 database', 'Samuel Helmey', 'Agency IT Manager', 'Live', 'N/A', 'Not Applicable', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'CAP60 Case Status History Report', 'Filter to cases that were in any of the statuses below either when the reporting period started or at any point during the reporting period. Deduplicate on Case ID. Statuses include "Approved", "Completed", "Open", "Applied", and "Pending"', 'These data are used to monitor active caseloads and, in combination with more detailed client management reporting, balance those caseloads and track performance across the five CAP centers.', NULL, 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (285, 'AGC4309', 4, '# of units of service provided to heads of households to remove barriers to self-sufficiency', 'Output', 'the sum of counts of unique water for all applications and unique energy assistance applicants approved in the reporting period plus the number of referrals provided by case managers in the reporting period. 

In previous years, case management was not included, but eviction prevention was. This is because the types of services provided by the agency sometimes vary from one year to the next.', 'Source Data: OHEP Payment Data Report, Water4All Database (application table), CAP60 Client Management System.', 'Samuel Helmey', 'Agency IT Manager', 'live', 'the sum of counts of all water and energy assistance cases approved in the reporting period plus referrals provided by case managers.', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Script for data transformations is stored here https://github.com/SamMOCFS/Performance-Plan-Metrics/blob/main/Performance%20Plan%20Measures.R', 'Details here: https://bmore.sharepoint.com/:x:/s/MOCFS-ChildrenandFamilySuccess/IQDQ66thwuI2TbWix4EvV0JbAYQn15U-sw3VQ-6pQP7Omrs?e=V6gETc', 'This measure is not meaningful in the aggregate. Case Management Service and Referral Counts are monitored to measure performance of case managers.', NULL, 'N/A', 'As noted in the submission, the measure is redundant and the "units of service" should not be lumped together since they arent comparable across programs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (286, 'AGC4310', 4, 'Annual # of business development webinars, speakers, conferences, and programs', 'Output', 'Webinars- online business development sessions.
Speakers-people who come to the SBRC to present business development information, people who speak at the conference, and people who present business development webinars. 
Programs-business development events that are part of a series of events, like Speaker Series. Business development events that are a single event where a speaker or SMBAD representative presents business development information.', 'Smartsheet', 'Vanessa Freund', 'Deputy Director', 'Events team enters this information weekly.', 'This will be measured by how many development events occur.  These are seperate from agency trainings and community outreach sessions.', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'Are events only initiated by MWB Office? Or can they be attendants to other events hosted by other entities?', true, NULL, 'Smartsheet', 'Smartsheet of events, python script to collect data.', 'To see what we are offering and who is attending so we can work to offer more sessions and assist more businesses.', NULL, NULL, 'Assuming MWB isn''t the only one putting on these events, it should be a percentage of events in the city that had a MWB presence', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (287, 'AGC4310', 4, 'Annual # of certified M/WBEs', 'Outcome', 'Number of certified MBE/WBE''s', 'B2G Diversity Compliance Software', 'Vanessa', 'deputy director', 'It is live in the B2G system and can be calculated based on the day.', 'This number fluctuates, but is tracked within B2G.  This reflects the number of certified MBE and WBEs.', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'B2G system', 'report ran in b2g', 'to see how many mbe/wbe''s we have', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (288, 'AGC4310', 4, 'Annual # of SBRC client participation in training', 'Output', 'SBRC client participation in training-any person who attends SMBAD webinars, programs, or conferences', 'Events Data Smartsheet, Webinar Spreadsheet, conference data.', 'Vanessa', 'Deputy director', 'weekly', 'This will be measured by our client/business training attendance in Smartsheet', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Smartsheet', 'Smartsheet', 'We use this data to see which trainings were well attended and to be able to offer those trainings more or additional trainings on those topics.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (289, 'AGC4310', 4, 'Annual # of training/outreach sessions provided', 'Output', 'Training-instructional sessions SMBAD directly puts on for internal and external partners. Outreach- events that SMBAD attends to promote the mission of the agency.', 'Tracked internally via information entered into Smartsheet for events. There is a python script that the data officer set up so the data can be pulled using that from the Smartsheet. If that fails we can review the sheet w detailed info', 'Vanessa Freund', 'Deputy Director', 'We are tracking the information quarterly, the event information is entered as the events team meets, which is weekly. The events team is reminded when each quarter is ending so that the Smartsheet is up to date.', 'Each event is tagged in Smartsheet using the appropritae definition to identify the event.', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Smartsheet', 'Entered by the events team into Smartsheet, python script pulls the information. If that doesn''t work, the sheet can be reviewed and sorted for the information', 'To review what sessions we are offering to assist businesses.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (290, 'AGC4310', 4, 'Annual % of procurement spent with M/WBEs', 'Outcome', 'spend for city certified mbe/wbe', 'B2G Diversity Compliance Software', 'Vanessa Freund', 'Deputy Director', 'hoping to get the most up to date information from b2g', 'This measure is not solely within the control of SMBA&D, but is furthered by our work.  This City spend will be tracked by inputting payment data for contract complaince in B2G.', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'Need more information on the data sources for calculating this metric (Where does the total procurement number come from that you divide M/WBE spend by to get a percentage?)', false, NULL, 'certified mbe/wbe spend is in b2g, but there are pieces of information missing.', 'B2G and WD for procurement spend', 'This data is important to understand where we are as a City for helping to support MBE/WBE''s and also how much work we need to do to achieve the goal.', NULL, NULL, 'Change measure type to "Effectiveness"', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (291, 'AGC4310', 4, 'Annual average # of days for certification application review', 'Output', 'The number of days to process a new or renewal application', 'B2G Diversity Compliance Software', 'Vanessa Freund', 'Deputy Director', 'Live data in the B2G system', 'This number is reached based upon the review of our ongoing statistics.  B2G measures from the time an application is completed and submitted until it has been approved or denied.', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'B2G', 'report in B2G', 'To assess how long it takes to review an applcation', NULL, NULL, '"Effectiveness", case can be made for output', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (292, 'AGC4316', 4, '# of unduplicated families that receive Family League funded home visiting services', 'Output', 'The number of unique families served by Healthy Families America Perinatal home visiting programs funded by Family League', 'Home visitor program enrollment data logged in Maxwell at enrollment', 'Jessie Tartanian', 'Director of Data and Evaluation', 'These data are entered by home visitors into Maxwell after visits so are available at any time. The partners do regular missing data checks weekly to prepare for quarterly data pulls and reporting by Family League.', 'Count of unique families', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Maxwell database', 'Home visiting partner organizations enter enrollment data into Maxwell', 'This is the bedrock measure for understanding the reach of Family League''s investment in home visiting programs. This measure is used to see if the funded partners are on track to serve the volume of families planned so that as many people can be served as possible. Home visiting program participation supports perinatal health outcomes and early development in myriad ways so tracking the numbered served allows us to monitor how many are able to benefit from these programs. We discuss the actuals for this measure with partners to assess if they are operating according to their contract and to support them with any issues with recruitment. Partners who excel in this measure are asked to coach struggling partners.', NULL, 'n/a', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (293, 'AGC4316', 4, '% of babies with low birth weight citywide (calendar year)', 'Effectiveness', 'The percentage of babies born in Baltimore who weigh less than 2500 g at birth during the calendar year', 'Baltimore City Health Department Annual Vital Statistics report', 'Jessie Tartanian', 'Director of Data and Evaluation', 'These data are 2 years behind their reporting and are updated annually', 'The number babies born in Baltimore who weigh less than 2500 g at birth/ the number of babies born in Baltimore during the calendar year', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'Amend measure type', true, NULL, 'Baltimore City Health Department database', 'Birth certificate records are collected by the Baltimore City Health Department', 'Family League compares home visiting partner organization birthweight trends to this whole city measure to inform how home visiting services might be impacting birth outcomes for participants. We also use this measure to track trends in birth outcomes across the city as a part of the wider B''more for Healthy Babies initiative, discussing implications with the strategic partners in the coalition at monthly and quarterly meetings.', NULL, 'We use the program level birth weight data instead of the city-level data as it is collected and accessible on a rolling basis.', 'Change measure type to "Outcome"', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (294, 'AGC4316', 4, '% of children in home visiting programs who exhibit developmentally on track social behavior, emotion regulation, and emotional well-being', 'Effectiveness', 'The percentage children  in home visiting programs who exhibit  developmentally on-track social behavior, emotion regulation, and emotional well-being according to the Ages and Stages Questionnaire- Socioemotional (ASQ-SE) screening tool, of those who were screened', 'Home visitor records of screening results logged in Maxwell after visits', 'Jessie Tartanian', 'Director of Data and Evaluation', 'These data are entered by home visitors into Maxwell after visits so are available at any time. The partners do regular missing data checks weekly to prepare for quarterly data pulls and reporting by Family League.', 'The percentage children  in home visiting programs who exhibit  developmentally on-track social behavior, emotion regulation, and emotional well-being according to the Ages and Stages Questionnaire- Socioemotional (ASQ-SE) screening tool divided by the nu', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'Not enough guidance on how an anlayst should handle, score, weigh answers in the questionnaire', false, NULL, 'Maxwell database', 'Home visitors record the data during home visits when the tool is administered', 'Family League reviews this performance measure quarterly with home visiting partner organizations to assess if providers and families need to change programming to support the socio-emotional development of children enrolled. This measure allows all parties to track the program impact on families and identify needs for additional support.', NULL, NULL, 'Change measure type to "Outcome"', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (295, 'AGC4316', 4, '% of people who report smoking in pregnancy citywide (calendar year)', 'Outcome', 'The percentage of birthing parents who report on their birth certificate form that they smoked tobacco products at any point during pregnancy. This does not include e-cigarette use.', 'Baltimore City Health Department via email correspondence', 'Jessie Tartanian', 'Director of Data and Evaluation', 'The data is 2-3 years behind their reporting and are updated annually', 'Number of birthing parents who report smoking during pregnancy/ number of birthing parents who fill out smoking data on birth certificate forms', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Baltimore City Health Department database', 'Birth certificate records are collected by the Baltimore City Health Department', 'Family League uses this measure to track trends in birth outcomes across the city as a part of the wider B''more for Healthy Babies initiative, discussing implications with the strategic partners in the coalition at monthly and quarterly meetings.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (296, 'AGC4321', 4, '# of youth served in Community Schools and community-based Out of School Time programs', 'Output', 'The number of youth who attended one day or more of Family League-funded Out-of-School Time programming', 'Daily student level attendance data collected in Family League''s salesforce based web platform, INSIGHT', 'Jessie Tartanian', 'Director of Data and Evaluation', 'Quarterly, but most is entered weekly', 'Count of youth served', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Family League salesforce web platform, INSIGHT', 'Out-of-School Time program site managers enter attendance data each week in INSIGHT', 'This is the bedrock measure for understanding the reach of Family League''s investment in comprehensive Out-of-School Time (OST) programs in Community Schools. This measure is used to see if the funded partners are on track to serve the volume of students planned so that as many students can be served as possible. OST participation supports youth development in myriad ways so tracking the number served allows us to monitor how many are able to benefit from these programs. We discuss the actuals for this measure with partners quarterly to assess if they are operating according to their contract and to support them with any issues with recruitment. Partners who excel in this measure are asked to coach new and struggling partners.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (297, 'AGC4321', 4, '% average daily attendance in Out of School Time programs', 'Effectiveness', 'The sum of the number of present participants at Out-of-School Time (OST) programs divided by the number of participants expected for each day of OST programming', 'Daily student level attendance data collected in Family League''s salesforce based web platform, INSIGHT', 'Jessie Tartanian', 'Director of Data and Evaluation', 'Quarterly, but most is entered weekly', 'Sum number  participants present/ sum number students expected', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Family League salesforce web platform, INSIGHT', 'Out-of-School Time program site managers enter participant enrollment data at the start of the school year and attendance data each week in INSIGHT', 'Average Daily Attendance (ADA) is the key measure for how well Out-of-School Time programs are doing with engaging their enrolled youth in the programming. We use this measure to assess the participation rate of enrolled youth because without this information, we cannot understand how much exposure the program intervention the youth actually are receiving. We discuss this measure with funded partners quarterly to address challenges with retention and attendance. We ask staff from sites with high ADA also coach sites that are new or struggling to engage the youth.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (298, 'AGC4321', 4, '% Out of School Time participants who are not chronically absent from school (miss less than 10% of enrolled days of school)', 'Outcome', 'The number of Out-of-School Time (OST) program participants who are present for more than 90% of school days for which they were enrolled divided by the total number of OST program participants', 'City Schools provides aggregate school attendance data matched to student-level Out-of-School Time participation data from Family League', 'Jessie Tartanian', 'Director of Data and Evaluation', 'Annually by 10/31', 'Number of OST participants not chronically absent from school/number of  students served by OST programs', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Baltimore City Public Schools database  and then aggregate data stored on Family League secure SharePoint Data Exchange', 'City schools takes daily student attendance. These data are matched with participant enrollment data entered in INSIGHT.', 'Out-of-School Time (OST) programs are a key aspect of the Community School model and support school-day attendance, which is arguably the first and foremost concern for schools. This measure allow us to continue to track if OST programs appear to promote attendance and protect against chronic absenteeism during the school day. These data are used to communicate the alignment of OST programs with school and district goals in annual conversations with decision makers and funders (such as principals and legislators), supporting the continued and expanded funding of this investment.', NULL, 'We use Average Daily Attendance in Out of School Time programs as a proxy for school-day attendance until the data are available.', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (299, 'AGC4326', 4, 'Number of visitors annually', 'Output', 'Sum of visitors across 4 BPMC Markets each quarter)', 'Placer.ai', 'Randi Norris', 'COO', 'Quarterly', 'count of annual visitors', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Placer.ai and Excel', 'Track visitors monthly', 'To provide guidance to our Marketing Director, Market Managers and Direct of Market Operations to assess how well we are attracting customers. The markets should continuously maintain or increase visitorship.', NULL, NULL, 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (300, 'AGC4326', 4, 'Percentage of MWBE Business Owners', 'Outcome', 'The number of businesses that are owned and operated by MWBE owners to ensure the markets are providing accessibility to populations that are often excluded from business ownership through traditional pathways.', 'Merchants sales tracking document', 'Randi Norris', 'COO', 'Live as merchants are onboarded(as merchants are onboarded)', 'Number of merchants/total merchants', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Excel', 'Self-identification during onboarding', 'To ensure we are prioritizing business ownership for WMBE entrepreneurs.', NULL, NULL, 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (301, 'AGC4326', 4, 'Percentage of stalls offering SNAP and WIC', 'Outcome', 'The number of businesses that are offering SNAP/WIC benefits to shoppers in the markets.', 'Merchants', 'Randi Norris', 'COO', 'Live as merchants are onboarded to accept SNAP/WIC benefits', 'Number of merchants/total merchants', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Excel', 'Merchants often work closely with our team to become certified to accept SNAP/WIC, and we track and support as they are accepted.', 'To provide guidance to our Food Equity Manager on how to support merchants with their applications and encouraging merchants to apply.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (302, 'AGC4326', 4, 'Number of visitors annually at Lexington Market', 'Output', 'Number of visitors at the market per quarter.', 'Placer.ai', 'Randi Norris', 'COO', 'Quarterly', 'Count of annual visitors', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Placer.ai and Excel', 'Track visitors monthly', 'To provide guidance to our Marketing Director, Market Managers and Direct of Market Operations to assess how well we are attracting customers. The markets should continuously maintain or increase visitorship.', NULL, NULL, 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (303, 'AGC4326', 4, 'Percentage of MWBE Business Owners operating in Lexington Market', 'Outcome', 'The number of businesses that are owned and operated by MWBE owners to ensure the markets are providing accessibility to populations that are often excluded from business ownership through traditional pathways.', 'Merchants sales tracking document', 'Randi Norris', 'COO', 'Live as merchants are onboarded (as merchants are onboarded)', 'Number of merchants/total merchants', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Excel', 'Self-identification during onboarding', 'To ensure we are prioritizing business ownership for WMBE entrepreneurs.', NULL, NULL, 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
    (304, 'AGC4326', 4, 'Percentage of stalls offering SNAP and WIC offered at Lexington Market', 'Outcome', 'The number of businesses that are offering SNAP/WIC benefits to shoppers in the markets.', 'Merchants', 'Randi Norris', 'COO', 'Live as merchants are onboarded to accept SNAP/WIC benefits', 'Number of merchants/total merchants', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Excel', 'Merchants often work closely with our team to become certified to accept SNAP/WIC, and we track and support as they are accepted.', 'To provide guidance to our Food Equity Manager on how to support merchants with their applications and encouraging merchants to apply.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.816075'),
