    (453, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of recruits hired', 'Outcome', '# of Sworn Hires', 'HR Sworn & Professional Hiring Vs Attrition Report', 'Brian R. Davis', 'HR Generalist II', 'Weekly', 'Sum of recruits hired', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'BPD Share Drive', 'Database system of record notification & HR processor data verification', 'Data is distributed to internal management, executive command & Baltimore City leadership for executive level decision making purposes.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (454, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of misconduct complaints (per 100 officers)', 'Effectiveness', 'The completed complaints per 100 officers in the department.  Complaints are Internal, External and Ethics.', 'IAPro', 'Jerome Forrest', 'Lieutenant', 'Updated live.', 'Total Q2 cases divided by total sworn, then multiplied by 100. This should decrease for the future.', 'Not Applicable', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'In IAPro', 'Information was retrieved from IAPro', 'The data is analyzed to assess deficiencies.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (455, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of minutes on average from dispatch to arrival on-scene for Priority 1 calls', 'Effectiveness', 'Unit level service time data is used for this measure, as PCalls data does not contain accurate dispatch and arrival times in a standardized date and time format. Calls without an assigned unit are excluded in the initial step. Quarter and year are derived from the call received date and time field. Patrol units are filtered based on unit numbers that conform to patrol unit format. Proactivity is defined using current proactivity measures, including calls coded as 20B (foot patrol), 20C (business check), 20P (bike patrol), and 25 (car stop). Priority 1 calls are identified based on their priority level. Response time for each Priority 1 call is calculated by subtracting the unit dispatched time from the unit arrival time. The average response time is then calculated across all Priority 1 calls. Response times derived from service time data are also compared with Response Time 2 reports pulled from RMS In Pursuit (not limited to patrol units) to ensure the results do not differ significantly.', 'COMSTAT.CFS_SERVICE_TIME', 'Kai Ji', 'Research Analyst Supervisor', 'Live (service time data is updated on a daily basis)', 'Response time for each Priority 1 call is calculated by subtracting the unit dispatched time from the unit arrival time. The average response time is then calculated across all Priority 1 calls.', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', 'minutes', 'N/A', true, NULL, 'BPD Oracle Server', 'Automated system extraction of Calls for Service data provided by ITD', 'Measure response times for high priority calls to track progress toward agency''s response time goal.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (456, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of Items Dispositioned', 'Output', 'the number of items housed in Evidence Management that are dispositioned rather than warehoused', 'SAFETracker', 'Rachel Lucas', 'Director', 'Weekly', 'Sum of items dispositioned', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'SAFETracker', 'run reports from SAFETracker', 'to demonstrate the effectiveness of dispositioning efforts, to show alignment with national best practice, to push for greater compliance from partners, to ensure property is returned to claimants in a timely fashion', NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (457, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of hours spent staffing Juvenile Booking', 'Effectiveness', 'Checking the constant for staffing coverage and use of OT', 'Workday', 'Joanne Wallace', 'Major', 'Weekly', 'Sum of hours spent staffing juvenile booking', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', 'hours', 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Workday and OT Tracker', 'Calculating hours worked across Adam Baker Charlie shifts', 'This is used to ensure continuity of operations and meeting operational need for a 24/7 post.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (458, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of hours of Training conducted to maintain national accreditation', 'Output', 'accreditation and regulatory mandates for CE of forensic science practitioners', 'Ideagen (formerly known as Qualtrax)', 'April Taylor', 'Supervisor, OSU', 'Weekly', 'Sum of training hours', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', 'hours', 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Ideagen', 'Run reports from Ideagen', 'To determine if we are meeting mandates and demonstrating high competency levels of practitioners.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (459, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of helicopter assisted arrests', 'Outcome', 'Number of arrests that Foxtrot recorded as having provided some assistance.', 'Aviation Flight Mission Database.', 'Andre Monroe', 'Sergeant', 'Live (based on when the entry is made to the Mission Database).', '(V2-V1) / (V1) x 100 = % change', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Aviation''s internal Flight Mission Microsoft Access Database.', 'Aviation records individual Flight Missions where they record "Arrest Assists" as a performance measure.', 'It shows that BPD''s helicopters provide value to the agency.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (460, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of events staffed', 'Output', 'Number of events staffed', 'Opengov', 'Alicia White', 'Major', 'Weekly/ Monthly', 'Sum of events staffed', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Opengov, spreadsheet shared drive for Special Events Unit', 'Permitted events Baltimore City Police Department staffed.', 'To project number of permitted events based on current/ previous years.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (461, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of deployments of advanced CrimeScene technology', 'Output', 'We capture how many times drones, 3D scanners and field tests are used on crime scenes', 'CrimePad', 'Rachel Lucas', 'Director', 'Monthly', 'Sum of advanced crime scene tech deployments', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'BPD Forensic Division servers and in the cloud', 'running reports from the CrimePad', 'Helps us to demonstrate the usage of our high-tech investments for improved crime scene work', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (462, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of applications received', 'Output', 'This metric counts the total number of times applications are submitted. It measures application activity, not the number of unique individuals. One applicant may submit multiple applications, and each submission is counted.', 'COB - REC - BPD - Active Applicant Review Business Process - Weekly via Workday', 'Olufunso Onamade', 'Deputy Director', 'Weekly via automated report every Monday at 9:00 AM.', 'Sum of applications received', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Workday, SharePoint Site via BPD Recruitment Section SharePoint', 'Workday automated report designed by BCIT', 'Details application volume down to the second received, allowing the section to evaluate applicant flow, monitor recruitment demand, and identify submission trends over time.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (463, 'AGC5900', 4, '# of 311 requests submitted by BPD', 'Output', 'A daily automated process has been established on the DDS server to extract 311 data from the linked CitiStat server (IP: 10.1.67.97). This process filters requests submitted by BPD personnel by identifying contact email addresses associated with BPD, covering data from 2020 to the present. As a result, the number of 311 requests submitted by BPD personnel can be directly queried from the DDS server.', 'CitiStat.dbo.CSR', 'Kai Ji', 'Research Analyst Supervisor', 'Live (data is updated on a daily basis)', 'City 311 database- sum of 311 requests', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'DDS/CitiStat Server', 'Automated system extraction of 311 data from CitiStat Server', 'The number of 311 requests submitted by BPD personnel has been tracked as part of the community policing effort.', NULL, 'N/A', 'straight-forward', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (464, 'AGC6100', 4, '% of alley cleaning service request closed on time', 'Effectiveness', 'Measure: Percentage of SW-Dirty Alley service requests completed within the established on‑time service standard.
Definition:
This measure tracks the proportion of SW-Dirty Alley service requests that are closed within the department’s defined timeframe for on‑time completion. It compares the total number of alley cleaning requests closed on time to the total number of alley cleaning requests closed during the reporting period.', 'SalesForce', 'John Land', 'Analyst: Solid Waste', 'Live as needed', 'On-time completion rate = # of SW-Dirty Alley requests closed on time/total # of SW-Dirty Alley requests closed x 100', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Salesforce', 'The data is collected from Salesforce using a standardized report. The report should:
•	Filter for SW-Dirty Alley service requests only
•	Filter the closing outcome “Work Completed” and “Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.” Record the c', 'The data is used to understand service demand, evaluate workload, and guide operational decisions. By tracking the number of closed Salesforce service requests for Dirty Alley staff can:
•	Identify trends in citizen reported issues and adjust staffing or routing to areas with higher volumes.
•	Evaluate the effectiveness of field operations by monitoring how often issues are resolved with “Work Completed” or “Reviewed and Closed” outcomes.
•	Prioritize resources based on the types of requests most frequently submitted by residents.
•	Improve service delivery by identifying recurring problem locations or conditions that may require proactive maintenance.
•	Support performance management by providing consistent, measurable data on how quickly and effectively service requests are addressed.
Overall, the measure helps leadership and field teams make data driven decisions that improve cleanliness, responsiveness, and operational efficiency', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (465, 'AGC6100', 4, 'Number of miles swept', 'Output', 'This measure captures the monthly aggregation of actual daily miles swept by each mechanical street‑sweeping driver and truck. Daily mileage recorded through operational logs is summed to produce a monthly total representing overall sweeping activity.', 'Operational logs', 'Rodney Bennett', 'Solid Waste Superintendent', 'Weekly in operational logs', 'Data provided by operation via manual input', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', false, NULL, 'Operational logs in the Street Sweeping division', 'Daily drivers communicate their number of miles swept to clerical staff in mechanical street sweepin division.', 'Tracking the monthly aggregation of actual daily miles swept provides a direct view into the productivity, coverage, and efficiency of mechanical street‑sweeping operations. Because the measure is built from daily activity logs, it reflects what is truly happening in the field—not estimates or scheduled routes.
This data helps operations teams:
- Monitor workload and productivity by showing how much sweeping each driver and truck is completing over time.
- Identify gaps in service coverage, such as routes consistently under‑swept or days where mileage drops unexpectedly.
- Optimize staffing and routing, ensuring resources are aligned with seasonal needs, high‑debris areas, or citizen‑reported hotspots.
- Evaluate equipment performance, since declining mileage may indicate mechanical issues, downtime, or the need for maintenance or replacement.', NULL, NULL, 'Indicate where the operationals logs are stored and how to pull the data to calculate the measure.', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (466, 'AGC6100', 4, 'Number of service requests completed (alleys, streets, and graffiti); citizen generated service request', 'Output', 'This measure counts all citizen generated Salesforce service requests that meet both of the following criteria:
1.	Closing Outcome:
o	Work Completed
o	Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.
2.	Eligible Service Request Types:
•	SW Dirty Alley
•	SW Dirty Street
•	SW Graffiti Removal
•	SW Graffiti Removal – Owner’s Request
Only service requests that match one of the eligible types and have one of the specified closing outcomes are included in the count.', 'SalesForce', 'John Land', 'Data Analyst-Solid Waste', 'Live as needed', 'SalesForce', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Salesforce', 'Download from Salesforce report to filter:
•Service Request Type: SW Dirty Alley, SW Dirty Street, SW Graffiti Removal, SW Graffiti Removal – Owner’s Request
•Closing Outcome: “Work Completed” OR “Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed"', 'The data is used to understand service demand, evaluate workload, and guide operational decisions. By tracking the number of closed Salesforce service requests for Dirty Alley, Dirty Street, and Graffiti Removal, staff can:
•	Identify trends in citizen reported issues and adjust staffing or routing to areas with higher volumes.
•	Evaluate the effectiveness of field operations by monitoring how often issues are resolved with “Work Completed” or “Reviewed and Closed” outcomes.
•	Prioritize resources based on the types of requests most frequently submitted by residents.
•	Improve service delivery by identifying recurring problem locations or conditions that may require proactive maintenance.
•	Support performance management by providing consistent, measurable data on how quickly and effectively service requests are addressed.
Overall, the measure helps leadership and field teams make data driven decisions that improve cleanliness, responsiveness, and operational efficiency', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (467, 'AGC6100', 4, '# of proactive rat inspections', 'Efficiency', 'Definition:
This measure counts the number of proactive Rat Rubout service requests that are completed of Property Management operations. 
Count of SW-Rat Rubout Proactive service requests with closing out comes of “Work Completed” or “Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.”', 'SalesForce', 'Guy Bell', 'Solid Waste Division Chief', 'Live as needed.', 'Count of SW-Rat Rubout Proactive service requests with closing out comes of “Work Completed” or “Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.”', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Salesforce', 'Download from Salesforce into Excel to filter:
•Service Request Type: SW-Rat Rubout Proactive
•Closing Outcome: Work Completed or Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.', 'The number of Rat Rubout Proactive service requests is used to understand the scale, focus, and effectiveness of Rat Rubout operations.

- Monitor operational activity and ensure crews are responding to rodent complaints and proactively treating high‑risk areas.
- Identify hotspots where burrow counts are consistently high, helping teams target neighborhoods or blocks with recurring rodent activity.
- Evaluate program effectiveness by comparing baiting activity with trends in service requests, sightings, or follow‑up inspections.
- Allocate resources strategically, such as adjusting crew assignments, scheduling additional treatments, or coordinating with sanitation teams on contributing factors like trash accumulation.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (468, 'AGC6100', 4, '# of rat burrows baited', 'Outcome', 'Measure: Total number of rat burrows treated with rodent‑control during the reporting period.
Definition:
This measure counts the number of rat burrows that field staff identify and bait as part of Rat Rubout  operations. Each burrow treated is counted once per baiting event. The measure reflects the volume of  rodent‑control interventions performed by the service.', 'SalesForce', 'Guy Bell', 'Solid Waste Division Chief', 'Live as needed', 'Count of SW Rat Rubout, SW-Rat Rubout Follow-up, SW-Rat Rubout Proactive service requests with  closing out comes of “Work Completed” or “Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.”  and with a closing response of Area Baited.', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Salesforce', 'Download from Salesforce into Excel to filter:
•Service Request Type: SW Rat Rubout, SW-Rat Rubout Follow-up, SW-Rat Rubout Proactive
•Closing Outcome: Work Completed or Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.
•Closing Response: Area Baited', 'The number of rat burrows baited is used to understand the scale, focus, and effectiveness of Rat Rubout operations. By tracking how many burrows are treated during a reporting period, the service can:
- Monitor operational activity and ensure crews are responding to rodent complaints and proactively treating high‑risk areas.
- Identify hotspots where burrow counts are consistently high, helping teams target neighborhoods or blocks with recurring rodent activity.
- Evaluate program effectiveness by comparing baiting activity with trends in service requests, sightings, or follow‑up inspections.
- Allocate resources strategically, such as adjusting crew assignments, scheduling additional treatments, or coordinating with sanitation teams on contributing factors like trash accumulation.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (469, 'AGC6100', 4, '% of boarding service requests completed on time', 'Effectiveness', 'Percentage of SW-Boarding service requests completed within the established on‑time service standard.', 'CHIP', 'Guy Bell', 'Solid Waste Division Chief', 'Live as needed.', '% of SW-Boarding SRs completed on time =# of SW-Cleaning SRs completed on time/total # completed x 100', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'CHIP', 'Download from Salesforce into Excel the standard report to filter:
•Filter for SW-Boarding SRs 
•Filter the closing outcome Work Completed and Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed. Record the count as the total SRs
•Filter SLA status Met', 'The on‑time completion rate for SW- Boarding SRs is used to evaluate how reliably and efficiently the service responds . By tracking whether boarding requests are completed within the expected timeframe, operations teams can:
• 	Monitor service performance
The measure shows whether crews are meeting established service‑level expectations and helps identify when performance is improving or slipping.
• 	Identify operational bottlenecks
Patterns of late completions can reveal issues such as staffing shortages, equipment downtime, routing inefficiencies, or high‑volume periods that strain capacity.
• 	Guide resource allocation
Supervisors can adjust staffing, shift assignments, or route planning based on where and when delays are occurring.
• 	Improve customer experience
Timely completion of boarding requests directly affects resident satisfaction and trust in the service.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (470, 'AGC6100', 4, '% of cleaning requests completed on time', 'Effectiveness', 'Percentage of SW-Cleaning service requests completed within the established on‑time service standard.', 'Salesforce', 'Guy Bell', 'Solid Waste Division Chief', 'Live as needed', 'On-time completion rate = # of SW-Cleaning service requests completed on time/total # of SW-cleaning requests completed x 100', 'Increase', NULL, NULL, 'Percent', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Salesforce', 'Download from Salesforce into Excel the standard report to filter:
•Filter for SW-Cleaning SRs 
•Filter the closing outcome Work Completed and Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed. Record the count as the total SRs
•Filter SLA status Met', 'The on‑time completion rate for SW- Cleaning SRs is used to evaluate how reliably and efficiently the service responds to resident needs. By tracking whether cleaning requests are completed within the expected timeframe, operations teams can:
• 	Monitor service performance
The measure shows whether crews are meeting established service‑level expectations and helps identify when performance is improving or slipping.
• 	Identify operational bottlenecks
Patterns of late completions can reveal issues such as staffing shortages, equipment downtime, routing inefficiencies, or high‑volume periods that strain capacity.
• 	Guide resource allocation
Supervisors can adjust staffing, shift assignments, or route planning based on where and when delays are occurring.
• 	Improve customer experience
Timely completion of cleaning requests directly affects resident satisfaction and trust in the service.', NULL, NULL, 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, false, false, true, true, 'Validated', '2026-06-01', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.817077'),
    (471, 'AGC6100', 4, 'Number of service requests related to rats', 'Outcome', 'This measure counts the number of Rat Rubout service requests that are completed of Property Management operations. 
Count of SW Rat Rubout, SW-Rat Rubout Follow-up, SW-Rat Rubout Proactive service requests with closing out comes of “Work Completed” or “Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.”', 'SalesForce', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Live as needed.', 'Count of SW Rat Rubout, SW-Rat Rubout Follow-up, SW-Rat Rubout Proactive service requests with closing out comes of “Work Completed” or “Your issue has been reviewed and is considered closed.”', 'Decrease', NULL, NULL, 'Count', NULL, 'N/A', true, NULL, 'Salesforce', 'Download from Salesforce into Excel to filter:
