    (1182, 662, 2023, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1183, 680, 2023, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1636, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1184, 1, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 210000, 'During Fiscal 2024, customers have become more familiar with using the online payment service which can answer most of the customer''s concerns during the initial prompts. Through the Paymentus payment provider, customers have more payment options at a lower cost. The Bureau''s website is more user friendly to assist customers with basic information. The city has a number of programs that helps individuals and families avoid tax sale by way of grans, deferments and the Mayor''s decision to remove owner occupied properties from the tax sale for the last several years.', 330000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1185, 2, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.71, 'Again, this service factor remains at 71%. Service requests are handled as quickly as possible by the call center, but the call center depends on other departments and Bureaus for assistance in helping the client. For some time, the Bureau had been understaffed by 15-20%.', 0.95, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1186, 3, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5, 'The average wait times for the call center have been steadily decreasing since the pandemic. It is anticipated that the 7-minute wait-time will maintain over the next year with the required staffing levels.', 7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1187, 4, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.99, 'During the tax sale of May 2024, the Mayor and City Council removed owner occupied properties from the tax sale. While 96% of the total real estate property taxes were actually received, the owner-occupied properties were removed from tax sale and lowered the number of properties that were collectible. Thus, creating a 99% collection rate for the remaining properties that were still subject to tax sale.', 0.96, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1188, 5, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'The City did not issue any GO bonds in Fiscal 2024 which led to a 0% rate on GO bonds issued.', 0.035, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1189, 6, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'In FY24 the city was operating under the old ERP, which allowed for greater vendor flexibility.', 5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1190, 7, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 11848, 'City was in midst of COVID pandemic operating under emergency procurements, allowing for increased spending.', 17500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1191, 8, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 11517, 'City was in midst of COVID pandemic operating under emergency procurements, allowing for increased spending.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1192, 9, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.55, 'In FY24 BOE met on a weekly basis to discuss contract approval.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1193, 10, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 104, NULL, 104, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1194, 11, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1325, 'City coming out of pandemic and replacing outdated equipment with new assets.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
