    (1258, 82, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 273, 'Decrease in number of collisions based on purchase and implementation of driving simulator program that is used to teach new recruits in a more realistic way.', 260, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1259, 83, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.74, 'Target established based on decrease in number of accidents over the past 3 years along with implementation of new program with simulator.', 0.75, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1260, 85, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.048, 'The percentage of maintenance and repair outside of regular wear and tear was 5% in FY24, which was unchanged from FY23. A large amount of these repairs originated with DPW – Solid Waste, and if we focus just on that division this metric is at 15.2%. Fleet continues to collaborate productively with DPW to find solutions through training, analytics, and close communication.', 0.07, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1261, 86, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.8179, 'Public Safety Fleet Availability, which is primarily represents marked police availability, declined slightly from 83% to 82%, which still exceeded our target of 80%. During FY24 Fleet added 72 new marked police vehicles, enough to decrease the median age of marked police vehicles from 6.5 in June 2023 to 3.0 years in June 2024. However, problems with recruitment and retention of technicians prevented Fleet from achieving an overall increase in this metric.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1262, 87, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.6172, 'Routine Services Availability fell from 65% in FY23 to 62% in FY24, in spite of an increase in the target for this metric from 70% to 75%. The higher target reflected confidence in Fleet that bringing new load packers into the Fleet would increase routine services availability.  _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
As it turns out, 26 new load packers went into service in FY24, but the median age for this vehicle type still increased from 4.4 years in the first month of the fiscal year to 4.8 years in its last. The city’s street sweepers, another key component of the routine services fleet, also aged substantially and saw poor availability (51% on average in FY24). These issues, combined with staffing and recruitment challenges for heavy equipment technicians as well as inexperienced operators at the agencies we serve, drove down our overall numbers for routine services.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1263, 89, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, 'The FY24 energy intensity of the portfolio of buildings included in DGS'' metric did not change significantly compared to FY23. DGS is not aware of any major capital projects or other energy efficiency projects that would have significantly shifted the energy use of the portfolio.', 60, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1264, 90, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1406501, 'In FY2024 there was an increase in available grant funds from the Maryland Energy Administration, through increased revenue from the Strategic Energy Investment Fund. DGS successfully increased its awards. In FY2024 DGS also secured the first rebates from the Direct Pay incentive from the IRS through the Inflation Reduction Act.', 1000000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1265, 92, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.18, 'The percentage of City government renewable energy usage did not meet the target in FY24 because in the absence of a legal or contractual mandate otherwise, the City purchases the lesser of: Renewable Energy Credits (SREC) or the Renewable Portfolio Standard (RPS) compliance fee. In FY24, the compliance fee was less than the Solar REC cost, which consists of 2% of the RPS requirement.', 0.2, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1266, 93, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.49, 'While CM on time delivery  improved from FY23, it did not hit the target. This was due to contractual issues. In February, the Contracts team worked on an Emergency Procurement Request, which was submitted on 02/21/2024 but did not get added to Workday until 03/14/2024. However, the contract proposal did not go to the board until June. Between February and July, the emergency contract was out of funds and therefore NAC was unable to perform work. During this period, J.F Fischer, our main HVAC vendor, had to step in to respond to emergencies, taking up more time and delaying them from attending to more routine work requests. From February to July, Fischer’s performance decreased as they were asked to fill in the gap left by NAC’s depleted funds. There were two backlog mass closing events in FY24. One in January 2023 and one in April 2024, both times negatively impacting the on time delivery rate.', 0.55, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1267, 94, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.97, 'This year''s elevator performance was impacted by three passenger elevators out of service for much of 2023. There was one elevator down in Mitchell Courthouse, one elevator down in Enoch Pratt Free Library Central Branch, and an elevator down in the Dr. Ralph W.E Jones Administration Building.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1268, 96, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.53, 'This KPI tracks the Department''s performance in managing HVAC maintenance and repair. It includes preventative maintenance (PM) activities for systems such as boilers, chillers, cooling towers, HVAC units, and HVAC infrastructure. FMD has worked to improve scheduling and planning of PM tasks with stakeholders, allowing both vendors and in-house staff to complete work more efficiently and reduce overall work duration. FMD saw an improvement in PM on time delivery for FY 2024, despite an increase in daily elevator PMs, which were meant to ensure accurate reporting of elevator availability. The increase in this performance metric indicates that the improvements to utilizing vendor support, scheduling, and planning made in previous fiscal years have worked. Moreover, better record keeping and date entry has contributed to a rise in PM on time delivery.', 0.55, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1269, 97, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'During Fiscal 2024, all construction projects were completed on time, which had a significant positive impact on performance. The timely completion contributed to higher efficiency, improved client satisfaction, and allowed the division to meet its planned milestones. As a result, the performance percentage increased, positively influencing the overall Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 0.89, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1270, 98, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.71, 'Throughout Fiscal 2024, most projects performed near the projected target percentage, with some variation in outcomes due to unforeseen site conditions and occasional errors or omissions in the construction documents. Given the unique challenges associated with each project, predicting outcomes with full accuracy is difficult. These factors led to occasional time extensions and or adjustments in project scope, influencing the overall performance and contributing to variances from the anticipated results. These elements played a significant role in shaping the Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 0.73, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1271, 99, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'During Fiscal 2024, all projects successfully fulfilled the MBE goal requirements, contributing to exceeding the target percentage and achieving a positive overall outcome. However, multiple factors influence the final results, including changes in project scope, unforeseen site conditions, owner requests, and the performance of subcontractors. These factors, by impacting timelines, project costs, and efficiency, can play a role in shaping the outcomes.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1272, 100, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.86, 'During Fiscal 2024, the balance of projects completed successfully met the planned WBE target. However, in the case of one project, a single driving factor led to the final outcome being slightly below 100%. This project experienced an account error by the prime contractor, which resulted in a lower participation percentage than initially expected. After investigating the issue and taking corrective action, the error was resolved shortly after the performance data on this metric was submitted. Furthermore, the number of projects completed during the performance reporting cycle can significantly influence the final performance percentage. When fewer projects are completed, the impact of each project''s performance is more pronounced, thus having a larger effect on the overall outcome.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1273, 102, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.88, 'During Fiscal 2024, one of our design projects experienced a delay in delivery due to the need for additional time to complete quality assurance (QA) and quality control (QC) procedures, which were not initially accounted for in the project timeline. This unforeseen delay impacted our ability to meet the planned schedules and caused a shift in expected completion dates, affecting the overall progress of the project. As a result, this time-related issue became a significant factor in the divergence from our target percentage.', 0.92, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1274, 103, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 12575, 'In FY24, the sexual health and wellness clinics implemented a new electronic medical record. This transition impacted operations.  We also lost several staff due to attrition, including a medical director of the program.  								_x000D_
_x000D_', 15000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1275, 104, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 927, 'Several factors impacted the program in FY24 including 2 support staff vacancies one vacant and one on FMLA. Additionally one of our dentists retired. Building conditions at the Druid location also affected patient volume. And our transition to a new electronic medical record required a few weeks of staff training which impacted patient appointments. 								_x000D_
_x000D_', 1750, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1276, 105, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'The TB program has nurse case managers focused on ensuring those who have active TB receive TB medication. The program also utilizes electronic software to maximize adherence and recording of adherence to medication.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1277, 106, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'The Tuberculosis clinic has a full time Public Health Investigator who conducts all case investigations for active TB cases', 0.92, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1278, 107, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.56, 'Changes in our electronic reporting system and the vacancy of the team''s data analyst may have impacted the quality of the data recording and/or extraction for FY24.  Staffing limitations, including lack of a medical director overseeing the program, may have also impacted quality of linkages.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1279, 108, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 513, 'In FY24, the blood lead "level of concern" - in essence, the blood lead level at which education and environmental inspections are mandated - was decreased from 5mg/dL to 3.5 mg/dL.  This change has resulted in a marked increase in the number of children referred to Healthy Homes and the number of environmental inspections required.  In FY25, Healthy Homes staff will endeavor to conduct environmental assessments for this increased number of clients.  All in-home visits, whether initiated by a lead or asthma concern, include an assessment for in-home lead hazards and provide resources, referrals, and interim lead hazard reduction education with the goal of mitigating lead hazards as immediately as possible.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1280, 109, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.37, 'There are two main factors that contributed to the Fiscal 2024 actual data: the increase in the number of cases for elevated blood lead levels and the hiring and training of new staff. The increase in the number of cases for elevated  blood lead levels was due to the lowering of the threshold to be a lead level of concern. This changed from 5mg/dL to 3.5 mg/dL. While this increased the number of children referred to the program for our services, not all parents/guardians wanted to have their home inspected if their child had a low lead level. In these cases, we still offered a home inspection as well as education on how to lower the lead level. Additionally, the hiring and training of environmental sanitarian staff also impacted the FY24 actual data. Environmental Sanitarians go through intensive training and as a result it takes time for them to be able to perform inspections. This has been a difficult position to hire and train which is reflected in the FY24 data.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 0.5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1281, 110, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.95, 'A child with asthma requires an emergency room visit when his/her asthma symptoms have worsened such that they are no longer responding to at-home medications and their difficulty breathing is causing symptoms associated with lack of oxygen. While there is no single factor that has been identified, it is believed that a combination of factors impacted the FY24 data: Families were willing to allow staff into their homes to: 1. assess the environmental triggers and provide mitigation efforts; 2. provide in-person observation of medicatoion technique and training where necessary.  Further the program provided the tools and supplies necessary to reduce environmental triggers; Staff received on-going training on how to identify and mitigate triggers and proper medication technique.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 0.95, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1282, 113, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 707519, 'In FY24 the program was impacted by several external factors that resulted in a continued decrease of client visits and subsequently the number of syringes distributed. One primary factor is the number of newly established SSPs now operating within Baltimore City which continues to increase and stood at 8 during this period. Most of these commuity-based organization syringe service programs offer the same or similar services via various outreach models. This has resulted in the defusion of our client-base and a subsequent decline in visits to our mobile units. Although we anticipate a slight increase in this performance measure, we do not think it will rise back to FY22 or FY21 level of service.', 2000000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1283, 117, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3940, 'The adolescent and reproductive health office is struggling to achieve the client volumes we had pre-COVID.  In addition, our long-time Director retired, which was a tremendous loss to the City.', 5200, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1284, 118, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 204, 'M&I exceeded its target of 150 families served (25 families for each of six nurses). The following factors influenced the number of clients served: 1) M&I was nearly fully staffed the entire year with experienced nurses, which enabled M&I to maintain a nearly full caseload; 2) increased nursing compensation increased nurse retention; 3) M&I implemented a highly successful continuous quality improvement project to increase the percentage of referrals converted to enrollment and had the support of a newly hired Community Health Educator III to outreach referred families and educate them about program benefits; and 4) several families in the program graduated, making space for additional families to be served beyond the 150 target caseload.', 150, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1285, 119, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.97, 'The Maternal & Infant Care Program (M&I) exceeded its target of 90% of children receiving a social-emotional development screening at recommended intervals. Factors that influenced their success include 1) M&I was nearly fully staffed with experienced nurses the entire year who have expertise in social-emotional screening with the ASQ:SE screening tool; 2) increased nursing compensation, which led to improved nurse retention; 3) maintaining a hybrid (in person and virtual) home visiting schedule, which means families are more likely to keep their appointments and more likely to be retained in the program; and 4) M&I''s work is supported with a strong evidence-based home visiting model (Nurse-Family Partnership) that prioritizes social-emotional screening and improving child development.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1286, 120, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 281000, 'The number of visits to school health suites increased by approximately 14% over the prior year''s performance.  Dring this same period there was an increase in the number of schools that were assigned a full-time nurse.  This allowed for more students with chronic health conditions who may have needed skilled nursing visits to be treated in the health suite.', 273000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1287, 121, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.63, 'This target has been impacted by the availability of nurse practitioners in school-based health centers.  During 2024 the coverage was reduced to one part-time nurse practitioner supplemented by the Clinical Director who also provided direct care to students part-time.  As such, the focus was on providing care for acute needs.  Students who were obese are typically identified either during a physical or while being treated for another health condition.  They are given brief counseling and sometimes fail to report for furthermore in-depth nutrition education.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 0.65, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1288, 122, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.87, 'This performance measures the percentage of students returning to class after a visit to the health suite for a minor injury or acute illness. Since COVID-19 has moved into the endemic phase, we are seeing fewer cases and less transmission in the community,  As such fewer hildren are reporting to the health suite with complaints that would require them to be sent home from school.  Further, as full-time registered nurse coverage has increased, students have greater access to care from a higher level nursing professional who is more likely to recommend that the student remain in school.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1289, 123, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1807, 'Extended program vacancies, challenges recruiting nurses and the discontinuation of a clinical staffing contract impacted the Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 2700, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1290, 124, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 884, 'Extended program vacancies, challenges recruiting nurses and the discontinuation of a clinical staffing contract impacted the Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 2700, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1291, 125, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 9755, 'Extended program vacancies impacted the Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 13728, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1292, 126, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 343, 'The program surpassed the FY24 target due to the inclusion of COVID and Mpox outbreaks.', 30, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1293, 127, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.87, 'FY24 data was impacted by the inclusion of COVID and Mpox outbreaks. The percent of outbreaks with confirmed etiology surpassed the targets due to rigorous investigations and timely reporting of laboratory results.', 0.75, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1294, 128, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 657, 'The program exceeded its annual target by 157 additional agency, organizational and program staff trained on Trauma Informed Care. The city agency trained in FY24 was Baltimore City Recreation and Parks, who had over 300 staff trained by the sub-contracted training provider. Program staff obtained requests for training from other agencies including the Housing Authority of Baltimore City, the State''s Attorney Office, City Schools, Transformation Health LLC, MOAAME, and MONSE. This level of interest and participation, coupled with the size of our legislated agency (BCRP) helped to boost our training outputs, enabling us to exceed our annual goal.', 500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1295, 129, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 226, 'FY24 was the first year the program began tracking for this metric, as the suicide prevention coordinator was onboarded in third quarter of FY23. The program reviewed data during FY24 to determine the baseline. During that period, the suicide prevention coordinator reached 226 including students, teachers, and parents through community outreach, presentations, and school engagement. While the program''s suicide prevention coordinator position is funded, there is no funding to implement additional prevention strategies beyond the education and awareness and activities including promotion of the 988 Campaign and distribution of gun safety locks to reduce access to lethal means.  All things considered, the program exceeded the annual target of 150, which was a good first year accomplishment.', 0, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1296, 131, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.87, 'The FY24 actual data was 3 points below the annual target. Trauma Informed Care''s framework was created in 1994 and has been gaining momentum in our city over the past 10 years. We suspect that many of the staff have heard of the concept, and we know that some have attended similar trainings previously. It is possible the decline in percentage satisfaction was due to trainees with previous training experience did benefit from learn anything new, thus contributing to their response on the post survey.   Another contributing factor can be that for anyone who is triggered during the training, may rate the training differently based on how adverse effected they were by a discussion during the training. Further research and analysis are required to validate that theory.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1297, 132, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.956, 'FY24 actual on the percentage change in increased knowledge of the content and how to apply concepts have exceeded our annual target of 90% by 6 percentage points.  Our data regarding this metric have been consistently in the 90-95% range. It has been our experience that many trainees, particularly if it''s the first time they''ve had the training, usually report learning something a new fact, technique, etc. during training. This is a metric that is usually responded to favorably.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1298, 133, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 11172, 'Animal shelter intake has drastically increased nationally. Limited community resources, lack of veterinary professionals, and housing instability have all been cited as reasons for the steep incline, which holds true specifically for our City residents.', 10000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1299, 134, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1300, 135, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.84, 'It has been difficult for the shelter to maintain a high release rate with limited resources for the community and a higher animal intake and as a result the shelter''s live release has been declining.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1301, 136, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4964, 'In FY24, EIS filled (3) food inspector vacancies.  It takes approximately 4-6 months to fully train the food inspectors.  Once trained, the inspectors are allowed to inspect facilities on their own.  The increased number of food facility staff conducting inspections greatly increased the FY24 actual by nearly 1,600 inspections.', 3750, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1302, 137, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.968, 'This PM saw a 4% increase as Supervisors increased their monitoring of the 311 system to ensure complaints are closed in a more timely manner.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1303, 138, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, 'The FY24 actual stayed consistent with FY23 final plan review inspection.  The 2 day average is still within the target number of days.', 5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1304, 139, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 149, 'One factor that impacted the actual FY24 data was an issue with contracts. There was a delay in contract approval, so staff were unable to conduct compliance checks for a majority of the fiscal year.', 1000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1305, 141, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6020, 'As the HIV epidemic changes, the focus of a successful intervention is evolving from solely focusing on testing numbers, to ensuring high impact programming with high risk individuals and communities. This is not always reflected solely in testing volumes. This year we were intentional about choosing new locations for the outreach team, and in particular focused on adding sites to focus on women, and increasing conversations about HIV prevention PrEP medication.  Some sites were successful based on conversations with high risk individuals, not based on testing numbers alone.  Other factors impacing FY24 data include the agency''s transition to a new electronic medical record which required our team to spend considerable time being trained in the new system (implemented June 2024), and the mobile van frequently requiring preventative maintenance and repairs which takes it out of service for several weeks at a time.', 12000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1306, 142, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'The Ryan White program''s subrecipients are effective in achieving undetectable viral loads for clients when they are actively engaged in care. The BCHD Ryan White team consistently engaged with itssubrecipients to provide technical assistance and facilitate quality improvement. Lastly, during FY24 a new fiscal agent was established and coordinated and carried out the fiscal requirements for operating the Ryan White program.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1307, 143, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.55, '"There are several reasons why we did not reach our target. First, some patients who are newly diagnosed with HIV are classified by the health department team as ""unable to locate."" The health department team reaches out to every individual newly diagnosed with HIV. However, if they do not answer their phone or are not available at the home address that is provided, it is difficult for the health department team to find them to conduct an interview. The team has a protocol that is followed for each patient, including multiple calls and site visits.  Reasons a patient might be unable to be located include unstable housing, mental health diagnoses, moving out of jurisdiction (without our knowledge), incorrect contact information associated at the time of the lab test, and/or unwillingness to engage/talk with the health department._x000D_
_x000D_
"', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1308, 144, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 43640, 'Numbers did not meet target numbers due to the change in methodology for collecting data.', 56000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1309, 145, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 25512, 'Numbers were higher than anticipated due to the launch of additional programs and services at centers.', 10000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1310, 146, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 40521, 'Numbers were higher than anticipated due to the launch of additional programs and services at centers.', 18000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1311, 147, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 28942, 'The Maryland Access Point (MAP) team increased its community outreach during FY 2024, attending resource events throughout Baltimore City. Staff engagement with local communities and dissemination of literature with the MAP phone number generated an increase in calls.', 23336, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1312, 148, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1149, 'The program received fewer complaints than anticipated in FY 2024. Complaint volume tends to be linked to the ability of the Ombudsman team to conduct regular outreach to nursing homes and assisted living facilities. In FY 2024, staff vacancies reduced the number of visits.', 1200, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1313, 149, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 780, 'The number of SHIP Medicare benefit counseling sessions is impacted by changes in Medicare plans affecting beneficiaries in Baltimore. In FY 2024, there were no significant changes, and no withdrawal of plans, resulting in future requests for counseling sessions.', 991, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1314, 150, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 140, 'The RSVP program has recovered from the COVID-19 pandemic. The number of volunteers participating has grown as they are able to become engaged in the community with less fear of infection.', 115, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1315, 151, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 56, 'None. The clients in this program are court appointed based on medical needs.', 40, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1316, 152, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 144, 'Additional grant funds were received for FY''2024 which allowed the program to hire additional staff. The sizeable increase in new clients is a direct reflection of the increased staffing levels.', 40, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1317, 153, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 26, 'The total number of program slots is established at 72 participants based on funding. Approximately 20-25 participants are new participants.', 70, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1318, 154, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 22, 'The number of volunteers has decreased due to the aftermath of Covid. Recruitment for both staff and volunteers is underway.', 30, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1319, 155, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6845, 'The number of participants in the TaxiCard program continues to rise, as older adults and persons with disabilities seek affordable transportation alternatives.  Reduced concerns about COVIO-19 infections have resulted in more enrollees in the program.', 5330, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1320, 156, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2699, 'Participation was within range of the 2024 goal. Numbers are different from 2023 due to a change in methodology for collecting data to more accurately capture active participants for the year.', 2500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1321, 157, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1684, 'Participation was within range of the 2024 goal. Participants are annually assessed for need and those with the most need are prioritized.', 1500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1322, 158, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.84, 'The community-based meal program continues to be shaped by participant feedback for meal improvement. Currently meals are still under emergency contract while the bid is being finalized.', 0.94, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1323, 159, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5932, 'Lingering COVID impacts, inflation and buyer trepidation, NPOs and agencies slow to report', 7000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1324, 160, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.99, 'This is a new performance measure selected for FY26.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1325, 161, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.98, 'This is a new performance measure selected for FY26. The previous PM was “% of activities carried out by sub-recipients and City agencies that met contractual goals.” DHCD has no control over the ability of CDBG grant subrecipients to meet their proposed goals. As such, this is not an accurate indicator of the service''s effectiveness.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1326, 162, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, 'This number is dictated by the licensing by the State of Maryland', 60, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1327, 163, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4000, 'Staffing cost, service contracts, food and all other programmatic related cost.', 4000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1328, 164, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.99, 'This was not a metric in 2024', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1329, 165, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 324, 'This is a new metric that we began tracking for FY26', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1330, 166, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 23, 'This metric was updated to encapsulate all types of service measures provided by the Weatherization department.  Previous outcomes were impacted by residual affects of the pandemic and by unstable staffing.  In FY25 this service line has gained stable leadership and unfilled positions have been or will be filled shortly', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1331, 167, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17, 'This is a new metric and FY24 data is unavailable.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1332, 168, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 158, '158 increase due to increase funding made available', 100, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1333, 169, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 695, 'New metric for FY26', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1334, 170, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.93, '93% increase was due to the amount of funding make available.', 0.4, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1335, 171, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 148711, 'We fell short of our goal by 41,289 inspections.  This was a direct result of the attrition.  During this period, we experienced a staffing decrease due to retirement, individuals moving on to other opportunities, and workforce challenges in the hiring process.  Despite these challenges, Code Enforcement continued to serve the residents of Baltimore while protecting personnel in the sometimes-challenging street environment.', 190000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1336, 172, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.87, 'In FY24 we were able to exceed our target by closing 70,011 or (87%) of Service Requests on time. This was achieved by following our standard operating procedures which require managers to assign SRs to inspectors while holding them accountable for those not addressed within the allotted timeframe. Active management oversight is necessary to ensure that this metric is accomplished.', 0.85, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1337, 173, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.85, 'The number of available vacant properties routinely breached by those suffering from the effects of poverty, homelessness, mental health issues, and drug addiction created an escalation in interagency requests from the Department of Public Works Solid Waste Division, Baltimore City Fire Department and the Mayor’s Office.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1338, 174, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1826, 'New Metric for FY26', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1339, 175, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 33484, 'Staffing in both the Registration & Licensing Office and Special Investigation Unit have impacted the ability to do proactive outreach and enforcement actions. The office manager retired this year which required recruiting a new manager and training them in their role. The Office Support Specialist positions have been particularly difficult to recruit and retain quality staff members. This makes it difficult to make progress in increasing registered and licensed properties.', 60000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1340, 176, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.35, 'Similar to metric one, staffing in both the Registration & Licensing Office and Special Investigation Unit have impacted the ability to do proactive outreach and enforcement actions. The office manager retired this year which required recruiting a new manager and training them in their role. The Office Support Specialist positions have been particularly difficult to recruit and retain quality staff members. This makes it difficult to make progress in increasing registered and licensed properties. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
 _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
This service has benefitted from additional attention to the need to be licensed in educational materials and the inability to proceed in failure to pay rent actions without having a proper license.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1341, 177, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17105, 'The lower revenue received in FY24 impacted the amount of city funding available per affordable rental and homeownership units created. Each year, funding allocations are based on budget and revenue received. Despite receiving less revenue in FY24 compared to FY23, we increased our goal to align with strategic priorities and ensure continued support for affordable housing initiatives.', 30000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1342, 178, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 16.38, 'The lower revenue received through local funds has directly impacted the actual fiscal year 2024 data.', 10, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1343, 179, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 24, 'We successfully funded multiple homeownership projects through the Community Land Trust program, creating and subsidizing affordable homeownership opportunities.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1344, 180, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 190, 'Revenue estimates for fiscal year 2024 were lower than those for fiscal year 2023, which was unexpected given the consistent revenue growth in prior years.', 250, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1345, 181, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.73, 'DHCD successfully achieved its target, completing at least 70% of property dispositions within 120 days.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1346, 182, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.41, 'DHCD exceeded its FY24 target and remains committed to reviewing and refining the compliance process to ensure purchasers adhere to the terms of their Land Disposition Agreements. Each Use and Occupancy permit issued represents a significant milestone in advancing the Mayor’s vacancy reduction initiative', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1347, 183, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 180, 'DHCD surpassed its FY24 target and continues to expand the number of in rem acquisitions, aligning with the Mayor’s vacancy reduction initiative.', 200, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1348, 184, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 970, 'DHCD surpassed its FY24 target and continues to expand the number of acquisitions assigned, aligning with the Mayor’s vacancy reduction initiative.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1349, 185, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 123, 'The FY 24 goal was 50 houses remediated for lead.  This goal was surpassed by 73._x000D_
