    (1433, 334, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.85, 'The actual FY24 data aligning with the target was a result of a combination of strategic planning increased funding community support eﬃcient project execution and favorable external conditions. These factors work together to ensure that the necessary amount of public art access was achieved.', 0.85, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1434, 335, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.6, 'The grant recipients who are black artists or belong to Black-LED organizations in FY24 matching the target reﬂects a combination of targeted outreach, supportive policies, and eﬀorts to increase racial equity in the arts.', 0.6, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1435, 336, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.5, 'FY24 was a combination of targeted outreach, supportive programs, cultural shifts advocating for gender equity, and the historical participation trends of women in the arts. This also reﬂects a measured and strategic eﬀort, so you continue improving gender equity in the grant making process, with the goal of eventually achieving gender parity in arts funding.', 0.5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1436, 337, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 90, 'The city''s strategic planning and judicious use of funds resulted in meeting the ﬁscal year target exemplifying eﬀective ﬁnancial stewardship and operational eﬃciency.', 90, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1437, 339, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.085, 'Eﬀective marketing strategies and proactive tenant engagement likely played a role attracting and retaining tenants, ensuring that studio spaces remained occupied throughout the year.', 0.85, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1438, 340, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4000, 'The annual attendance was attributed to a combination of strategic marketing initiatives and engaging events.', 5000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1439, 344, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 191691, 'The FY24 target was set at 205,000, with actual attendance reaching 191,691 from 72 events. This metric is a new approach to tracking the agency’s 18-month sales performance. Determining conversion rates for leads over an extended period requires additional benchmarking to establish accurate trends. Throughout the year, we reviewed the data fields in our event management system to ensure accurate data capture. Specifically, we focus on the "source code" field, utilizing totals from source code values such as Facility, Facility and Hotel, and Facility and Visitors Bureau. Public events are the largest driver of attendance. For recurring annual events, such as the Autoshow, B''more Healthy Expo, Tattoo Convention, and Comic-Con, the Visitors Bureau is not required to sell the venue, as these events are already established.', 205000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1440, 345, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 113, 'The FY24 Target was 73 with the actualized is 113. This is a good variance as we got more business than anticipated.', 73, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1441, 346, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 10.08, 'The target revenue for FY24 was set at $11.45 million, while actual revenue totaled $10.08 million, resulting in a variance of $1.37 million. This difference is primarily attributed to the uncertainty surrounding partner contracts at the time. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Planning for the Convention Center’s FY24 began in July 2022, during a period of recovery from the COVID-19 pandemic. This recovery impacted attendance, event numbers, and booking windows, with events becoming more short-term than in previous years. Additionally, the unknown commission percentages for four revenue-generating partner contracts and the retirement of the agency’s Executive Director contributed to the challenges. To establish the revenue target, we calculated rental revenues based on contracted events and high-quality leads, then factored in recent performance data from our revenue partners, specifically from FY19. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
In terms of actual performance, Food and Beverage commissions were recognized as revenue starting in Q3, in line with contractual terms (Q1 and Q2 revenues were allocated to reserve accounts). As a result, we realized $1.3 million in commissions, compared to a forecast of $2 million. Furthermore, the Convention Center provided complimentary rent for two significant events—the CIAA (the HBCU annual basketball tournament) and the National Minority Supplier Development Council Conference & Business Opportunity. These events would have generated approximately $838,000 in rental income. However, the broader economic impact of these events, including the influx of attendees to the city, is even more substantial. If the Convention Center had received full rent for these events and Food and Beverage commissions, actual revenue would have exceeded $12 million.', 11.45, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1442, 347, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.89, 'The Convention Center developed a web-based tool for client feedback, which is sent after each event. Responses are automatically reported into a database, analyzed through Microsoft BI, and shared with senior staff via a TEAMS channel. The tool allows for filtering by year, fiscal year, and provides detailed insights by event. Over the past three years, the average survey return rate has been 26.1%. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
In FY24, the Convention Center reported an overall customer satisfaction rate of 89%. Upon further review, an error was discovered, and the actual satisfaction level for the fiscal year is 92%. The 89% figure reflected satisfaction from January to June 2024, while the period from July to December 2023 had a satisfaction rating of 96%. Incorrect data selections for past fiscal years led to this reporting discrepancy. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
For FY22, the overall satisfaction rating was 93%. From July 2021 to December 2021, the rating was 95%, while from January to June 2022, it was 92%. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The FY23 satisfaction rating was reported as 94% as of February 1, 2023, with the final rating for the year being 92%. The Ppowerapps tool for KPI tracking was rolled out early in 2023, so the number reported was the most up to date number at that time. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The primary areas for improvement identified in the feedback include building cleanliness (which is also influenced by the building''s age) and the facility’s ability to adapt to the specific needs of clients. We are focused on improving scores in these areas for FY26, as well as increasing the return rate for satisfaction surveys.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1443, 348, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 443444, 'The FY24 target was 338,400 with the actualized being 443,444. This is a variance of 105,044.', 338400, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1444, 351, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.16, 'Lack of housing navigators and access points across the system', 0.25, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1445, 352, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.24, 'Exceeded target', 0.15, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1446, 353, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3260, NULL, 3800, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1447, 354, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 174, 'The city of Baltimore continues to struggle with accesible access points for residents expereiencing  that will be able to complete their coordinated access infomration which is critical to clients experiencing homelessness. Our lack of  shelter is contributing to our inability to decrease the lenght of time clients are on the street. This upcoming year, we will focus on increasing access points within our continuum.', 90, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1448, 355, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1487, 'PIT not conducted in 2024', 2200, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
    (1449, 356, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1191, 'The purchase of two hotels has lead to the increase from FY2023. Double room occupancy has also increased our bed count as we continue to move forward with post pandemic shelter operations. MOHS is also working to identify permanent shelter locations for our homeless citizens', 1535, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.997112'),
