    (1457, 365, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.159, NULL, 0.15, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1458, 366, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 38, 'The ECB has a new case management system that allows the hearing officers to note when an interpreter is used in a hearing. That has helped us with tracking. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
In terms of the use of Language Line in general, the ECB has worked with MIMA to get us a Legal Interpretation account which is different from a regular account. We have also started to translate more documents, including general correspondence, notices, and decisions. We believe that our willingness to accommodate non-English speaking residents helps them to trust in our process and feel comfortable using the interpretation service in their hearings.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1459, 367, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9398, 'The ECB has created an efficient scheduling process. In FY24 we started a new tracking process to prevent hearing requests from "falling through the cracks" and our proactive approach to addressing properties with multiple citations helps us to consolidate citations into one hearing date.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1460, 368, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'It should be noted that the performance metric is in decimal points because it is a percentage. In FY24, the Board agreed with 100% of the hearing officers'' decisions. This shows that the hearing officers are conducting these hearings using sound judgement.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1461, 369, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 9.93, 'FY24 was the first year that we tracked the turnaround time for the hearing officers'' response. Previously, we were tracking general resolution but not the timing. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
We have a good process set up but it is still a highly manual process that is impacted by things like staffing and requests for additional information from citing agencies. Despite those factors, we were still able to perform efficiently.', 14, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1462, 370, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 8.14, 'The FY24 actual data was very favorable because that agency was able to do proactive resolution of open citations before the Final Bill and Legal Notice was sent out. We pulled reports to see what was outstanding and prioritized "low hanging fruit" - citations with partial payments, citations that "fell through the cracks" because of a property transfer, etc.', 14, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1463, 371, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1464, 372, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 289500000, NULL, 220000000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1465, 373, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 96, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1466, 374, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 681, NULL, 2750, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1467, 376, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 105, 'MOED relies on referrals from the school system to meet their enrollment numbers at the YO Academy. Since we cannot recruit on our own, MOED has little control over the output related to the number of students that attend the school. For those referred by BCPS, students benefit from a focused learning environment and multiple levels of instruction, as well as access to job readiness and career services offered at YO Baltimore. An additional factor affecting the actual numbers is that students may transfer back to their home school.', 120, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1468, 377, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.06, 'MOED, BCPS, and BCCC piloted Blueprint in multiple schools in Spring 2024 and began servicing all middle and high schools in Fall 2024. The FY24 goals reflect the fact that the focus in this pilot year was on hiring and onboarding staff, developing school plans, relationship-building within schools to ensure student access, and collecting information about students to determine baseline competencies and establish timelines.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1469, 378, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'MOED, BCPS, and BCCC piloted Blueprint in multiple schools in Spring 2024 and began servicing all middle and high schools in Fall 2024. The FY24 goals reflect the fact that the focus in this pilot year was on hiring and onboarding staff, developing school plans, relationship-building within schools to ensure student access, and collecting information about students to determine baseline competencies and establish timelines.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1470, 379, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.22, 'Due to heightened staff turnover, only 22% of participants were placed in work-based activities, such as work-study programs, job shadowing, and summer jobs, compared to the proposed 80%. The frequent transitions in staffing disrupted continuity in program planning, reduced the capacity to build and maintain partnerships with local employers, and delayed the implementation of structured placement initiatives. Additionally, student turnover, including those who were removed from the school, dropped out, or faced other barriers to consistent participation, further hindered the program''s ability to meet its placement goals within the intended timeline. These factors collectively impacted our ability to effectively deliver key services.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1471, 380, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 978, 'Starting in November 2023, customers who had reached the federal 60-month limit for benefits were no longer automatically granted extensions by the state of Maryland. They were notified that their Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (TANF) cases would close within 30 days. However, these customers were given the option to apply for a hardship extension, with eligibility criteria determined by local Department of Social Services offices. As a result, the number of customers served and referred to our work activity program decreased. Additionally, around the same time, the sanctioning process for customers who did not comply with program requirements was reinstated, leading to an increase in closed cases and a lower number of clients served at the Workforce Reception Center.', 1100, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1472, 381, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.78, 'Starting in November 2023, customers who had reached the federal 60-month limit for benefits were no longer automatically granted extensions by the state of Maryland. They were notified that their Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (TANF) cases would close within 30 days. However, these customers were given the option to apply for a hardship extension, with eligibility criteria determined by local Department of Social Services offices. As a result, the number of customers served and referred to our work activity program decreased. Additionally, around the same time, the sanctioning process for customers who did not comply with program requirements was reinstated, leading to an increase in closed cases and a lower number of clients served at the Workforce Reception Center.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1473, 382, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.84, 'Starting in November 2023, customers who had reached the federal 60-month limit for benefits were no longer automatically granted extensions by the state of Maryland. They were notified that their Temporary Assistance for Needy Families (TANF) cases would close within 30 days. However, these customers were given the option to apply for a hardship extension, with eligibility criteria determined by local Department of Social Services offices. As a result, the number of customers served and referred to our work activity program decreased. Additionally, around the same time, the sanctioning process for customers who did not comply with program requirements was reinstated, leading to an increase in closed cases and a lower number of clients served at the Workforce Reception Center.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1474, 383, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 806, 'The service onboarded new leadership in FY24 and experienced a high rate of position vacancies. The Community Job Hub network also was expanded with the addition of the International Rescue Committee site. As a result, 75% of the service’s staff of Career Development Facilitators needed to be recruited and trained in FY24. Overall, while fewer residents obtained job placements through the Career Center Network, the number of visits to the Hubs vastly increased, as did the number of residents who received intensive services.', 1000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1475, 384, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1702, 'The MOED’s Career Center Network which is comprised of the two One-Stop Career Centers, Employment Connection Center (ECC) and the Community Job Hubs (CJH)s, placed over 1,700 jobseekers focusing on high growth, high-demand industry sector jobs at an average hourly wage of $20.02.', 2500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1476, 385, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1288, 'The service onboarded new leadership in FY24 and experienced a high rate of position vacancies. The Community Job Hub network also was expanded with the addition of the International Rescue Committee site. As a result, 75% of the service’s staff of Career Development Facilitators needed to be recruited and trained in FY24. Overall, while fewer residents obtained job placements through the Career Center Network, the number of visits to the Hubs vastly increased, as did the number of residents who received intensive services.', 1415, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1477, 386, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 22014, 'In Fiscal 2024, both low unemployment (4.3%) and low labor force participation were significant factors impacting MOED’s ability to meet target service numbers. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Although MOED aimed to serve 30,000 residents, 22,014 were served, reflecting a reduced demand for services. When unemployment rates are low, fewer individuals actively seek job search assistance, which reduced the number of people visiting MOED’s centers for resources and services. This directly impacts the overall number of job seekers served, as fewer people are in need of employment services. Additionally, a decline in labor force participation rates indicates that fewer people are actively looking for work, due to increased retirements, disengagement from the workforce, or other personal or economic factors caused by COVID-19. Low participation reduced the overall pool of job seekers, which impacted our ability to meet service targets. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
In addition to in-person offerings, MOED provides a number of virtual services, such as the Employ Baltimore Show, which connect job seekers to employers and provide critical information about specific industries, but are not fully captured in the Maryland Workforce Exchange reporting system.  The increase in demand for virtual services highlights the need for improved tracking methods for virtual engagements, ensuring that these services are counted and reflected in future reporting data.', 30000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1478, 387, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.71, 'MOED’s Business Services Division hosts hiring events to provide employers with access to prescreened qualified skilled workers. In addition, BSRs provide HR services to local employers such as recruitment and pre-screening assistance that reduce their cost of finding skilled workers. The Career Center staff prepares job seekers for in-demand sector jobs available in Baltimore City and/or generated by the Business Services Unit. Job retention is a critical component of post-placement services that includes follow-up services to employers and job seekers. The Career Center staff follows-up with job seekers regularly for up to one (1) year after job placement to assist with mitigating any issue(s) that may lead to resignation or termination and the BSR follows up with employers to ensure satisfaction with services and candidates._x000D_
_x000D_
Based on a wage record match conducted by MD Department of Labor, 71% of those receiving services provided by staff reported earnings one year after receiving services.  The targets for this measure are negotiated with the MD Department of Labor and MOED has met or exceeded the yearly target since the inception of WIOA.', 0.6, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1479, 388, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.68, 'Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (WIOA) formula funds and a variety of other special WIOA grants provide jobseekers with access to a variety of workforce services including occupational skills training to compete in the local economy. Based on a wage record match conducted by MD Department of Labor, 68% of those receiving services provided by staff gained employment AND continued to have reported earnings after 120 days.  The targets for this measure are negotiated with the MD Department of Labor and MOED has met or exceeded the yearly target since the inception of WIOA.', 0.6, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1480, 389, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2162, 'MOED works with the State Department of Parole and Probation as a referral source and has a new arrangement with Baltimore City Circuit Court Judges and the DCREP (District Court Re-Entry Project) program to register city residents for service as an alternative to serving time in the judicial system. As a result of these partnerships, MOED was able to meet or exceed all targets for FY24.', 1800, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1481, 390, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 401, 'MOED works with the State Department of Parole and Probation as a referral source and has a new arrangement with Baltimore City Circuit Court Judges and the DCREP (District Court Re-Entry Project) program to register city residents for service as an alternative to serving time in the judicial system. As a result of these partnerships, MOED was able to meet or exceed all targets for FY24.', 400, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1482, 391, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 556, 'In response to the evolving needs of youth, YO’s model has shifted to providing a broader range of intensive services beyond job placement and occupational skills training. These services now include behavioral health supports, ID services, housing referrals, and other critical resources aimed at addressing the holistic challenges faced by participants. Youth mental health has emerged as a significant factor, with many participants experiencing mental health challenges that impact their ability to fully engage in the program. This, along with the need for comprehensive support services, has contributed to a decline in participant numbers as the program works to meet these complex needs effectively.', 850, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1483, 392, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.77, 'In response to the evolving needs of youth, YO’s model has shifted to providing a broader range of intensive services beyond job placement and occupational skills training. These services now include behavioral health supports, ID services, housing referrals, and other critical resources aimed at addressing the holistic challenges faced by participants. Youth mental health has emerged as a significant factor, with many participants experiencing mental health challenges that impact their ability to fully engage in the program. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The Youth Opportunity Centers plan to restructure the delivery of job readiness services to ensure all new registering youth able to work receive lifeskills, resume development, and  job prep skills.', 0.85, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1484, 393, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.31, 'In response to the evolving needs of youth, YO’s model has shifted to providing a broader range of intensive services beyond job placement and occupational skills training. These services now include behavioral health supports, ID services, housing referrals, and other critical resources aimed at addressing the holistic challenges faced by participants. Youth mental health has emerged as a significant factor, with many participants experiencing mental health challenges that impact their ability to fully engage in the program. This, along with the need for comprehensive support services, has contributed to a decline in participant numbers as the program works to meet these complex needs effectively.', 0.54, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1485, 394, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.86, 'As part of the monthly follow-up with each participant, staff record in the case management system if the young adult has had interaction with the legal system.  As a validity check, participants are checked quarterly against the MD Judicial Case Search.  The number of those connected to the criminal justice system after participation in the YO program was 14% in FY 24.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1486, 395, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 7913, 'YouthWorks enhanced support for potential youth workers by offering in-school registration sessions and in-person document drop-off appointments, ensuring ample assistance with completing the online application and required documents. This increased the number of youth that completed an application and were eligible to participate in summer 2024.', 7000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1487, 396, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.85, 'Despite efforts from staff to encourage early completion, employer participation in the post-survey process declined in FY24, with many waiting until after their temporary program staff had already departed and were unable to provide informed feedback.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1488, 397, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.97, 'All participants are encouraged to complete pre- and post-work readiness assessments, and staff increased outreach efforts and offered incentives for completion, which improved the response rate. Among youth who completed both assessments, 97% demonstrated improvement job readiness skills.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1489, 398, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 139, 'While a large majority of the service providers selected for this program met their recruitment and enrollment goals, several experienced multiple staff turnovers. This both affected their ability to meet goals and required MOED staff to work to retrain new frontline staff on program policies and procedures. MOED has worked to develop partnerships with organizations to help interested participants eliminate barriers related to documentation of Personally Identifiable Information (PII) required for registration and employment.', 215, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1490, 399, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.85, 'While a large majority of the service providers selected for this program met their recruitment and enrollment goals, several experienced multiple staff turnovers. This both affected their ability to meet goals and required MOED staff to work to retrain new frontline staff on program policies and procedures. MOED has worked to develop partnerships with organizations to help interested participants eliminate barriers related to documentation of Personally Identifiable Information (PII) required for registration and employment.', 0.67, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1491, 400, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.52, 'While a large majority of the service providers selected for this program met their recruitment and enrollment goals, several experienced multiple staff turnovers. This both affected their ability to meet goals and required MOED staff to work to retrain new frontline staff on program policies and procedures. MOED has worked to develop partnerships with organizations to help interested participants eliminate barriers related to documentation of Personally Identifiable Information (PII) required for registration and employment.', 0.55, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1492, 401, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6, 'The goals for community engagement and inter-office collaboration were successfully achieved during this period. A key accomplishment was leveraging our partnership with the Equity Office within the OECR to enhance data analysis, community engagement, and outreach efforts. A primary focus was ensuring equitable access to Wage Commission services, particularly addressing the ongoing need for language access for non-English speakers. Through this collaboration, we identified effective strategies to refine and sustain service delivery while also strengthening the capacity of our current personnel. These efforts reflect our commitment to fostering inclusivity and ensuring that all members of the community can access the resources and support they need.', 4, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1493, 402, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 198, 'Our target for addressing the number of late payroll issues is strategically set to reflect the compliance levels of contractors engaged in service and construction projects within the city. This target underscores our commitment to fostering a culture of punctuality and accuracy in payroll submissions. We provide continuous training and support to contractors to help them achieve and maintain compliance with city regulations. Despite these concerted efforts, we recognize that some contractors may still submit documentation late. In such cases, fees will be assessed in accordance with Article 5, Subtitle 25, ensuring that all actions are grounded in established legal frameworks.', 161, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1494, 403, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'By the time the data was provided for FY2024, there were two cases pending due to potential litigations. I am pleased to report that both cases have now been successfully resolved. The Wage Commission achieved a 100% collection rate on restitution for these cases, demonstrating our commitment to upholding wage compliance and ensuring fair outcomes for all parties involved. This accomplishment underscores our dedication to thorough and effective case management, even in the face of complex legal challenges.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1495, 404, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'Closing cases in less than six months can be challenging due to several factors. A thorough review of extensive documentation, sometimes spanning many years, is often necessary to ensure accuracy, which can extend timelines. The cooperation level from contracting agencies is crucial, as delays in receiving required information can slow progress. Contractors may request extensions for various reasons, and while we strive to accommodate these, they can impact timelines. Additionally, not all contractors meet deadlines, leading to further delays despite our efforts to encourage timely compliance. External factors such as regulatory changes and resource constraints also play a role and are often beyond our control.', 0.65, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1496, 405, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 123, 'Fiscal Year 2024 actual data was impacted by staffing limitations, including vacancies in the divisions Equity Legislative Liaison role between January 2023 and July 2024.', 40, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1497, 406, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15, 'Regularly scheduled MCD meetings, and MCD committee meetings were considered when calculating this metric.  The level of activity of the MCD committees directly impacts this outcome.', 14, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1498, 407, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4, 'This was a new performance metric for CRC that sought to train city agencies.  CRC was able to reach 4 agencies', 4, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1499, 408, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5, 'Education and outreach meetings performance metrics were met in 2024.  Community Relations Commission was able to met this metric by participating and organizing various community based events, Fair Housing Month, Civil Rights week, Joint Activities with State and Federal agencies and other resource fairs.', 5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1500, 409, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3, 'Fiscal Year 2024 data for informational and public hearings was impacted by scheduling conflicts and the availability of city agencies.', 4, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1501, 410, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 34, 'Factors that impacted the Fiscal 2024 actual data: Lack of inventory provided to the CRC from the EEOC for investigation.  Budget cuts by the EEOC required for the CRC to downward modify the amount of complaints to close as well as shortage of staff.', 50, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1502, 411, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.5, 'This performance metric was met.  The Community Relations Commission investigators were able to meet this metric by following best practices for investigating and closing complaints within 1 year.', 0.5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1503, 412, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 56, 'Community outreach efforts were modeled after the successful strategies of the Civilian Review Board, adapting their proven approaches to better engage and serve the local population.', 40, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1504, 413, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'The Maryland Police Accountability Act of 2021 requires timely adjudication of misconduct investigations by either asking for additional information or making the determination to charge the officer with misconduct.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1505, 414, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'The Maryland Police Accountability Act of 2021 requires timely complaint delivery to the law enforcement agency and the Police Accountability Boards.', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1506, 415, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'FY24 Actual of 100% was achieved by fully staffing our Urban Design Team.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1507, 416, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.86, 'FY24 actual of 86% was achieved despite losing the primary staff member to retirement in February of 2024, which is nearly half of the reporting period.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1508, 417, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.96, 'FY24 Actual of 96.6% was achieved despite losing the primary staffer to another agency.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1509, 418, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.58, NULL, 0.75, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1510, 419, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.51, 'CHAP had an unfilled position for ten months of FY 2024.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1511, 420, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, NULL, 50, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1512, 422, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.5, '50% of permits were reviewed within 3 days of assignment in FY''24. Our performance fell short of our target primarily due to glitches in the CCE permit system. Permits have not been viewable in reviewers'' permit queue and therefore, the reviewer was unaware that a permit was waiting for their approval. We are hopeful that this issue will be addressed with the new permit system.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1513, 423, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 84940, 'In FY24, we were able to fill open positions to fully staff all positions under this service, increasing our capacity to engage with customers and grow our outreach through our monthly newsletter, meetings and engagement events, and our website.', 75000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1514, 424, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 147, 'We were able to exceed our target under this measure in FY24 due to the opportunity to offer floodplain training to DOP and HCD staff through FEMA at no cost and through the opportunity for members of our staff to provide environmental regulations training to DOT project management staff, in addition to trainings that were planned at the beginning of FY24.', 100, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1515, 425, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.14, 'This performance measure reflects calendar year data for 2024. Actual data will be available in the first quarter of 2025.', 0.05, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1516, 426, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.31, 'Implementation for the 2024 Climate Action Plan began midway through FY24. The first actuals reported for this performance measure will be those reported at the end of FY25.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1517, 427, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 154275, 'This service achieved the FY24 target set for this measure by investing the full amount of HFPA Funds allocated through grant agreements with community organizations and urban farms.', 154275, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1518, 428, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 34, 'Removing the outliers (projects that took 0 hours to complete or the opposite end of the spectrum) showed an average of 34 hours to completion. Keeping those outliers in the data showed 15 hours to completion. Using ALL the data, 95% of the time in FY24, DDSD analysts were able to complete their projects in 3 of fewer days.', 72, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1519, 429, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.4, 'The percentage sworn hires from Baltimore City FY24 actual were 40%, attributed to targeted marketing efforts in the city and surrounding counties, as well as events and career fairs.', 0.3, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1520, 430, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.37, 'We continue to increase in our performance around proactivity. As we review this increase the department is aiming to become more specific in how we positively and proactively engage community. Next year this measure may decrease as we are removing directed patrol that does not encourage officer to get out of the car as much as the other proactivity options (foot patrol, business checks)', 0.35, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1521, 431, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'The lab was able to make improvements to backlog reduction due to additional staff and efficiency improvements including a Lean Six Sigma review of at least one process in every unit. While the goal of 125% was not attained this FY, the lab still was able to reverse backlog growth significantly, and achieve strong backlog reduction for the FY.', 0.75, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1522, 432, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.1, 'We met our goal for % of Level 2 Use of Force cases audited by PRB', 0.1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1523, 433, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'BPD met the 7 day SLA the previous year so we will continue to aspire to that high standard.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1524, 434, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.17, 'Voluntary program.  Officers must be granted time (40hrs) to attend.', 0.2, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1525, 435, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.87, 'We have made progress on % of paragraphs in implementation.', 0.95, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1526, 436, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.73, 'Watch Center personnel dedicated to OIDs decreased by (1) member and (1) member on military leave. This left fewer members to work on requests as they were submitted, resulting in longer wait times. This issue is expected to worsen as DDSD is scheduled to lose (3) additional members by September of 2024. As a result, this goal should be adjusted to compensate for the loss in manpower (3-4 hours per request).', 0.95, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1527, 437, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.45, '•The Centralization of Criminal Investigations Command that allowed Citywide Investigation Division (CWID) to have an extreme focus on the non-fatal shooting (NFS) investigations and to ensure that every District Detective Unit (DDU) has the same level of focus and effort when investigating an NFS; prior to 2023, each DDU reported to their district command and district commanders all had varying degrees of experience in investigations.  This new format now ensure they report to a command that has knowledge and experience.	_x000D_
_x000D_
•Development of case task lists ensured detectives perform the necessary functions on each case._x000D_
_x000D_
•DDU Stat created a forum where we review cases and hold leadership accountable to tasks and follow up._x000D_
_x000D_
•Our State’s Attorney Office (SAO) relationship improved which has helped lead to an improved clearance rate through prosecution._x000D_
_x000D_
•Changes in leadership increased investment in providing quality investigations and accountability._x000D_
_x000D_
•Investment in technology and technology training (e.g. Nighthawk, other technology training) has helped lead to better cases and improved outcomes._x000D_
_x000D_
•Incorporating an enforcement component to investigations though the move of Mobile Metro Unit (MMU), Regional Auto Theft Taskforce (RATT), and Citywide Enforcement Team (CWET) to CWID, and focused them on enforcement related to violent crime drivers and actors and closing NFS cases.', 0.239, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1528, 438, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.21, 'We achieved 100% by ensuring all use of force was scheduled, if not already reviewed.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1529, 439, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.25, 'Staffing shortages continue to be an issue with completing cases in the required time.  We have added professional investigators to assist, but it will take time before they have completed the necessary training to fully contribute to meeting this metric._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_', 0.6, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1530, 440, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.69, '•Decrease in caseload (approximately a 15% reduction in average case load per detective from the previous calendar year)_x000D_
_x000D_
•Increased coordination with internal partners (e.g. GVRS, DDU) with regard to intelligence sharing and Person -of-Interest/Suspect targeting_x000D_
_x000D_
•Re-organization of Criminal Investigation Division under PC Worley’s direction_x000D_
_x000D_
•Increased experience of investigators and leadership_x000D_
_x000D_
•On-boarding of professional investigative specialists', 0.478, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1531, 441, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.98, 'Warrants resolved without injuries is not on track, A warrant served during the1st quarter had a subject jump off a balcony in an attempt to flee, seen by Medics. During the 2nd quarter a warrant was served peacefully where the occupant opened the door for the SWAT team, no use of force required but subject complained of pain on his side and was seen by Medics.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1532, 442, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.96, 'PIB and the ACC have been working together to continue growing the process, and the belief is 100% of cases will be agreed upon eventually.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
