    (1599, 509, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3635, 'Factors influencing the Fiscal Year 2024 actual data included expanded programming opportunities that fostered an inclusive and accessible sports environment for all community members. Additionally, partnerships with key community stakeholders helped subsidize program costs, making participation more affordable.', 3000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1600, 510, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1638, 'Several factors influenced the Fiscal Year 2024 actual data. First, the implementation of an improved data management and participant tracking system enhanced accuracy and efficiency. Additionally, key partnerships with other organizations expanded services for the adult population. Lastly, the introduction of new sports offerings and multi-session programs contributed to increased participation and engagement.', 1025, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1601, 511, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4203, 'Hosted Extended Hour programs at 11 facilities, summer teen camps, Youth Base''s After-school program at 9 facilities, summer pool parties, Spring Fling and Summer Kickoff.', 1500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1602, 512, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 11892, 'Factors influencing the Fiscal 2024 actual data at recreation centers include Summer Camps, After-School Programs, and year-round activities offered at various locations across the city. These figures represent unduplicated children enrolled in at least one activity at a recreation center.', 3000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1603, 513, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2218, 'Factors influencing the Fiscal 2024 actual data include an increase in staffing, which has enhanced capacities at certain recreation centers, and reconfigured programs that now offer a more diverse range of summer camps.', 2200, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1604, 514, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1605, 515, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 44667, 'For Cylburn Arboretum, the target for FY24 was inadvertently carried forward from FY23 without an increase.  The Cylburn Arboretum Friends, our NPO partner at Cylburn Arboretum, opened the renovated carriage house as a Nature Education Center (NEC) and have increased open hours where visitors can be counted, increased educational programming, and increased field trips.  In FY24 the NEC walk-in open hours accounted for over 13,000 documented visitors to Cylburn.', 20000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1606, 516, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 36587, 'The Rawlings Conservatory was scheduled to undergo renovation starting in January of 2024 so we continued to use a half rate for the visitorship target.  The renovation was pushed back and will likely start at the beginning of FY26. _x000D_
_x000D_
Consequently, in FY24, there was a full year of walk-in visitors, field trips, nature and art programs and rentals.  The annual flower shows also brought in record number of monthly visitors for December 2023 and March of 2024.', 14750, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1607, 517, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 13340, 'According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), all older adults—both men and women—can benefit from regular, moderate physical activity. This is true even for people with medical conditions such as arthritis, heart disease, obesity, and high blood pressure. Exercise provides a protective effect against a host of chronic illnesses, including cardiovascular disease, colon cancer, diabetes, obesity, and hypertension. If you already have a chronic condition, physical activity can minimize symptoms. It can even help reduce cognitive decline. One study found that participants over the age of 60 showed fewer Alzheimer''s disease biomarkers when they performed 30 minutes of exercise every day. https://www.ncoa.org/article/the-life-changing-benefits-of-exercise-after-60/. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The Senior Division continues to be flexible and innovative with programming.  To meet the ever changing needs and demands of our participants, the senior division has added the following: _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
1. Fall Brawl and Spring Swing Pickleball tournaments:  The Senior Division has hosted two pickleball tournaments.  One in the spring and one in the fall.  Both tournaments were well attended.  Each tournament is held over a two-day period. Majority of the participants are 60 and older. Day one is singles and mixed doubles. Day two is women''s doubles and men''s doubles. Seniors swung, slammed and grunted their way to pickleball victory. Participants received lunch, tournament, t-shirt and 1st and 2nd place trophies._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
2. A Night at the Gatsby: Theme parties are now part of the Senior Division experience.  The Senior Division partnered with Eating Together in Baltimore to offer a one-of-a-kind theme party.  Seniors from all over Baltimore came out dressed in feathers, flapper dresses and long beaded necklaces. The men did not disappoint in their top hats, black suits and bow ties. By combining our resources, e were able to serve more seniors and lower prices. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
3. QiGong Classes:  Qigong is the newest class offered as part of our "Stepping with Grace" Fall Prevention initiative. Stepping with Grace is an 8- week program targeting seniors 50 and older suffering with arthritis or join pain. The goal of the program is to educate participants on the benefit of exercise, improve performance of daily activity and improve mobility. Qigong uses exercises to optimize energy within the body, mind and spirit. The program has been implemented in 17 locations throughout Baltimore City.  Assisi House of Saint Patrick is the newest senior group to join our program.  Bringing Stepping with Grace locations to 18.', 17618, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1608, 518, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.75, 'A large portion of the participants in TR Programming come from adult daycare agencies.  These agencies have struggled with staffing issues and often cancel last minute. Additionally, the agencies register a quantity of participants and then do not always bring that quantity to the program, thus taking a spot from someone else on the waiting list. The TR Program continues to increase marketing of programs and has seen a significant increase in the number of new agencies and individual participants.', 0.75, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1609, 519, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 14532, 'In Fiscal 2025, program participation numbers were lower than usual. This was mainly due to two factors: staffing issues and reduced program offerings. The Therapeutic Recreation team was down two full-time staff members, the Program Manager and Inclusion Specialist, which greatly impacted the capacity of the programs to run at the capacity they were run before. Additionally, with fewer staff and resources, fewer programs were offered, which also contributed to lower participant numbers. This includes the larger programs such as Bingo, Socials, and Discos.', 21220, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1610, 520, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 33, 'Our targeted goal in FY24 was 30 events. We managed to achieve 33 due to several planned and unplanned collaborations with internal and external partners.', 30, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1611, 521, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.365, 'One of the primary factors for the SR percentage is that the service level agreement (SLA) is 30 days, but the SRs are not actually closed out in the system until after the work is completed. This means that even though the inspection is completed within 30 days (which is what the SLA is for), the SR is not closed out for much longer. Depending on the type of work, an SR might not be closed out for up to a year. Urgent requests are closed out sooner, although the resident might see the work complete prior to seeing the SR closed. Forestry has worked with BCIT and the Mayor''s office on this issue over the years to improve the process. At a minimum, better communication via the 311 app would go a long way to resolve complaints - stating up front what the expected wait time will be for a specific request. Many residents incorrectly assume the 30 days means the work will be complete within that time frame.', 0.5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1612, 522, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5846, 'The primary factor for the FY24 number is that the tree planting contract was not functional. That contract typically plants upwards of 3,000 trees per year. The remaining trees are planted by our non-profit planting partners such as Baltimore Tree Trust and Blue Water Baltimore, to name a few. Because we did not plant trees under the City contract, the number was lower than normal. For FY25, we should have an active contract for the second half of the fiscal year, so we expect the number to increase slightly, although not up to historical levels.', 7000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1613, 523, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.75, 'Factors include only having a total of 3 skilled employees in this division. Facility Maintenance also interested a backlog of outstanding SRs and did not immediately have the ability to purchase all necessary supplies and equipment without extensive time delays. Also having to heavily relay on on-call contractors and the assistance from our sister agency, DGS, these have all contributed to time response delays.', 0.5, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1614, 525, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.65, NULL, 0.6, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
