    (1668, 580, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.57, NULL, 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1669, 581, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.89, 'In FY 2024, 89% of appeals from BMZA’s decisions were upheld by the courts, with 8 out of 9 appeals affirmed. The number of court appeals varies from year to year but typically totals 10 appeals or fewer. With such a small number of appeals, the win percentage can sometimes be influenced by chance, but overall, we maintain a strong affirmance/dismissal rate. This reflects the Board''s consistent performance in ensuring fair and sound decisions.', 0.75, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1670, 582, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 100, 'The average number of days between filing an appeal and the public hearing increased in FY24 due to several factors. An uptick in post-COVID development has led to more applications, while new policies requiring more complete submissions and extended pre-hearing reviews have added time to the process. Additionally, some appellees delayed responses, further contributing to scheduling challenges. Finally, due to BMZA''s new policies, only about 12-14 cases per docket can be heard, as opposed to 20+ cases on past dockets. When there are more appeals and fewer cases can be heard per docket, the timelines get longer.', 60, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1671, 583, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 23, 'The average number of days from public hearing to written resolution was 23 in FY24. BMZA has worked diligently to provide resolutions in a timely manner, with the Zoning Code allowing up to 30 days, with the possibility of an extension. Hiring an Assistant Counsel in the fall of 2023 helped to improve this timeline, but that position became vacant again between November 2024 and April 2025. Resolutions are detailed and contain essential information that requires careful consideration; in a post-consent docket environment, the issuance of resolutions will naturally take more time.', 30, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1672, 584, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 47, 'Hearings per full-time employee decreased significantly in FY24 and are expected to remain low in FY25 due to a sharp reduction in the number of appeals heard by the BMZA. Previously, the consent docket allowed a high volume of appeals to be processed quickly, but without meaningful Board review in a way that was arbitrary and capricious and contrary to the law. Now, each appeal is given the thorough consideration it deserves, as it always should have been, which requires more time and effort per case.', 100, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
