    (1680, 660, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 53672, 'The number of sessions for FY24 reflects consistent user activity, with a slight increase in the overall engagement compared to prior periods. Changes in session behavior, such as more frequent or longer visits to key pages, could have contributed to the higher session count. Additionally, any adjustments made to the session timeout settings or increased usage of the site during peak times, such as live hearings or other events, may have further influenced the session totals for the fiscal year.', 45000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1681, 661, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6676, 'The FY24 actual data has been impacted by several factors related to extended meetings. A baseline of 6,500 programming hours is set for government meetings. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The actual programming hours for FY24 were slightly higher than the base due to certain live hearings extending beyond their scheduled time slots. These longer sessions sometimes overlapped into other pre-scheduled programming blocks, requiring adjustments to the overall schedule. As a result, additional programming hours were allocated to ensure the completion of all necessary meetings leading to a slight increase from the baseline._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
This variability in meeting length is a key factor contributing to the deviation from the initial programming hours projection. However, the programming hours were not as high as projected due to a reduction in the length of live hearings.', 7500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1682, 662, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'This metric is maintained at 100%.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1683, 680, 2024, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1314, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1684, 1, 2025, 53614, NULL, 40478, NULL, 46932, NULL, 46200, 'Calls requiring assistance peak at the beginning of the fourth quarter with the pending Tax Sale in May of each year. April calls were 17k vs 14k for the remaining months in the quarter. July is the highest month as residents receive annual tax bill. July 2024 there were 21k calls.', 187200, 'The actual number of calls requiring assistance was in line with the projections.', 250000, 'Customers are becoming more familiar with the online payment options. In addtion, DPW implemented a new online payment system.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1685, 2, 2025, 0.83, NULL, 0.84, NULL, 0.77, NULL, 0.72, 'There has been much improvement in the number of service requests completed within service times. Operations are 90% staffed along with improved internal operations.', 0.79, 'Service Requests closed on time improved over the last year. The main reason is a full and well trained staff with more institutional knowledge.', 0.75, 'The Bureau continues to have high employee turner due to competitive wages, and is unable to offer 100% teleworking options.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1686, 3, 2025, 5, NULL, 3, NULL, 4, NULL, 1, 'Shown in minutes._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Wait times have decreased over the last several years with a fully staffed Call Center and improvements in internal operations for both BRC and DPW.', 4, 'The average wait times ranged between 1 to 4.5 minutes. This is in line with the original projections when compared to the results of 2025.', 7, 'Wait times vary with the tax season. Wait times fluctuate between 3 minutes up to 10 minutes. Employee turnover also factors into wait times. For the last four years, this area experienced high turnover rates due to competitive wages.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1687, 4, 2025, 0.83, NULL, 0.91, NULL, 0.96, NULL, 0.96, 'Annual projected rate for the last three years.', 0.96, 'The tax collection rate will be approximately 96%.', 0.96, 'Based upon  customer repayment history and the Council''s decision to delay tax sale for certain residents, the same collection rate is anticipated.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1688, 5, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 'Treasury Management has not issued any bonds during the 1st, 2nd, or 3rd quarters.  We anticipated the general obligation bonds will occur during the 1st quarter of FY2026. _x000D_
