    (1719, 39, 2025, 0.0363, NULL, 0.0302, NULL, 0.0344, NULL, 0.0379, 'The Federal Reserve has cut interest rates twice: by 0.50% in September 2024 and by 0.25% in December 2024. Currently, the yield curve is inverted, which means that short-term investments are yielding more than those with longer maturities. The investment portfolio consists of 48% short-term and 52% long-term investments, which has caused the overall yield to fall below the target of 4.00%._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The final rate represent the average earning rate for the fiscal year with a range of 2.90 to 5.98%', 0.05, 'Treasury invests excess unrestricted cash of the city to manage liquidity while earning highest possible yield.  This is done through timing of security purchases, minimizing idle cash, and optizing investment tenure', 0.03, 'The target is based on the anticipated earnings rate for a treasury and agency portfolio with a duration of 6-9 months in FY25.  The rate takes into account the expected 75 bps decline in interest rates in CY24 and an additional interest rate decline in CY25.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1720, 40, 2025, 0.0119, NULL, 0.0204, NULL, 0.0158, NULL, 0.0153, NULL, 0.02, 'The 2% of fires escalating to multiple alarms is influenced by external factors such as aging buildings and wind-driven fire conditions. Enhanced incident command training is helping commanders request resources earlier and maintain tactical reserves to manage incidents safely.', 0, 'The ultimate goal of the department is to not have any incident that escalate beyond a first alarm of fire.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1721, 41, 2025, 0.8606, NULL, 0.875, NULL, 0.9082, NULL, 0.882, NULL, 0.8807, 'FY25 performance was impacted by staffing shortages that increased travel distances, CAD outages requiring verbal status updates, and occasional status entry errors during high-demand incidents. Staffing improvements, CAD upgrades, and ongoing training are expected to improve performance.', 0.9, 'NFPA Standard 1710 is the national response time standard for career fire departments', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1722, 42, 2025, 0.17, NULL, 1.42, NULL, 0.71, NULL, 0.18, 'Fy25Q4 and FY25 total based on population of 568271', 2, 'While the Department strives for zero fatal fires, external factors cannot always be controlled. Efforts to reduce fatalities include grant-funded SSUs, increased staffing for better coverage, and expanded fire safety outreach through social media and community media partnerships.', 0, 'The ultimate goal of the department is prevent any loss of life with fire prevention and education', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1723, 43, 2025, 14680, NULL, 13248, NULL, 13117, NULL, 18426, 'Inspection reports may be submitted late after data reporting, resulting in slight variances between total count and quarterly counts.', 59540, 'We are on target with the goal. The number represented is by quarter and should be a cumlative total. It has since been chanbed for FY27.', 12000, 'This target coincides with the targets for the previous reporting periods', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1724, 44, 2025, 0, NULL, 46, NULL, 0, NULL, 66, 'This year the CERT program has developed with the engagement of Community Partners to host and promote training that is accessible to their neighbors and also engagement of training for BCRP staff. OEM also coordinated with City schools to provide CERT training as part of their safety program curriculum in 2 local high schools.', 112, 'The CERT program continued to develop more in FY25. Thanks to the coordination of our Liasion Officer, OEM has added to our volunteer CERT trainers and started hosting classes in the community allowing us to meet people where they are.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1725, 45, 2025, 3, NULL, 2, NULL, 1, NULL, 4, 'In quarter 4, OEM held 4 Tabletop exercises including the Baltimore City IT/OT Convergence Cybersecurity TTX, the Extreme Heat TTX, the Artscape TTX, and the Storm Recovery TTX. All events were well-attended by City Agencies and Private Partners.', 10, 'OEM hired a new Training and Exercise Coordinator in July 2025. There was a lapse in the position for several months in 2025, but OEM was still able to meet the goal with support from other positions.', 7, 'Now that we are no longer in COVID Pandemic, the Training and Exercise Section Chief can focus on one of the important aspects of Emergency Management which is exercise plans and procedures.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1726, 46, 2025, 19, NULL, 32, NULL, 16, NULL, 31, 'OEM Duty Officers remained active this fiscal year responding to City emergencies such as 3+ Alarm fires, interruptions to infrastructure, underground fires, the mass opioid OD response, the Harbor oil spill, and more.', 98, 'OEM duty officer responses data collection was previously based on CAD calls for responses to OEM. This data captured all response requests regardless of whether a response was needed.', 55, 'The on-scene response capability is a critical element necessary for OEM to perform the role of city-wide coordination during large-scale incidents.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1727, 47, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'OEM continues to spend down all Federal Homeland security grant funds on time which is critical to show the need for ongoing Federal funding support.', 1, 'All grant funds were expended. OEM had a bit of turnover in the Fiscal officer role but we were able to continue coordinating with our partners to spend down funds. Several grants received extensions to support the spend-down.', 1, 'OEM will continue to work torward 100% of grant dollars being spent or invoiced within 60 days. Grant Funding a key part of the City Emergency Management and Homeland Security programs.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1728, 48, 2025, 42342, NULL, 39025, NULL, 37748, NULL, 39635, 'Q2 correction: 39025', 158750, 'FY25 dispatches totaled 158,750, slightly below the 160,000 target, reflecting improved call management and efficient resource use. Optimized unit deployment, stable staffing, and targeted triage protocols helped reduce unnecessary responses while maintaining system readiness.', 160000, 'Goal to reduce call volume', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1729, 49, 2025, 2753, NULL, 2320, NULL, 1945, NULL, 1945, NULL, 2150, 'EMS exceeded its FY25 outreach goal of 1,200 patients, reaching 2,150 through strong program implementation, community partnerships, and targeted outreach to high-utilizer and vulnerable populations. Dedicated staffing and coordination with hospitals and service agencies supported this growth.', 1200, 'Realistic Number of projected patients', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1730, 50, 2025, 0.51, NULL, 0.5, NULL, 0.48, NULL, 0.52, NULL, 0.51, 'FY25 response time performance was impacted by several operational challenges. Ongoing staffing shortages limited the number of EMS units available to respond to calls, reducing our ability to maintain full system coverage. At the same time, call volume remaFY2ined consistently high across the city.', 0.9, 'NFPA Stanadard', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1731, 51, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'we are requesting to remove', 1, 'All ePCRs are reviewed by FirstWatch', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1732, 52, 2025, 0.27, NULL, 0.4, NULL, 0.3, NULL, 0.19, NULL, 0.29, 'The FY27 outreach target remains at 1,200 to align with sustainable staffing, funding, and program capacity. While the program has exceeded this level in the past, the target provides a realistic benchmark that maintains accountability and supports consistent outreach services.', 0.35, 'National Goal', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1733, 53, 2025, 1590, NULL, 494, NULL, 1207, NULL, 1830, NULL, 7745, 'Participation in this program is voluntary. While the FY25 result fell slightly below the target, the variance was minimal at 1.3%, reflecting strong overall engagement despite normal fluctuations in citizen participation.', 7850, 'It is an achievable increase to public request', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1734, 54, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 'This metric should be remove as of FY2024', 0, 'Metric has no alignment with the mission of Community Outreach. See proposal below.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1735, 55, 2025, 2105, NULL, 1616, NULL, 1095, NULL, 2074, NULL, 6890, 'EMS distributed 6,890 naloxone kits in FY25, exceeding the 5,000 target. Strong community engagement, dedicated staffing, stable funding, and targeted outreach in high-risk areas—along with coordination with health and social service partners—contributed to the increased distribution.', 5000, 'It is an achievable and beneficial target for the public', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1736, 56, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 'This metric should be remove as of FY2024', 0, 'Metric has no alignment with the mission of Community Outreach. See proposal below.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1737, 57, 2025, 126, NULL, 94, NULL, 52, NULL, 65, NULL, 683, 'Requests are driven by interest from individuals and organizations seeking BCFD participation in community events. Demand varies based on community engagement, partnerships, and opportunities for the Department to support public safety outreach and education.', 450, 'It is an achievable increase to public request', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1738, 58, 2025, 5617, NULL, 4742, NULL, 4822, NULL, 5136, NULL, 20317, 'FY25 performance exceeded the target due to clear expectations, consistent supervisory oversight, and ongoing QA/QI review of inspection activity. Teams maintained strong accountability standards, which helped ensure inspections and related tasks were completed consistently and efficiently.', 14000, 'Based on the staffing compliment, 14,000 inspections is a reasonable and obtainable target.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1739, 59, 2025, 803, NULL, 662, NULL, 608, NULL, 672, NULL, 2082, 'Clear expectations, strong pre-inspection guidance, and consistent enforcement standards helped reduce deficiencies and minimize the need for rework.', 2000, 'Total is based on economic trends and development within the City. FY24 appears to be slighty higher than FY23', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1740, 60, 2025, 524, NULL, 558, NULL, 328, NULL, 672, 'Last year, the BCFD did not meet its annual target for the number of plans reviewed. The goal was to review 2,400 plans, but the year concluded with 2,082 plans completed. The 318 plan shortfall can be attributed to variables beyond the department’s control  factors. The number of plans reviewed is directly influenced by the volume of requests submitted by businesses, which is directly tied to the economic health of the City. Staffing played a role in the outcome as well; staff availability, including vacancies, reduced the team’s capacity to process incoming plans efficiently. The combination of these challenges contributed to the lower-than-expected number of plans reviewed. While the department cannot control the economic health of the City we have stabilized staffing and are continuously working to streamline processes, and collaborate with other City agencies for improved outcomes.', 2082, 'The Plans Reviewer position has historically been difficult to fill due to the specialized qualifications required. In CY25, the Department hired a Plans Review Manager to strengthen oversight and support the review process.', 2400, 'Total is based on economic trends and development within the City. FY24 appears to be slighty higher than FY23', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (424, 81, 2022, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1140, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1742, 62, 2025, 0.9, NULL, 0.92, NULL, 0.9, NULL, 1, NULL, 0.92, 'Increased staffing levels combined with the use of technology have helped the BCFD exceed its targeted performance goals.', 0.9, 'Dedicating personnel to handle complaints and fire code violations will improve service delivery time', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1743, 63, 2025, 0.8, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 0.6, NULL, 0.9, NULL, 0.85, 'FY25 goals were exceeded following the hiring of additional personnel to support the plans review process. The implementation of a third-party plans review option also provided customers with an additional pathway to move their projects forward more efficiently.', 0.8, 'The hiring of a plan reviewer will increase the number of plan reviews completed within 30 days.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1744, 64, 2025, 39, NULL, 28, NULL, 14, NULL, 26, NULL, 215, 'For FY25 there was an increase in incendiary vacant home fires determinations exacerbated by cold weather. These fires are investigated by BCFD FIB and BCPD Police Arson.', 130, 'The Fire Investigation Bureau has reported that in FY23, 108 incidents of arson were reported in Baltimore City, which accounted for only 17% of all suspicious fires. Although predicting arson is challenging, the Bureau plans to increase the number of investigations through improved field training and a new Quality Assurance program. The Bureau is confident that it can investigate and rule on 130 cases of arson by FY25, which is a realistic goal.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1745, 65, 2025, 132, NULL, 166, NULL, 149, NULL, 141, NULL, 588, 'The number of fires investigated increased in FY25 due to a rise in smaller trash fires. These incidents required investigative review, contributing to the overall increase in cases handled during the year.', 500, 'During FY23, the Fire Investigation Bureau conducted investigations for 550 fires that occurred in Baltimore City. However, this number only represents 29% of all the fires that took place in the city. Our aim is to investigate 40% of all fires within the city limits. Unfortunately, due to limited staffing levels, we believe that conducting 500 investigations in FY25 is a more achievable goal.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1746, 66, 2025, 0.9, NULL, 0.9, NULL, 0.9, NULL, 0.9, NULL, 0.9, 'The FY25 target was met. During this period the Office of the Fire Marshal operated with one investigator per shift. While investigators maintained strong case management, the volume of daily incidents required careful prioritization and coordination.', 0.9, 'This is a realistic target', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1747, 67, 2025, 0.5, NULL, 0.5, NULL, 0.5, NULL, 0.65, NULL, 0.65, 'In FY25, BCFD strengthened collaboration with the BPD Arson Unit, improving communication and coordination between agencies. This renewed partnership helped streamline investigations and contributed to the metric being exceeded.', 0.5, 'Taking into account delays in receiving additional reports from external agencies and gathering witness statements, this is a realistic target.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1748, 68, 2025, 0.65, NULL, 0.65, NULL, 0.65, NULL, 0.5, NULL, 0.5, 'FY25 performance exceeded the target largely due to an increase in training opportunities conducted with external partners and stakeholders. These collaborative training sessions strengthened coordination and expanded the number of personnel receiving fire code and safety-related instruction.', 0.65, 'This is the national standard', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1749, 69, 2025, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, 'Fire investigators must meet required training hours to conduct investigations. In FY25, the target was slightly exceeded due to additional collaborative training opportunities with the ATF, which helped strengthen investigator readiness and professional development.', 0.8, 'In FY23, the Fire Investigation Bureau introduced a new performance measure that will be compared to FY24 to create a more realistic performance measure for training for FY25. The goal is to have 80% of the Bureau''s investigators attend three or more training classes per year, after accounting for unforeseeable time off.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1750, 70, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'In FY25, BCFD tested all in-service ground ladders for compliance with NFPA 1932 standards. Any deficiencies were addressed through repair or replacement to ensure safety and reliability. Historically, about 20% of ladders fail annual testing and require corrective action.', 1, 'The National Fire Protection Association establishes codes and standards for all aspects of the fire service. The standards set by NFPA 1932 establish guidelines for the construction and maintenance of our ground ladders.  By adhearing to these standards, we are assuring our firefighters are equipped with the safest ground ladders available.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1751, 71, 2025, 0.65, NULL, 0.75, NULL, 0.83, NULL, 0.74, NULL, 0.74, 'Some in-service turnout gear was not captured for the NFPA 1851 inspection due to members being on leave, off duty, or reassigned. These situations can affect inspection timing, but any missed gear is captured and inspected during the next scheduled annual cycle to ensure compliance.', 0.9, 'The National Fire Protection Association establishes codes and standards for all aspects of the fire service. The standards set by NFPA 1851 establish guidelines that address the construction and maintenance of all of our firefighting protective clothing. By adhearing to these standards, we are assuring our firefighters are outfitted with the safest protective clothing available.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1752, 72, 2025, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 7, NULL, 7, 'BCFD expanded use of Operative IQ’s seven modules in 2025, adding annual facility inspections through the Facilities Module. This improved tracking of deficiencies, inventory, and expiration dates, enabling timely repairs, better supply management, reduced waste, and stronger operational readiness.', 7, 'This is the maximum number of Operative IQ systems Currently available.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1753, 73, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 68601, 'This metric should be a count, not a decimal. Count of BCFD units responding to EMS call types:_x000D_
_x000D_
Q1: 73,763_x000D_
_x000D_
Q2: 67,720_x000D_
_x000D_
Q3: 66,350', 276434, 'The FY25 total of 168,000 EMS dispatches reflects overall call demand and staffing capacity. Seasonal illness, high-acuity incidents, and fluctuations in medical emergencies increased system use, while staffing levels, overtime, and unit availability influenced response capacity.', 160591, 'A target cannot be estimated for this as it is dependant on the number of 911 calls for service.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1754, 74, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 17787, 'This metric should be a count, not a decimal. Count of BCFD units responding to suppression call types:_x000D_
_x000D_
Q1: 18,465_x000D_
_x000D_
Q2: 19,811_x000D_
_x000D_
Q3: 18,985', 74948, 'The FY25 total of 52,000 fire response dispatches was driven by call demand and operational capacity. Seasonal trends, incident complexity, staffing levels, and unit availability all influenced response volume, including periods impacted by vacancies or apparatus downtime.', 48102, 'A target cannot be estimated for this as it is dependant on the number of 911 calls for service.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1755, 75, 2025, 0.81, NULL, 0.89, NULL, 0.91, NULL, 0.93, NULL, 0.92, 'The FY25 result of 98% reflects strong QA monitoring, ongoing coaching, and adherence to customer service standards. Weekly QA/QI reviews, targeted feedback, staffing stabilization, and refresher training helped strengthen performance despite high call volume.', 0.9, 'Each 911 specialist''s level of quality and accurancy is monitoried by a 3rd party agency along with our Quality Adsurance team. The results from both allows 911 to create and seek out continous training plans to improve the efficency and effectiveness of the cal handling processes.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1756, 76, 2025, 0.8917, NULL, 0.9004, NULL, 0.896, NULL, 0.8917, NULL, 0.89, 'The FY25 result of 89% was impacted by staffing shortages and higher call volumes. Ongoing vacancies and the onboarding of new dispatchers temporarily reduced processing efficiency, particularly during peak demand periods as new staff progressed through training.', 0.92, 'Increasing the staffing in Fire Communications by filling the (10) vacant positions will reduce the number of overtime hours individual Fire Dispatcher work.  This will allow for dispatchers to make decisions more clearly, decreasing the chances of errors and an increase of scores.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1757, 77, 2025, 0.81, NULL, 0.89, NULL, 0.91, NULL, 0.92, NULL, 0.88, 'The FY25 result of 90% was influenced by staffing levels and call volume. Vacancies, sick leave, and overtime affected coverage during peak periods, while increased call demand and high-volume incidents placed additional pressure on answer times.', 0.9, 'With the continous hiring of 911 specialist, this will allow apprioprate staffing to handle the increasing call volume.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1758, 78, 2025, 0.9632, NULL, 0.9634, NULL, 0.9685, NULL, 0.9676, NULL, 0.97, 'Staffing shortages and onboarding of new dispatchers affected consistency as newer staff required coaching and reinforcement of protocols. Increased call volume and higher-acuity incidents also created a fast-paced environment that made maintaining both speed and accuracy more challenging.', 0.99, 'Each individual dispatcher’s level of quality and accuracy is monitored by the Quality Assurance Officer and results/performance is used to create continuous training plans to address repeated inaccuracies.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1759, 79, 2025, 4.35, NULL, 3.97, NULL, 2.11, NULL, 4.54, NULL, 16, 'Operational policy updates, expanded field training, and targeted recruit skill development in key improvement areas have contributed to a measurable reduction in line-of-duty injuries.', 19, 'Realistic goal based on previous LOD injuries with goal of decreasing numbers', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1760, 80, 2025, 60, NULL, 22, NULL, 52, NULL, 19, NULL, 153, 'Based on operational needs, multiple overlapping fire suppression and EMS recruit classes were hired.  This significantly increased the total number of recruits who entered the Fire Academy._x000D_
_x000D_', 100, 'Goal of hiring 3 recruit classes per fiscal year', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (814, 81, 2023, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2498, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1762, 82, 2025, 76, NULL, 85, NULL, 76, NULL, 86, 'Although we have not met this goal, we have done some analysis on the cause.  We have determined one factor is new or inexperienced drivers. As we have closed the rate on vacancies we have hired many people. Additionally, some of the new vehicles are larger than they were previously use to.  The changes we are making are: Returning to the original specifications of vehicle size. We are introducing a new policy that mandates anyone with a preventable collision will be retrained.  Lastly, we are enhancing our use of drivecams to better monitor traffic law compliance.', 338, 'As more recruits graduate from the Fire Academy, the Department sees an increase in newer drivers. At the same time, apparatus are being built larger while city streets remain narrow, creating additional challenges that require continued driver training and operational awareness.', 295, 'Target increased based on average number of collisions over the past 3 years and current projections', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1763, 83, 2025, 0, NULL, 0.88, NULL, 0, NULL, 0.58, 'Last year, the BCFD Fire Academy was unable to provide a percentage for the number of recruits who completed training. This is primarily because the Academy’s training program spans several months, and the training cycles overlap fiscal year quarters and sometimes entire fiscal years. As a result, many recruits who begin training in one reporting period do not complete their program until following periods._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The multi-month timeline means that, at any given point, a significant portion of recruits are still in progress. Variations in class start dates and the timing of hiring processes throughout the year further complicate the ability to calculate accurate completion percentages within a single fiscal year.', 0.73, 'The slight decrease in the graduation rate was primarily due to a higher number of recruits being separated from the program for medical reasons during training.', 0.75, 'Realistic goal based on previous percentages of recruits who graduate', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1764, 85, 2025, 0.039, NULL, 0.055, NULL, 0.049, NULL, 0.036, NULL, 0.04, 'The FY25 target overestimated the impact of increased older assets in the Fleet . It was assumed those assets due for replacement would see more abuse that would result in an increase in avoidable costs', 0.09, 'This measure is pivotal in our strategy to minimize avoidable costs and enhance fleet performance. By focusing on maintenance and repair costs outside regular wear and tear, we gain insights into key drivers of vehicle downtime. This not only informs agencies about the impact of avoidable costs on their budgets and operations but also allows us to identify trends at various levels, from the agency to the vehicle and even specific divisions and drivers. The goal is to hold stakeholders accountable, preserve fleet value, and ensure the city receives the best return on its investment when decommissioning equipment.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1765, 86, 2025, 0.793, NULL, 0.819, NULL, 0.837, NULL, 0.837, NULL, 0.82, 'Fleet fell just shy of the target and anticipates meeting or surpassing the target in FY 26 because we will prioritize technician and driver training on asset usage and diagnostics, leverage improved telematics and implement parts and vendor strategy plans to optimize operations.', 0.85, 'Fleet availability is the main measure of our success. By tracking the availability of both public safety and routine service vehicles, we empower ourselves to make informed, data-driven decisions. Fleet availability is not just a metric; it is an integral aspect of our commitment to providing reliable and timely services to our sister agencies. It serves as the ultimate gauge of our division''s effectiveness and efficiency.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1766, 87, 2025, 0.599, NULL, 0.645, NULL, 0.707, NULL, 0.731, NULL, 0.67, 'There are a few categories of vehicles where there are limited assets. Those assets are often overdue for PMS and over used, which will result in extended time when the assets are finally brought.', 0.75, 'Fleet availability is the main measure of our success. By tracking the availability of both public safety and routine service vehicles, we empower ourselves to make informed, data-driven decisions. Fleet availability is not just a metric; it is an integral aspect of our commitment to providing reliable and timely services to our sister agencies. It serves as the ultimate gauge of our division''s effectiveness and efficiency.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1767, 89, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Some performance measures may not show data for certain quarters due to the nature of how the data is collected or how the services are delivered. Measures that rely on a full year of operations, have strong seasonal patterns, or involve delayed data reporting (e.g., from external systems or partners) may not yield meaningful or available results every quarter. As a result, and to maintain transparency, accuracy and relevance, some annual DGS performance measures may be reported yearly or appear only in specific quarters where activity occurs. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
(Data for this measure is received between September and October annually. The division anticipates being able to report on this measure in late October.)_x000D_
_x000D_', 61, 'The difference in FY25 Actual EUI from the target EUI is insignificant across the portfolio of buildings. In FY25 we did see an increase in steam and chilled water that we are focused on addressing.', 60, 'DGS does not expect any large capital improvements in FY24 that will significantly change performance of energy use intensity.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1768, 90, 2025, 18347, NULL, 81667, NULL, 549500, NULL, 4703881, 'Some performance measures may not show data for certain quarters due to the nature of how the data is collected or how the services are delivered. Measures that rely on a full year of operations, have strong seasonal patterns, or involve delayed data reporting (e.g., from external systems or partners) may not yield meaningful or available results every quarter. As a result, and to maintain transparency, accuracy and relevance, some annual DGS performance measures may be reported yearly or appear only in specific quarters where activity occurs. _x000D_
_x000D_', 5353400, 'For FY25 we secured a one-time grant of $4M from MDOT Carbon Reduction Program (federal pass-thorugh funds) for EV supply equipment, which took us far beyond our expected target of $1M from MEA grants. We had a federal funding surge which explains our perfomance for FY25.', 1000000, 'We assume no changes in grant funding availability from FY24 to FY25', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1769, 92, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Some performance measures may not show data for certain quarters due to the nature of how the data is collected or how the services are delivered. Measures that rely on a full year of operations, have strong seasonal patterns, or involve delayed data reporting (e.g., from external systems or partners) may not yield meaningful or available results every quarter. As a result, and to maintain transparency, accuracy and relevance, some annual DGS performance measures may be reported yearly or appear only in specific quarters where activity occurs. (Data for this measure is received between September and October annually. The division anticipates being able to report on this measure in late October.)_x000D_
_x000D_', 0.18, 'The state Renewable Portfolio Standard is 20% or payment of an Alternative Compliance Fee. In FY25, the ACP was less expensive than the purchasing of a REC for a percentage of the requirement, which is why we didn''t meet our goal.', 0.2, 'This is the purchasing goal set in the MD Renewable Portfolio Standard.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1770, 93, 2025, 0.53, NULL, 0.41, NULL, 0.33, NULL, 0.45, NULL, 0.43, 'Our lean workforce throughout the year which limited the ability to meet demand, especially in key trade areas such as HVAC, plumbing, and electrical. Weather conditions, particularly in the winter and early spring, led to an increase in emergency and high-priority requests.', 0.55, 'The % of corrective work request completed on time is the counterpart of preventive maintenance.  We use this metric to track and measure how efficient our staff is at completing corrective maintenance work in DGS managed facilities. This KPI allows transparency on the Departments on-time completion of work request against the problem types benchmark. It is important to track this metric so staffing, vendor, and training deficiencies can be managed effectively in order to meet the demands of providing prompt response and repairs.  CM on time compliance tells the story of how well our staff responds to work order request and is a gateway to how we make decision on staffing, programming, and also sets the course for capital investment decision making.  The FY25 target of 55% has increased due to a number of factors- positive in nature.  Key managerial and technician positions have been filled prompting and increse in work completed on time.  Many needed contracts that have not been available or active in the past fY have been create and/or active allowing FMD to complete a higher number of work orders on time.  Also, training of staff in utilizing archibus (cmms software) has improved flow of work.  FMD has also establish benchmarks for majority of work types and has socialized them with staff; therefore increasing awareness and gradually promoting improved work performance.  All efforts are actively underway and will continue to be executed and developed through the next fiscal year.  We are optimistic about the improved performance.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1771, 94, 2025, 0.97, NULL, 0.97, NULL, 0.97, NULL, 0.97, NULL, 0.97, 'In FY2025, this measure reported a consistent 97.1% elevator availability each quarter, based on tracking 102 available elevator cars out of 105 total. Maintained across 42 buildings.', 0.8, 'This KPI tracks daily operation of a crticical life safety/transport system in many of the core municipal buildins.  It is critical that we know what units are oprational each day to ensure transport and emergency protocols remain active. Management uses this metric to inform on which units require maintenance repair, capital investment, and also how to address programming and commnications. Current benchmark for DGS FMD is each day no less than 80% elevators are out of order each day at the start of the day.  This target percentage takes into effect the age units, industry standard uptime of elevator portfolio, and also vendor and staff availability to sustain units.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1772, 96, 2025, 0.45, NULL, 0.47, NULL, 0.72, NULL, 0.84, NULL, 0.58, 'Initial declines in Q1 and Q2 were primarily due to operational factors in the downtown and contract team. This timeframe also marked the early stages of our shift toward a more data-driven approach, which required changes in workflows, reorientation of teams, and alignment with system tracking.', 0.65, 'PM compliance KPI is important as FMD works to exceed performance standards.  While PM is used as a check and balance for CM we also focus on how efficient we are with completing preventive maintenance per benchmarked durations.  This metric is used daily/weekly/etc. by managers to manage performance and make operational decision regarding how we facilitate pm activities. FY25 target of 65% is driven by our belief that compliance will increase and hold at a higher rate through the current FY to FY25.  In FY22 the KpI declined due to lasting pandemic effects and also vendor/contract availability.  During this time many of the driving work order types could not be completed on time or at all due to little or no resources.  As we transitioned to FY23 many efforts were made to restore key services such as roofing, electrical, plumbing, and also HVAC which is a critical service agency and city wide.  Restoration of contracts and available vendors were key components in drastic increase  from FY22 to 23.  Staff vacancies were also filled that facilitated much of the PM work that lagged.  A renewed focus on PM also contibuted in the compliance increase as management worked at higher frequency with staff to ensure PM schedules were embraced, monitored, measured, and kept in compliance.  As we look ahead to FY25 we notice that the current compliance is at 71% (current in FY24); prompting a confident target of 65%.  While we love to aim high we are aware that contract, staffing, and programming issues could arise, therefore we chose to not be reasonable and not overly agressive.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1773, 97, 2025, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Some performance measures may not show data for certain quarters due to the nature of how the data is collected or how the services are delivered. Measures that rely on a full year of operations, have strong seasonal patterns, or involve delayed data reporting (e.g., from external systems or partners) may not yield meaningful or available results every quarter. As a result, and to maintain transparency, accuracy and relevance, some annual DGS performance measures may be reported yearly or appear only in specific quarters where activity occurs. _x000D_
_x000D_', 1, 'Total 10 construction projects were completed in current fiscal year (FY25). 8 projects were completed in second quarter (Q2), 1 project was completed in third quarter (Q3) and 1 project was completed in fourth quarter (Q4). All of these projects completed on time.', 0.88, 'We determine the target value by averaging the actual data from the last 9 years, using the historical performance of completed construction projects on time as a benchmark for future projects.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1774, 98, 2025, NULL, NULL, 0.75, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Some performance measures may not show data for certain quarters due to the nature of how the data is collected or how the services are delivered. Measures that rely on a full year of operations, have strong seasonal patterns, or involve delayed data reporting (e.g., from external systems or partners) may not yield meaningful or available results every quarter. As a result, and to maintain transparency, accuracy and relevance, some annual DGS performance measures may be reported yearly or appear only in specific quarters where activity occurs. _x000D_
_x000D_', 0.8, 'Total 10 construction projects were completed in current fiscal year (FY25). Out of these 10 projects, 2 projects have change order greater than 10% of accepted bid value due to unforeseen condition and added scope.', 0.73, 'Target value is based on the average of last 9 years of  actual data, considering the historical data of completed construction projects.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1775, 99, 2025, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Some performance measures may not show data for certain quarters due to the nature of how the data is collected or how the services are delivered. Measures that rely on a full year of operations, have strong seasonal patterns, or involve delayed data reporting (e.g., from external systems or partners) may not yield meaningful or available results every quarter. As a result, and to maintain transparency, accuracy and relevance, some annual DGS performance measures may be reported yearly or appear only in specific quarters where activity occurs. _x000D_
_x000D_', 1, 'Final payments were processed for 5 construction contracts in current Fiscal year (FY25). Final payments of 3 contracts  were processed in first quarter (Q1) and for 2 contracts final payments were processed in third quarter (Q3). All of these 5 contracts met the MBE goals.', 1, 'Target value is based on average of last 3 years of  actual data, which reflects the historical trends.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1776, 100, 2025, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Some performance measures may not show data for certain quarters due to the nature of how the data is collected or how the services are delivered. Measures that rely on a full year of operations, have strong seasonal patterns, or involve delayed data reporting (e.g., from external systems or partners) may not yield meaningful or available results every quarter. As a result, and to maintain transparency, accuracy and relevance, some annual DGS performance measures may be reported yearly or appear only in specific quarters where activity occurs. _x000D_
_x000D_', 1, 'Final payments were processed for 5 construction contracts in current Fiscal year (FY25). Final payments of 3 contracts  were processed in first quarter (Q1) and for 2 contracts final payments were processed in third quarter (Q3). All of these 5 contracts met the WBE goals.', 1, 'Target value is based on average of last 3 years of  actual data, which reflects the historical trends.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1777, 102, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Total 7 projects were completed in current fiscal year (FY25) . 2 projects were completed in first quarter (Q1), 3 projects were completed in second quarter (Q2), 1 project was completed in 3rd quarter (Q3) and 1 project was completed in 4th quarter (Q4). All of these projects completed on time.', 0.9, 'Target value is based on the average of last 9 years of  actual data. This approach involves considering the historical performance of completed design projects on time to set a benchmark for future projects.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1778, 103, 2025, 1531, NULL, 2080, NULL, 1650, NULL, 1825, NULL, 7157, NULL, 1500, 'Number of STI visits is one indication of how frequently residents utilize our services.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1779, 104, 2025, 70, NULL, 83, NULL, 91, NULL, 98, 'Several factors impacted the dental visits. A new electronic medical record was introduced. In addition, several positions were vacant. The program is making progress in filling vacancies.', 342, NULL, 1500, 'Number of dental visits is one indication of how we  measure how many residents are utilizing our services.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1780, 105, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'An important aspect to Tuberculosis prevention and control is ensuring all patients take all of their medications, to limit the spread of Tuberculosis.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1781, 106, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 0.92, 'This is an important metric in evaluating the effectiveness of TB prevention and control activity.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1782, 107, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'The time period covered includes transition into the clinic’s new electronic medical record (EMR). While transition into the software has been completed for patient care, we are continuing to modify and improve reporting from the new system, and ensuring all metrics are entered in a way that accurately reports performance. The data reflect that out of 20 patients newly diagnosed in the Health Department clinics, we documented linkage in 15 of them.', 0.75, NULL, 0.9, 'This is a key metric reported nationally as part of the HIV care continuum, and partly reflects efficiency of our program.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1783, 108, 2025, 108, NULL, 135, NULL, 101, NULL, 106, 'Although we make every effort to conduct home visits and assess homes for health & safety risks, The target was not met for a host of reasons. Some residents decline our home visiting services, and we conduct the visit telephonically. Residents also have privacy concerns, immigration concerns, embarrassment, or guilt regarding the condition of their home. In addition, we cannot always enter residents’ home due to scheduling conflicts. Finally, in some instances there are cultural differences in healthcare beliefs and practices.', 310, 'The inability to assess homes and complete environmental inspections is on impact on FY25. Childhood Lead Poisoning Prevention Program holds four positions for sanitarians and only had two positions filled.', 500, 'We continue to stretch to attempt to  reach this target.  If it is obtained in FY24, then we will increase  for FY25.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1784, 109, 2025, 0.11, NULL, 0.11, NULL, 0.05, NULL, 0.5, 'TThe Childhood Lead Poisoning Prevention Program currently has only two licensed Environmental Sanitarians. Historically, these positions have been challenging to fill nationwide, due in part to rigorous position requirements. The program has recently hired a 2 new Sanitarians who are apprentices and will not be fully licensed for another 18-24 months. There were also a few mitigating factors that contributed to our low inspection percentage. First, 72 parents refused environmental inspections which is usually high. Those that refused were sent a letter and follow up to confirm their refusal. In addition, another 21 parents moved with no forwarding address or to another jurisdiction.', 0.32, NULL, 0.65, 'With the hiring of new Sanitarians in FY24, we anticipate that we will be able to increase our adherence to inspection protocols in FY25.  The licensing process is lengthy, with it taking upwards of 12 months before staff is able to conduct an environmental inspection independently.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1785, 110, 2025, 0.67, NULL, 0.55, NULL, 0.45, NULL, 0.42, 'It is imprtant to note that some families did not adhere to asthma action plans. We administered re-education when needed. Many families moved which introduced a new set of environmental factors in the new home and we conducted another home visit & created a new asthma action plan.  Finally in an attempt to conduct additional home visits, there were  a number of families that refused further contact as a result of immigration concerns.', 0.67, 'Many factors affected the 2025 data, including leadership changes, staff shortages, political shifts within the country, and residents’ fear of government agencies. These challenges limited our ability to interact with the community and were associated with an increase in emergency department visits', 0.98, 'With typical percentages of reductions in asthma related ED visits for program participants remaining around 95%, we are stretching to reach this target.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1786, 111, 2025, 1248, NULL, 2101, NULL, 1244, NULL, 1811, NULL, 6449, 'In FY25, BCHD''s Overdose Prevention program only had 2 trainers on staff. This impacted the total number of trainings conducted and annual totals for individuals trained.', NULL, 'Naloxone is a life-saving medication that can rapidly reverse the effects of an opioid overdose.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1787, 112, 2025, 1305, NULL, 2113, NULL, 1254, NULL, 2478, NULL, 7275, 'Limited staffing (only 2 dedicated trainers) also significantly impacted capacity for naloxone kit distribution in FY25.', NULL, 'Naloxone is a life-saving medication that can rapidly reverse the effects of an opioid overdose.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1788, 113, 2025, 234121, NULL, 256367, NULL, 322000, NULL, 241320, 'Although we were hoping to come closer to this PM target, we knew that we were more likely to not reach the goal. This target was reached/exceeded once during the pandemic, and was the result of several strategies used by the program to ensure there was increased and adequate access to new sterile syringes among people who inject drugs within the jurisdiction. However, post-pandemic we are seeing these numbers level back out to were they were pre-pandemic, which is a result of several factors. One is that we have returned to normal operations and protocols in regard to syringe distribution. Other factors also include the presence of several community-based syringe services program operating within our jurisdiction, there have also been brief periods when we have had some level of supply and staffing  shortages. The post-pandemic landscape is much different than the one we have been providing services in since 1994. However, we have implemented new outreach and engagement strategies to help address these challanges.', 889712, 'Internal and external challenges affected the program''s ability to meet the FY25 target. Post-pandemic environmental changes made it more difficult to engage the population most in need of services. Staffing shortages and recurring mechanical issues with mobile units (vehicles) also were a factor.', 2000000, 'This metric is used to determine the overall reach of the SSP program and subsequent outcomes.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1789, 114, 2025, 80, NULL, 76, NULL, 79, NULL, 71, NULL, 278, 'The program experienced significant staffing changes in FY25 with vacancy in two senior positions. In addition, driver position vacancies limited day-to-day operational capacity.', NULL, 'Buprenorphine is a medication used to treat opioid use disorder.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1790, 115, 2025, 63, NULL, 192, NULL, 308, NULL, 133, NULL, 318, 'The FY25 target was not met due to staffing fluctuations. The providers experienced varying levels of clinician vacancies at different points in the fiscal year, which impacted service delivery capacity and the pace at which services were documented and reported.', NULL, 'Substance use disorder providers collaborate with City Schools to identify schools interested in participating in providing substance use disorder services.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1791, 116, 2025, 0.89, NULL, 0.88, NULL, 0.89, NULL, 0.9, NULL, 0.89, 'FY25 actuals of 89% were only minimally under the expected target of 90%.', NULL, '988 is a national helpline to access high quality emergency emotional support and resources. We aim for Baltimore City''s call center to answer 90% of local calls before they are sent to a backup call center elsewhere in the country.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1792, 117, 2025, 1675, NULL, 1399, NULL, 1343, NULL, 1567, 'The FY25 target was met through strong partnerships with Title X clinics across the city.', 4376, 'The Adolescent and Reproductive Health Office started to recover numbers lost during the COVID pandemic and had a very strong immigrant population using services', 4157, 'Clinical services have been challenged with reaching clients in this post-COVID environment.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1793, 118, 2025, 142, NULL, 137, NULL, 143, NULL, 139, 'The Nurse Family Partnership model is based on a full-time nurse home visitor caseload of between 21 and 25 active clients. In FY25, BCHD had 6 full-time nurses so the combined caseload target is actually a range of  between 126-150 clients. At 139 total clients, we have met this targeted range for FY25.', 139, 'M&I met its target goal of serving between 126-150 families by servicing 139 familes. Factors impacting the Fiscal 2025 data: 1) M&I has significant expertise in social-emotional screening with the ASQ:SE screening tool; 2) increased nursing compensation, which led to improved nurse retention; 3) ma', 150, '_x000D_
_x000D_
We are currently fully staffed with 6 nurses. Per NFP fidelity guidelines our caseload capacity when were are fully staffed is 25 clients per each nurse', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1794, 119, 2025, 0.98, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'This target was met for FY25.', 0.99, 'The Maternal & Infant Care Program (M&I) exceeded its target of 90% of children receiving a social-emotional development screening at recommended intervals. Factors that influenced their success include 1) M&I has significant expertise in social-emotional screening with the ASQ:SE screening tool; 2)', 0.9, '_x000D_
_x000D_
This is an average based on past fiscal year performance with consideration for some clients that may not reach the screening age to capture data by the FY25 target year', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1795, 120, 2025, 43888, NULL, 90213, NULL, 97953, NULL, 76494, NULL, 285307, 'The number of visits to the health suite are typically related to school enrolment.  During Fiscal Year 2025 the number of health suite visits increased by 1.5% over the prior year.  During that time student enrolment increased by 1.3% and attendance increased by 1.2%.', 273300, 'We do not anticipate a significant increase in visits to the health suite. Enrolment in City Schools has decreased, and nurse staffing shortages continue.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1796, 121, 2025, 0.5, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.8, NULL, 0.66, NULL, 0.67, 'This measure increased from 63% in FY2024 to 67% in FY2025.  This was a direct result of the addition of two nurse practitioners in the SBHCs. They are able to provide more care for chronic conditions; and well child, health maintenance and preventive care rather than treating acute conditions only.', 0.65, 'There continues to be nursing professional staffing shortages. Even with the addition of a second provider, we do not expect an increase in the target as efforts will be geared towards acute illnesses', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1797, 122, 2025, 0.82, NULL, 0.8, NULL, 0.8, NULL, 0.87, NULL, 0.87, 'This performance measures the percentage of students returning to class after a visit to the health suite for a minor injury or acute illness. Having trained full-time school health staff onsite in every school ensures that students can be treated and return to class.', 0.82, 'Since it appears that we have moved from the  the COVID-19 pandemic to an endemic phase, we anticipate that the return to class rate will continue to increase as students will no longer be sent home due to this highly contagious condition.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1798, 123, 2025, 516, NULL, 1678, NULL, 3207, NULL, 4127, NULL, 4127, 'The AERS program was able to maintain sufficient staffing capacity by filling program vacancies and recruiting contractual staff during the fiscal year.', 2700, 'Organizational nursing capacity projections and interRAI assessment referal trends support the proposed FY25 targets', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1799, 124, 2025, 445, NULL, 707, NULL, 1218, NULL, 2553, NULL, 2553, 'During FY25, there was transition in clinical staff that perform nurse monitoring functions that impacted the nurse monitoring data. All vacancies were filled by Q3 and positions were maintained throughout the year.', 2700, 'Organizational nursing capacity projections and nurse monitoring visit referal trends support the proposed FY25 targets', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1800, 125, 2025, 2070, NULL, 5483, NULL, 8810, NULL, 11878, NULL, 11878, 'During FY25, there was staff turnover that impacted supporting planning hours.', 13800, 'Organizational Supports Planner capacity projections, increasing clients'' service needs and an expanding eligible population collectively support the proposed FY25 targets', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1801, 126, 2025, 5, NULL, 17, NULL, 24, NULL, 112, 'In the Q4 reports COVID outbreaks were added to the triditional ACD outbreak investigations. Total outbreaks investigated in FY 25 were 158 (101 COVID outbreaks and 57 non COVID outbreaks).', 158, NULL, 30, 'This is the prepandemic target. We expect to see fewer outbreaks in FY25 than FY24 as the temporary COVID staff positions end.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1802, 127, 2025, 0.6, NULL, 0.53, NULL, 0.83, NULL, 0.938, NULL, 0.94, NULL, 0.75, 'This is the prepandemic target. Based off of a number of factors that can impact whether there is confirmatory testing including individuals providing a specimen and particularly for GI illness, clinical stool testing does not identify a pathogen if samples are not collected timely.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1803, 128, 2025, 258, NULL, 71, NULL, 229, NULL, 219, NULL, 762, 'In FY25, the program began to account for agencies/organizations trained beyond those named in the legislation. During this period, the program trained Youthworks Sites twice (July 2024 and June 2025) yielding over 400 site level staff trained alone.', 500, 'We identify and select at least 1 agency from the legislation per year to implement TIC.  Based on the size of the agency and number of staff employed, the target could increase or decrease. We are also providing trainings to other city agencies and community-based organizations not listed in the legislation to help us meet our annual targets, and expand this resource to the broader  Baltimore community', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1804, 129, 2025, 179, NULL, 24, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 'The suicide prevention coordinator position was vacant from February 2024-May 8, 2025. There was no suicide prevention outreach during the 4th quarter as we were onboarding the new staff person assuming this role.', 203, 'In FY25, the program proposed conservative measures that would account for the staff vacancy in the SPC position, timeline for onboarding new staff, and time allottment for new staff to become acclimated to the position.  This enabled the program to not only meet target, but to slightly exceed it.', 150, 'This target was chosen based on staff capacity, availability of funding, and community need/experiences. While Suicide is a public health concern, its prevalence in youth is increasing, but is still very low compared to adults. This target seems realistic and attainable givenn the factors outlined.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1805, 131, 2025, 0.92, NULL, 0.95, NULL, 0.7, NULL, 0.92, NULL, 0.89, 'The program has steadily maintained a 90% satisfaction rate as reported by trainees since inception. The program feels confident that this trend will continue into subsequent reporting periods.', 0.9, 'It is our hope that 100% of the trainees will complete training with satisfaction, however over the past 3 years trainees reported 100% satisfaction in just one year of implementation compared to 90% in 2 of 3 years. Based on previous actual percentages, we wanted to set a more realistic target for FY25', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1806, 132, 2025, 0.95, NULL, 0.86, NULL, 0.79, NULL, 0.96, NULL, 0.9, 'Like the satisfaction rate, the percentage of trainees reporting increased knowledge remained steady at 90% with little to no fluctuation. Given the nature of BCFD''s work, most trainees reported attainment of knowledge that typically falls outside of the scope of their fire fighting training.', 0.9, 'Our evaluation of the training''s success is by measuring if trainees have gained knowledge and/or skills. We understand that within every training group there are various learning styles and varying degrees of foundational knowledge.  Our measure of success is noted, if after the training we are able to see increased knowledge between 90-100% in trainees reporting.  We are also trying to account for the fact that 100% of staff participating in the training do not always complete the surveys.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1807, 133, 2025, 3051, NULL, 2534, NULL, 1906, NULL, 2517, NULL, 10008, 'The number of dogs/cats entering the shelter increased due to the national shortage of affordable veterinary care, housing insecurity, and lack of local funding to adequately fund programs to assist families with keeping their pets.', 10000, 'The target is set to a reasonable number that the program believes it can reach based on funding and continued efforts to reduce intake.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1808, 134, 2025, 0.98, NULL, 0.99, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 0.94, NULL, 0.97, 'Animal Control strives for a 100% closure rate for all calls, but due to a staffing change within the bite investigation team the closure rate for animal attacks slightly decreased which decreased the overall closure rate.', 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1809, 135, 2025, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.81, 'BARCS implements programs to help decrease the number of pets entering the shelter and to increase pet retention. These programs include low cost vaccines, spay/neuter, and connecting owners with resources to include food and low cost vet care.  However, due to the current veterinary and shelter staffing shortages and the lack of affordable services in our community, BARCS is facing unprecedented hardships in maintaining normal operations.  Disruption in services across the animal care and welfare industry have created a serious challenge in preventing the intake of animals and finding homes as fast as animals come in, especially for medical and behavior cases.  This nationwide staffing shortage means a reduction in available resources to the community and a serious strain on organizations like BARCS to reach goals such as a high live release rate. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Additionally, during FY25, the shelter experienced a 2-month shutdown for the intake of dogs due to a serious respiratory virus that plagued the shelter._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The target value is 90% as the program continues to strive and accomplish saving more lives each year with the ultimate goal of saving all healthy and treatable animals.  This target value is a national goal for animal shelters.', 0.84, 'The live release rate is affected by the number of animals entering the shelter and adequate funding for community based programs to keep pets with their family.  The intake remained high due to lack of resources/funding and as a result the number of positive outcomes (live release rate) declined.', 0.9, 'The target value is 90%, as the program continues to strive and accomplish saving more lives each year with the ultimate goal of saving all healthy and treatable animals. This target value is a national goal for animal shelters.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1810, 136, 2025, 1421, NULL, 1233, NULL, 1062, NULL, 1202, NULL, 4918, '4918 inspections were completed due to a fully trained food control staff.  During this time 12 of the 13 positions were filled.  Additionally, staff were volunteering to conduct after hours inspections so we saw an increase in total inspections.', 3750, 'The target is set at 3750 inspections because the program believes that with the current level of staffing we can conduct this number of inspections. As vacancies are filled for the inspectors the number of inspections will increase.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1811, 137, 2025, 0.9903, NULL, 0.9834, NULL, 0.9878, NULL, 0.99, NULL, 0.97, '100% was not achieved due to staffing changes in the Food Supervisor being in training for half of the fiscal year.  Minor changes in reporting complaints have been made to ensure a 100% closure rate.', 1, 'The target is set to 100% because our program believes that with the appropriate resources, all complaints can be resolved within the expected timeframe.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1812, 138, 2025, 2, NULL, 2, NULL, 2, NULL, 2.5, NULL, 2, 'FY25 saw a continued 2 day average for plan review inspections.  The volume of new businesses opening has remained below average.  Staffing for the program has remained consistent.', 5, 'The target is still set at 5 because the program believes that there may be an increase in new businesses opening as the economy recovers in a post-Covid world.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1813, 139, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 4, 'The program submitted the contracts for the Enforcement Officers late, which led to a delay in the contract approval process. When compliance checks were to start, the contracted vendor informed the program that they did not have the capacity to carry out the work, due to a number of issues including recruitment of youth and a chaperone. The program then partnered with MOED to recruit a chaperone and 2 youth ages 16-20, however there was no interest expressed from participants at that time. BCHD continues to advertise and meet regularly with MOED. In a continued effort to conduct compliance checks, BCHD met with the Sheriff''s office, and several compliance checks have been made. BCHD has decided to operate under a new model for FY 26 and has recruited and hired in-house staff to conduct compliance checks. While in FY 25 the checks were not completed, outreach and education to tobacco retailers was conducted and 1,094 visits were made across the FY.', 4, 'Program leadership vacancies led to late contract submissions which delayed our contractual enforcement staff from being able to perform compliance checks. Our community based organization partner that provides underage individuals for compliance checks was unable to continue out the work.', 1000, 'BCHD contracts with retired police officers to check for compliance. This target reflects the maximum number of retailers the contracted officers are able check for compliance.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1814, 141, 2025, 652, NULL, 433, NULL, 355, NULL, 1903, 'Current data includes BCHD Outreach team data and subgrantees providing HIV testing in Non Health care settings', 6627, NULL, 12000, 'Number of tests conducted is a measure of the impact of the program', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1815, 142, 2025, 0.79, NULL, 0.8, NULL, 0.78, NULL, 0.78, 'The targets were set based on the goal of achieving a suppressed viral load, not an undetectable viral load. At some point, these terms may have been used interchangeably. The current performance measure target should reflect the suppression percentage and not the undetectable percentage.', 0.79, NULL, 0.9, 'This metric is an indicator for the effectiveness of Ryan White-funded HIV treatment providers in the Baltimore EMA. This metric also aligns with the federal Ending the Epidemic funding target.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1816, 143, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.88, 'The time period covered includes completion of transition into a new state software (Q1 and Q2). The second half of the year (Q3 and Q4) show marked increase in performance.  In Q4,  32 of 36 individuals were successfully interviewed.  Reasons for not successfully interviewing patients include lacking access to accurate contact information and patient’s preference not to speak with health department staff when the Health Department calls for a contact tracing interview.', 0.71, NULL, 0.9, 'This metric is used to determine effectiveness of the partner services team.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1817, 144, 2025, 15451, NULL, 25299, NULL, 31599, NULL, 44380, 'Data is collected cumulatively through the quarters. Additionally, we have adjusted our data capturing to not include general phone call inquiries. The target goals will be adjusted for future years.', 44380, 'The FY25 data is comperable to FY24 data. As the center reopened post pandemic, staff redirected their focus toward building up in-person education and recreation programming capacity. This led to a slight decreased in the focus on information and assistance.', 58240, 'We believe that we can increase programming by 4% as we continue to increase staff and services', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1818, 145, 2025, 11024, NULL, 20527, NULL, 25914, NULL, 48418, 'Data is captured cumulatively through the quarters. With increased staffing at senior centers we have been able to provide a higher level of programming and engagement.', 48418, 'Center staff have focused on expanding education program offerings through increased partnerships, especially focusing on health education.', 10500, 'We plan increase participation by 5% as we continue to centralize educational programming at centers', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1819, 146, 2025, 14467, NULL, 31477, NULL, 40887, NULL, 72963, 'Data is captured cumulatively through the quarters. With increased staffing at senior centers we have been able to provide a higher level of programming and engagement.', 72962, 'Center staff have focused on expanding recreation program offerings to encourage more participation at centers. Activities focus on participant interests, such as arts and crafts, performances, group games, and festive events.', 18720, 'We believe that we can increase programming by 4% as we continue to increase staff and services', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1820, 147, 2025, 9578, NULL, 17728, NULL, 24690, NULL, 32251, 'The data for each quarter are cumulative from the beginning of the fiscal year.', 32251, 'Increased community outreach by the Maryland Access Point team, and out stationing of MAP staff in senior centers resulted in greater awareness of the service, and generated a rising  number of calls to the call center.', 23993, 'MAP calls have increased 8% in FY 2024 compared with a comparable period in FY 2023. We expect this trend to continue, but at a slower rate in FY 2025. The trend is due to expanded community outreach conducted by MAP staff.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1821, 148, 2025, 295, NULL, 503, NULL, 694, NULL, 981, 'The data for each quarter are cumulative from the beginning of the fiscal year. The program did not meet the target due to staffing shortages in the period September 1, 2024 through April 1, 2025.', 981, 'Staff turnover and vacancies in FY 2025 impacted the capaciy of th program to conduct visits to nursing homes and assisted living facilities, resulting in less program visibility and fewer complaints received.', 1300, 'Complaint levels tend to fluctuate and are affected by federal and State action, program staffing, and changes in the long term care industry. On the whole we are predicting an increase in complaints over the FY 2024 target.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1822, 149, 2025, 209, NULL, 443, NULL, 601, NULL, 763, 'The data for each quarter are cumulative from the beginning of the fiscal year.  We were slightly under our target due to  fluctuations in requests for service.', 763, 'The Medicare fall Open Enrollment period generates the largest number of requests for SHIP assistance. In FY 2025, Medicare plans serving the City of Baltimore were relatively stable, reducing the need for beneficaries to seek assistance.', 774, 'In the absence of major changes in Medicare or plans offered, the SHIP program anticipates a level of beneficiary service consistent with previous years.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1823, 150, 2025, 148, NULL, 158, NULL, 159, NULL, 159, 'The data for each quarter are cumulative from the beginning of the fiscal year.', 159, 'Volunteer recruitment continues to rise as the Baby Boomer generation in Baltimore City retires and seeks opportunities for community engagement.', 145, 'We project a steady  increase in volunteers  as older adults venture more out into the community, and the health risks generated by the pandemic diminish.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1824, 151, 2025, 18, NULL, 36, NULL, 48, NULL, 17, 'There were 65 new guardianship cases appointed in addition to 89 cases that were avoided.', 65, NULL, 40, 'A social worker position has been created to prioritize alternatives to guardianship.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1825, 152, 2025, 55, NULL, 90, NULL, 115, NULL, 41, NULL, 150, NULL, 40, 'MDOA provided additional funds in FY 24 solely for waitlisted clients that will yield outcomes in FY 25.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1826, 153, 2025, 69, NULL, 67, NULL, 65, NULL, 69, 'There were 69 total participants.', 69, NULL, 70, 'The monthly subsidy amount has been stabilized to  accommodate additional clients.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1827, 154, 2025, 21, NULL, 17, NULL, 22, NULL, 22, 'The data for each quarter are cumulative from the beginning of the fiscal year. Volunteer recruitment was curtailed in the final quarter, due to the uncertainty of continued federal funding. The grant for this program was finally renewed for FY 2026 at the end of June 2025.', 22, NULL, 28, 'There was attrition to the number of volunteers post covid. Recruiting will be a priority.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1828, 155, 2025, 6925, NULL, 7046, NULL, 7126, NULL, 7245, 'The data for each quarter is cumulative from the beginning of the fiscal year.', 7245, 'The number of participants in the TaxiCard program continues to rise, as older adults and persons with disabilities seek affordable transportation alternatives.', 6500, 'We expect a continued growth in TaxiCard participants in FY 2025 building upon post pandemic trends in the program.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1829, 156, 2025, 2009, NULL, 2009, NULL, 4071, NULL, 2915, 'Data captured cumulatively through the quarters. Q3 numbers need to be adjusted due to a system error - it should be 2670.', 2915, 'BCHD  focused on improving meal quality, and selected a new vendor, which has increased program participation.', 2500, 'The pandemic led to higher than usual demand for meals. We aim to return service to more sustainable levels, especially with ARPA ending', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1830, 157, 2025, 1090, NULL, 1090, NULL, 1149, NULL, 1318, 'Data captured cumulatively through the quarters. We continue to see elevated food access needs for older adults in the city.', 1318, 'BCHD continues to adjust its numbers to slowly scale down home delivered meals so that there is not a cliff once ARPA funding ceases.', 1000, 'The pandemic led to higher than usual demand for meals. We aim to return service to more sustainable levels, especially with ARPA ending', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1831, 158, 2025, 0.84, NULL, 0.84, NULL, 0.84, NULL, 0.84, 'Satisfaction survey is done annually. This year we collected an increased number of survey responses and noted that participants desired a higher quality meal. We have contracted with a new meal provide and plan to survey participants in September to assess their satisfaction with the new service.', 0.84, 'During the pandemic, congregate meals were a grab and go structure. With the re-establishing of community meal sites in its original in person format, the congregate meal program was able to survey more participants compared to previous years. With more responses, came a wider range of responses.', 0.94, 'We believe 94% is a measure that can be attained while creating space for additional feedback', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1832, 159, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 1469, NULL, 4884, 'Reduced number of rehabs using CDBG funds due to federal restraints on funding; utilized easier sources of funding first. Housing counseling goals generally trend toward meeting  projected amounts. Additionally, it can be difficult to have all data reported in time for actuals to be reported on KPIs', 6000, 'We anticipate the funding will remain level, so service levels will remain static.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1833, 160, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Data being collected in quartely reports was more narrative than numerical which made calculating measures difficult', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1834, 161, 2025, 0.1625, NULL, 0.5375, NULL, 0.7, NULL, 0.86, 'This is a new KPI set to begin with FY26 but have started roughly compiling metrics for FY25. Tracking will be automated through Neighborly during FY26.', 0.68, 'In general, NPO subrecipients are meeting reporting deadlines. Reporting from city agencies/programs funded with CDBG continues to be difficult to compel, which skews this measure.', 0.85, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1835, 162, 2025, 15, NULL, 15, NULL, 15, NULL, 15, 'number is max that can attend with 1 employee. Believe that the Target was incorrectly entered as 60 - should be 30', 84, 'Recuited for position and all candidates decline due to payscale of position.  Position was slated to be reclassed and was eliminated from the FY26 budget', 60, 'MD Regulations for childcare centers limit each program to 30 children each.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1836, 163, 2025, 2087.99, NULL, 4053.3, NULL, 5667.15, NULL, 4004, 'amount spent/census', 3953, 'Rise in food cost in addition to students attending for extended times when schools were closed.', 3500, 'We are recruiting to bring in staff to meet the regulation of 30 children per site.  The amount spent per child will increase with the rise in food cost and supplies , as well as the need to replace equipment in high touch areas for children for them to remain in a healthy environment.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1837, 164, 2025, 0.9, NULL, 0.8, NULL, 0.8, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.84, 'familial related factors that may require the student to be absent from school', 0.9, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1838, 165, 2025, 18, NULL, 29, NULL, 23, NULL, 82, 'Developing full functionality of  the Weatherization Assistance Program, (Wx) in the Neighborly software system will enable us to better record and track certification of applications as this item does not exist in the reporting process for our mandated software, (Hancock)', 152, 'Significant organizational and administrative changes to the intake and assessment arm or weatherization kept numbers lower than expected.', 270, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1839, 166, 2025, 4, NULL, 9, NULL, 16, NULL, 0, 'There was not an active weatherization contract in place during Q4', 29, 'Navigated contract, funding, and bidding challenges that inhibited the amount of work completed in FY25.  Only one Wx contractor and HVAC company was authorized to complete work.', 100, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1840, 167, 2025, 6, NULL, 1, NULL, 14, NULL, 20, 'The increase in audits performed reflects the increase in trained staff', 41, 'FY 25 Wx was at half capacity for Building Performance Specialists (Auditors), and onboarded a new Construction Project Supervisor I.', 300, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
