    (1920, 264, 2025, 165177, NULL, 134023, NULL, 154447, NULL, 148385, NULL, 602032, 'Several factors impact the volume of 311 calls received each year. Some examples include inclement weather, roadwork, power outages etc.  Weather, seasonal events, city operations and service delivery, communications (press conferences) and public awareness, calendar driven impacts .', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1921, 265, 2025, 0.8176, NULL, 0.9132, NULL, 0.9352, NULL, 0.8069, 'The key factors driving this deterioration are:_x000D_
_x000D_
1.	Staffing vacancies: Of the 46-311 agents, currently we are only staffed at 72% due to:_x000D_
_x000D_
a.	4 agents temporarily reassigned to the DHCD call center to expand operations;_x000D_
_x000D_
b.	8 agent positions vacant; and,_x000D_
_x000D_
c.	1 agent serving as an acting supervisor._x000D_
_x000D_
2.	Unfunded Support of SYE (Summer Youth Engagement) requires us to extend hours until 2AM Friday and Saturday. To cover this initiative 4 agents that typically cover the 2-6 pm time had to be shifted to start at 6 pm to support this initiative._x000D_
_x000D_
3.	Leave usage by staff increases during the summer_x000D_
