    (1974, 365, 2025, 0.19, NULL, 0.14, NULL, 0.14, NULL, 0.21, NULL, 0.18, NULL, NULL, 'MOHS has deployed system improvemet stratgies in flex  funds wihc will assist with rental assistance for up to 6 months and by incorporating diversion at community access points', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1975, 366, 2025, 12, NULL, 9, NULL, 11, NULL, 15, 'These numbers indicate the level of hearing engagement the agency has with residents/property owners who have limited English proficiency. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Targets are never provided for this performance measure because we cannot force people into using Language Line. We can only provide it when requested.', 47, 'There''s a strong immigrant population in Baltimore and they are engaging in this process more. We also see a lot of non-English speakers with VBN properties. I think the increase in enforcement across the board is having an impact on their communities and those $1,000 fines are not easily paid.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1976, 367, 2025, 0.8, NULL, 0.58, NULL, 0.84, NULL, 0.79, 'The mainframe system that house the citations overwrites dates when a hearing is reschedule. Due to this, compiling the requested data requires manually reviewing every rescheduled hearing to see when the first hearing was scheduled. The casuses a margin of error. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
300 of those un-reviewed citations were during the 2nd quarter. Those un-reveiwed numbers likely have a big impact because the holiday season typically have a lot of reschedules._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The ECB is working with BCIT to eliminate the need for manual review so that future numbers can have a higher level of accuracy._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Regarding Q4, the further decrease in the number of hearing scheduled within 60 days was caused by an increase in citation issuance by the issuing agencies. By the end of April, the number of citations issued in 2025 had more than doubled. Additionally, the ECB was short staffed. The ECB only had one full time staff member processing requests (among their other duties). _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
As of August 14, 2025, the ECB is now fully staffed but has a significant backlog. Due to this, the numbers may not show real improvement until Q2 of FY26.', 0.75, 'Issuance is high, volume is high, and a lack of a consistent Scheduler on staff.', 0.9, 'This percentage is a high bar but our current scheduling practices should help us to hit this target', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1977, 368, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Two types of issues are appealed to the Board: 1) Unfavorable hearing decisions, and 2) Denials of a new hearing date. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The first is typically done by the respondent when they are found liable for the cited violation._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The second is typically done by the respondent when they missed their hearing, requsted a new hearing date, and were denied.', 1, 'The board agreed with all of the decisions.', 0.9, 'This percentage is a high bar but realistic bar as the number of appeals has grown over the past fiscal year. The increase in appeals seems to relate to the increase in enforcement against vacant buildings', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1978, 369, 2025, 7.75, NULL, 5.35, NULL, 7.24, NULL, 8.97, 'The hearing officer is primarily responding to respondents who have missed their opportunity to have a hearing and are seeking to either restore their hearing rights and/or have their penalties waived._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
These requests are usually received via mail, email, walk-in, and/or fax. Responses are majorily provided via email, if an email address is provided.', 7, 'These requests are pretty straight forward. We usually do very well.', 14, 'Same as the above', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1979, 370, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 16.84, NULL, 11.64, 'Q1 & Q2 are "0" because the tax sale review begins in February when the Final Bill and Legal Notices are mailed out by the Department of Finance. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Q3 was high due to outliers where the hearing officer waited for additional documentation to be provided. For example, there were 9 citations that took over a month because the Hearing officer was waiting for additional information.The volume of requests was also higher than in prior years. Combined with agency vacancies, the result was a slower turn around than anticipated. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The average for Q4 improved, as anticipated, due to several last minute requests that were turned around quickly. _x000D_
_x000D_', 14, 'The biggest impact is capacity. We also had a few rqeuests that required additional information/research where we either waited on a different City agency to provide us with information or we waited on the constituent to provide us with infomation.', 14, 'This is turnaround time gives the hearing officer time to review citations for notice and legality using various systems. Reviews can take a number of days to complete, depending on the number of properties listed in the request, the number of citations against the property, the volume of requests pending, etc.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1980, 371, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Given the target is 1, I''m assuming this is to be expressed in decimal form rather than as 100%', 1, 'All quarterly reports due in FY25 were submitted on time to the U.S. Department of Treasury.', 1, 'All treasury reports should be completed on time.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1981, 372, 2025, 328500000, NULL, 391300000, NULL, 434900000, NULL, 473400000, NULL, 473400000, 'All ARPA funds were obligated by the December 31, 2024 deadline. Because all eligible projects were underway in FY25, spending increased significantly as administrative burdens related to establishing agreements and contracts were reduced.', 370000000, 'Targets were chosen based on current spending trends and an expected increased rate moving forward', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1982, 373, 2025, 85, NULL, 90, NULL, 98, NULL, 94, NULL, 92, 'While a FY25 target was not provided, the actual number of performance and technical assistance meetings held per month were line with the number held on average during FY24. This further demonstrates that all projects were underway in FY25 due to the December 31, 2024 ARPA obligation deadline.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1983, 374, 2025, 711, NULL, 734, NULL, 760, NULL, 836, 'The original data from the Baltimore development corporation, which is the majority of small businesses served so far, was found to be unverfiable.  The data was amended to match verified small businesses served and will remain well below the FY25 target for that reason.', 840, 'The number of small businesses served in FY25 was less than anticipated due to the term end of some of the grant agreements that served small businesses.', 2875, 'Small business were a priority early, so there was a large amount served immediately, so that number is increasing at a slower rate as time goes on.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1984, 376, 2025, 0, NULL, 87, NULL, 87, NULL, 126, NULL, 126, 'Baltimore City Public Schools (BCPS) refers students for participation in YO Academy programming. This factor is based on the number of youth they refer and gives a sense of scale for service delivery in the program.', 120, 'Targets are based on an agreement with Baltimore City Public Schools.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1985, 377, 2025, 0.111, NULL, 0.38, NULL, 0.496, NULL, 0.618, NULL, 0.62, 'This represents the first full year of the BluePrint career coaching intiative. Complexities that arose from staff recruitment and building new relationships with school principals and other leaders had differential impacts on staff''s ability to reach students across different schools.', 0.6, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1986, 378, 2025, 0.07, NULL, 0.11, NULL, 0.148, NULL, 0.172, 'Blueprint career coaching is a new initiative with it''s first full school year of operations in FY25. Delays in work and reduced outcomes were in part caused by need to onboard new staff, building relationships in schools, and devising new program models. No historical baseline was available to set this goal, so 25% was a very speculative estimate.', 0.17, 'As of FY25, Blueprint Accountability and Implementation Board (AIB) didn''t provide guidance on the components of the post-secondary plan (now 6-year plan). Tools for collecting information were still being developed throughout the year and student access hindered ability to collect this information.', 0.25, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1987, 379, 2025, 0, NULL, 0.138, NULL, 0.138, NULL, 0.143, 'In some cases, students may be transferred back to traditional school after temporary YO Academy placement, leading to an inability to provide placement services to individual.', 0.41, 'Prior transposition error led to a 14% rate reported instead of a 41% rate reported. This represents an improvement from the prior year. Students missed experiences if they returned to their home school before the late spring or and failed to complete applications for work experiences.', 0.8, 'Targets are based on an agreement with Baltimore City Public Schools.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1988, 380, 2025, 612, NULL, 1002, NULL, 1362, NULL, 1749, NULL, 1749, 'Performance is based on referrals from DSS, which is based on enrollment of individuals in TANF programming. New federal policy that limits benefits may impact the number of referrals made to MOED.', 1200, 'Goals set by DSS Contract.  Contract to change for FY 24 requiring outreach for non-custodial parents and juvenile offenders', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1989, 381, 2025, 0.9286, NULL, 0.9444, NULL, 0.4928, NULL, 0.49, 'The population of individuals being included in this retention metric has expanded to a larger and more difficult to reach pool. Previously, it only included individuals actively engaged with program during the retention period.', 0.49, 'DSS modified metric to be inclusive of individuals who are no longer receiving TANF benefits. These individuals are more difficult to contact than those still on their caseloads, which has led to a reduction in performance.', 0.65, 'Goals set by DSS Contract.  Contract to change for FY 24 requiring outreach for non-custodial parents and juvenile offenders', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1990, 382, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 0.619, NULL, 0.27, 'The population of individuals being included in this retention metric has expanded to a larger and more difficult to reach pool. Previously, it only included individuals actively engaged with program during the retention period.', 0.27, 'DSS modified metric to be inclusive of individuals who are no longer receiving TANF benefits. These individuals are more difficult to contact than those still on their caseloads, which has led to a reduction in performance.', 0.65, 'Goals set by DSS Contract.  Contract to change for FY 24 requiring outreach for non-custodial parents and juvenile offenders', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1991, 383, 2025, 139, NULL, 276, NULL, 417, NULL, 561, 'Program experienced staff turnover across multiple centers as well as turnover of program leaderhsip.', 561, 'Community Job Hub staff focus on job fair models brought individuals to the center, but didn''t yield long term engagement with clients. CJH staff were also frequently requested to attend public-facing events diverting time away from intensive service delivery.', 1000, 'Since more job readiness services are now being delivered virtually such as the Employ Baltimore Show on Facebook Live, it has become more difficult to track the number of job readiness services delivered. We are exploring ways to expand virtual services that will allow for counting of individual attendees. Intensive services include job readiness services delivered by staff. Staffing has increased and stabilized ability to deliver services.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1992, 384, 2025, 644, NULL, 898, NULL, 1065, NULL, 1521, 'Program experienced staff turnover across multiple centers as well as turnover of program leaderhsip.', 1521, 'Significant staff turnover across One-Stops and Employment Connection Center left agency at less than full capacity during this period. This also represented a time of expanidng unemployment following post-COVID recovery.', 2500, 'With the expansion of the Community Job Hub network and mobile career navigators as a result of American Rescue Plan Act (ARPA) funding, MOED will be reaching more Baltimore City residents.  As the economy recovers from COVID, more residents will be placed in employment', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1993, 385, 2025, 517, NULL, 913, NULL, 1200, NULL, 1522, NULL, 1522, 'New Community Job Hubs became more established in their second year of operations and were able to bring more individuals into centers, especially through hosting of regular job fair events.', 1415, 'With the expansion of the Community Job Hub network and mobile career navigators as a result of American Rescue Plan Act (ARPA) funding, MOED will be reaching more Baltimore City residents.  As the economy recovers from COVID, more residents will be served in their communities.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1994, 386, 2025, 7970, NULL, 12689, NULL, 17405, NULL, 22446, NULL, 22446, 'MOED One-Stop Centers serve any walk-in clients from Baltimore City. Greater comfort with in-person services and increased unemployment are two macro-factors that increased client load from prior years.', 20000, 'The number served is based on historical data within the current Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act legislation (WIOA)', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1995, 387, 2025, 0.684, NULL, 0.688, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.676, NULL, 0.68, 'The state of MD calculated performance lagged an annualized, with FY25 data representing clients exiting programs 1/1/2023 - 12/31/2023 and the jobs they attained in CY2024. CY2024 saw increases in unemployment following post-pandemic recovery following historically low unemployment in May 2023.', 0.595, 'These Federal Funds are disbursed from the Federal Department of Labor and passed through the MD Department of Labor.  There are performance measures developed by the legislation that must be met for this funding.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1996, 388, 2025, 0.67, NULL, 0.649, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.654, NULL, 0.65, 'The state of MD calculated performance lagged an annualized, with FY25 data representing clients exiting programs 7/1/2023 - 6/30/2024 and the jobs they attained in CY2024. CY2024 saw increases in unemployment following post-pandemic recovery following historically low unemployment in May 2023.', 0.595, 'These Federal Funds are disbursed from the Federal Department of Labor and passed through the MD Department of Labor.  There are performance measures developed by the legislation that must be met for this funding.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1997, 389, 2025, 379, NULL, 783, NULL, 1586, NULL, 2001, NULL, 2001, 'MOED Re-Entry Center services serve any walk-in clients from Baltimore City with experience in the criminal justice system. Factors that could influence outcomse include availability of other re-entry services, economic circumstances, and changes in pre-trail detension and prison population.', 1800, 'The Mayor''s Office of Employment Development has an annual contract with the Maryland Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services (DPSCS) to provide workforce services to previously incarcerated residents looking to return to the workforce.  The goals are set within this agreement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1998, 390, 2025, 103, NULL, 141, NULL, 270, NULL, 433, NULL, 433, 'Increase in robust re-entry hiring partnerships allowed for modest increase in performance from prior year.', 400, 'The Mayor''s Office of Employment Development has an annual contract with the Maryland Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services (DPSCS) to provide workforce services to previously incarcerated residents looking to return to the workforce.  The goals are set within this agreement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (1999, 391, 2025, 268, NULL, 510, NULL, 665, NULL, 882, NULL, 882, 'FY25 saw new strategies put in place to expand reach of YO centers, following post-COVID return of in-person services. These efforts focused on large events succeeded in getting young people into the center and enrolled.', 850, 'The Youth Opportunity Centers have been in Baltimore for over 20 years and historical data has been used to set the target values', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2000, 392, 2025, 0.84, NULL, 0.68, NULL, 0.63, NULL, 0.53, NULL, 0.53, 'Significant staff turnover at HEBCAC as well as prior statements on large event focus from Westside influenced frequency of job readiness support provision to participants.', 0.85, 'The Youth Opportunity Centers have been in Baltimore for over 20 years and historical data has been used to set the target values', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2001, 393, 2025, 0.18, NULL, 0.16, NULL, 0.16, NULL, 0.22, 'Significant staff turnover at one of two YO centers led to significant decline in performance due to several months without full staffing.', 0.22, 'HEBCAC YO staff experienced full staff turnover, significantly reducing their outcomes. A bellweather of their ultimate closure. Efforts to increase enrollment through events didn''t yield longer-term engagements that end in placement/training, so model is being getting exeternal evaluation.', 0.54, 'Historical data has been used as a baseline to set the target values. New strategies will determine whether the targets will need to be adjusted in the upcoming year.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2002, 394, 2025, 0.99, NULL, 0.99, NULL, 0.99, NULL, 0.96, NULL, 0.96, 'As always, YO interventions continue to support youth and provide alternatives to behaviors that lead to criminal justice involvement. Loss of PACT funding also influenced amount of indivduals with prior justice involvement interacting with YO.', 0.9, 'When the outcome budgeting process first began, the Youth Opportunity Service was in the Public Safety pillar with the thought that engaging young people in productive services would keep them out of trouble.  Once the service was moved to Prioritizing Youth the measure was not removed as the purpose for the measure remains the same.  The target values are based on historical data.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2003, 395, 2025, 10212, NULL, 10212, NULL, 10212, NULL, 10212, NULL, 10212, 'YouthWorks always experiences greater demand than supply, because young people want to work and their families benefit from these additional wages.  In FY25, the injection of temporary ARPA funding enabled us to offer more jobs than we have ever done before.', 7000, 'The number of slots available for youth works participants is based on the amount of funding from a variety of sources including the Baltimore City general funds to pay the salaries of the youth.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2004, 396, 2025, 0.928, NULL, 0.928, NULL, 0.928, NULL, 0.928, NULL, 0.93, 'YouthWorks continues to work hard to support workplaces in finding talented youth.', 0.9, 'Numeric values based on historic data', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2005, 397, 2025, 0.865, NULL, 0.865, NULL, 0.865, NULL, 0.865, NULL, 0.87, 'With a 25% increase in the number of youth offered opportunities, YouthWorks was required to pitch a broader tent of workplaces to host youth. Some of these new workplaces may not have had as much practice as legacy sites in connecting work experience to job readiness skills.', 0.9, 'The survey questions include a scale of scoring that asks if the young person feels like their skills have increased over their time in the program in categories like time management, career exposure, financial literacy, and was the worksite engaging for the youth.  Numeric values based on historic data', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2006, 398, 2025, 76, NULL, 149, NULL, 171, NULL, NULL, 'This service is connected to our WIOA Youth Programs which are funded on an annual cycle via federal dollars passed through the state. State holds us to their fiscal year (October - September). We have only completed the 3rd quarter of operations for this program''s funding cycle. To align with my predecessor''s work and the project itself, we''ve only reported Q1, Q2, Q3.', 171, 'FY25 performance was mired due to issues with two providers. Despite applying and getting offered funds, one provider declined to participate. Another performed poorly and had remaining funds rescinded.', 215, 'A Request for Proposal is released every two years to select providers who will deliver youth services as outlined in the Workforce Innovation and opportunity Act Legislation.  The target enrollment is based on the selected providers.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2007, 399, 2025, 0.054, NULL, 0.289, NULL, 0.708, NULL, NULL, 'This service is connected to our WIOA Youth Programs which are funded on an annual cycle via federal dollars passed through the state. State holds us to their fiscal year (October - September). We have only completed the 3rd quarter of operations for this program''s funding cycle. To align with my predecessor''s work and the project itself, we''ve only reported Q1, Q2, Q3.', 0.87, 'Providers who did enroll students were high performing ones, capable of connecting individuals to credentials and measurable skill gains.', 0.67, 'These Federal Funds are disbursed from the Federal Department of Labor and passed through the MD Department of Labor.  There are performance measures developed by the legislation that must be met for this funding.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2008, 400, 2025, 0.257, NULL, 0.597, NULL, 0.708, NULL, NULL, 'This service is connected to our WIOA Youth Programs which are funded on an annual cycle via federal dollars passed through the state. State holds us to their fiscal year (October - September). We have only completed the 3rd quarter of operations for this program''s funding cycle. To align with my predecessor''s work and the project itself, we''ve only reported Q1, Q2, Q3.', 0.92, 'Providers who did enroll students were high performing ones, capable of connecting individuals to credentials and measurable skill gains.', 0.55, 'These Federal Funds are disbursed from the Federal Department of Labor and passed through the MD Department of Labor.  There are performance measures developed by the legislation that must be met for this funding.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2009, 401, 2025, 2, NULL, 2, NULL, 3, NULL, 5, NULL, 6, 'FY25 goal was 4; we completed 6 due to increased demand for outreach, strong partner engagement, and proactive scheduling with Contracting agencies. These meetings help prevent violations by clarifying requirements and improving compliance early.', 4, 'We are dedicated to fostering a collaborative environment through the organization of meetings, forums, and presentations between the community and the wage commission. These initiatives are designed not only to ensure contractors comply with all relevant wage laws, but also to educate workers about their rights. By encouraging open dialogue and shared understanding, we aim to create strong partnerships between all stakeholders. We believe that these collaborative efforts are fundamental in promoting a fair and informed workforce, and in strengthening the relationships between the community, contractors, and the wage commission.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2010, 402, 2025, 66, NULL, 80, NULL, 54, NULL, 73, NULL, 200, 'FY25 met the goal of 200 (completed 200). Results are largely driven by contractor compliance—late payroll violations are not within investigators’ control. OECR provided outreach and contract support to help contractors comply, but timeliness varies.', 200, 'While the number of payrolls issued by the commission is beyond our direct control, we are actively committed to helping contractors maintain compliance with all aspects of the prevailing wage law. Through focused outreach and comprehensive education, we aim to equip contractors with the necessary knowledge and tools to adhere to these laws. Our ultimate goal is to assist contractors in avoiding any potential fines or penalties.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2011, 403, 2025, 0.9, NULL, 0.95, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Despite the percentage of cases closed having decreased, the Wage Commission remains committed to collecting 100% of the money owed to complainants. Our focus continues to be on ensuring that all claims are addressed and resolved effectively.', 1, 'FY25 achieved 100% (target 80%) because staff prioritized timely intake, early outreach, and aggressive follow-up to move cases to closure. Timing was still influenced by contractor responsiveness, extension requests, and Board decision schedules.', 0.8, 'Upon conclusion of investigations, it is often found that employers owe their employees a certain amount in restitution. This compensation, intended to rectify any harm or loss suffered by the employees, is typically collected at the end of these investigations. However, some contractors may contest the findings of the investigationand this course of action can subsequently lead to litigation.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2012, 404, 2025, 0.84, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.87, NULL, 0.8, 'At the beginning of the fiscal year, our department experienced a significant staffing change when we lost an employee. For the majority of the year, we operated with only two investigators. In Quarter 3, we hired a new employee who has been undergoing training. Unfortunately, during this time, a seasoned employee retired, which has further impacted our operations. This reduction in personnel has led to a decrease in the number of cases we are able to close.', 0.85, 'FY2025 exceeded the 70% target, closing 85% of cases within 6 months while operating most of the year with only two investigators. Closure timelines were influenced by contractor response times, extension requests, and the timing of final Board decisions.', 0.7, 'With the provision of additional resources and tools, as well as the recruitment of a new investigator, we anticipate that cases will be closed within a timeframe of less than six months."', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
