Q4: 17 meetings (13-ACC, 4 PAB), 7 presentations or outreach events we hosted or participated in', 71, 'FY25 outreach activity increased due to continued engagement with community groups, agencies, and stakeholders to share information about the Police Accountability Board, Administrative Charging Committee and complaint process.', 40, 'Community and External Parter engagement and education is a key component of supporting police accountability, increasing stakeholder knowledge and buy-in to accelerate increases in public trust and safety', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2021, 413, 2025, 0.97, NULL, 0.94, NULL, 0.91, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 0.95, 'FY25 performance reflects established review procedures and coordination with law enforcement agencies, which supported timely responses and case determinations.', 0.9, 'State and local law require that the Administrative Charging Committee issue a determination or request further investigation within 30 days of receiving the completed investigation from the law enforcement agency', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2022, 414, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 0.99, NULL, 0.99, 'FY25 results reflect established intake and case management procedures that support prompt review and forwarding of complaints to the appropriate law enforcement agency.', 0.9, 'State and local law require that a complaint of police misconduct directly filed with the Police Accountability Board should be forwarded to the appropriate law enforcement agency within 3 days', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2023, 415, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Of the 5 projects scheduled for UDAAP meetings in FY2025 Q4, all were scheduled within 60 days of initial submittal.', 1, 'In FY2025, agency staff provide timely support to design teams working on 26 items scheduled for UDAAP review (a similar number of items scheduled in FY2024). Performance remained high despite mid-year staffing changes with the departure of the Urban Design Team supervisor in Jan. 2025.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2024, 416, 2025, 0.698, NULL, 0.714, NULL, 0.894, NULL, 0.971, 'Of the 35 projects scheduled for the BMZA docket in FY2025 Q4, only 1 was later than the 2 business days before the meeting.', 0.8, 'In FY2025, agency staff met the target for timely submission of recommendation reports to BMZA. Agency staff also onboarded a new BMZA liaison in Sept. 2024 (replacing a retiring staff member) and migrated to use Accela for the management of appeal cases.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2025, 417, 2025, 0.8, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 0.89, 'In FY2025, the number of subdivision requests decreased for the second year. Reported review times remained above the target value. In Sept. 2024, the agency hired a new Subdivision Manager who took over from other staff who had filled the role on an interim basis since the beginning of FY2025.', 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2026, 418, 2025, 0.77, NULL, 0.76, NULL, 0.74, NULL, 0.84, NULL, 0.78, 'In FY2025, CHAP staff maintained improved Authorization-to-proceed application review times throughout the year. In Jan. 2026, the CCE to Accela migration created challenges for CHAP staff in managing the Authorization-to-proceed application process and, in spring 2025, CHAP leadership retired.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2027, 419, 2025, 0.65, NULL, 0.88, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'In the first quarter of FY25, we had just onboarded a new staff person and were actively training them to be the primary tax credit reviewer.', 0.88, 'The FY2025 actuals show significant improvements compared to FY23 and FY24 due to an increased emphasis on timely review by CHAP supervisor and leadership and a modest decline in overall application volume.', 0.7, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2028, 420, 2025, 20, NULL, 27, NULL, 10, NULL, 12, 'FY2025 Q1 reported accurately, based on calendar information.  FY2025 Q2-Q4 updated later with information provided by CHAP director.', 69, 'In FY2025, CHAP staff continued to participate in community meetings and other activities related to landmark and historic district designation. Agency staff onboarded a new CHAP staff member in Jun. 2024 to support designations and tax credit review.', 60, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2029, 422, 2025, 0.56, NULL, 0.41, NULL, 0.78, NULL, 0.66, 'The FY''25 total data doesn''t include data from 1/27/25 - 2/5/25. The new permit system doesn''t include data in that timeframe.', 0.55, 'Technical issues w/ CCE in FY2025 Q1 and Q2 slowed review time for some permits and the migration to Accela in late Jan. 2025 created additional challenges in Q3/Q4 due to staff re-training needs and issues with permit assignments. Note permits from 1/27/25 - 2/5/25 are excluded from this report.', 0.6, 'Employee retention has been challenging and the hiring process has been slow-moving. Given that permits are assigned to specific permit reviewers, they will need to be re-assigned when we''re not fully staffed. Adding the extra workload to remaining staff will likely reduce the speed at which permits can be reviewed so a decrease in the target will be expected if we''re unable to retain staff or until new staff is hired.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2030, 423, 2025, 84940, NULL, 84940, NULL, 84940, NULL, 84940, 'The Office of Sustainability collects and reports data annually in the city''s Sustainability Report (https://www.baltimoresustainability.org/about/achievements-2/ ). Annual reporting better accommodates our reporting process, progress and year over year comparisons for the fours measures in our service which related to the Office’s work. Performance measures 7651 through 7654 were initially only reported for Q2 of FY 2025 which reflects the end of calendar year 2024 as we have finalized the data collection process for January – December for 2024. Data for Q3 of FY25 that cover January through March of 2025, will be included in the city’s 2025 Annual Sustainability report which will be released in April/May 2026.  Per guidance from OPI staff, the FY25 total and FY25 Q4 data has been input to match the FY25 Q2 report.', 84940, 'Agency staff reported that the number of customers engaged in calendar year 2024 exceeded the FY2025 target value again due to both robust communications/programs and a continued increase in traffic on the Office of Sustainability website.', 78000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2031, 424, 2025, 147, NULL, 147, NULL, 147, NULL, 147, 'The Office of Sustainability collects and reports data annually in the city''s Sustainability Report (https://www.baltimoresustainability.org/about/achievements-2/ ). Annual reporting better accommodates our reporting process, progress and year over year comparisons for the fours measures in our service which related to the Office’s work. Performance measures 7651 through 7654 were initially only reported for Q2 of FY 2025 which reflects the end of calendar year 2024 as we have finalized the data collection process for January – December for 2024. Data for Q3 of FY25 that cover January through March of 2025, will be included in the city’s 2025 Annual Sustainability report which will be released in April/May 2026.  Per guidance from OPI staff, the FY25 total and FY25 Q4 data has been input to match the FY25 Q2 report.', 152, 'Agency staff exceeded the FY2025 target for city staff engagement due to combined work on DGS Energy Efficiency trainings, GSI (Green Infrastructure) Accelerator Sessions, WEDG (Waterfront Edge Design Guidelines) Certification training, and the Mayor''s Sustainability and Resiliency Subcabinet.', 120, 'We anticipate being able to increase performance under this measure as we begin to engage with additional agency staff to implement actions under the updated Climate Action Plan and Disaster Preparedness Plan, which were adopted in FY24.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2032, 425, 2025, 0.14, NULL, 0.14, NULL, 0.14, NULL, 0.14, 'The Office of Sustainability collects and reports data annually in the city''s Sustainability Report (https://www.baltimoresustainability.org/about/achievements-2/ ). Annual reporting better accommodates our reporting process, progress and year over year comparisons for the fours measures in our service which related to the Office’s work. Performance measures 7651 through 7654 were initially only reported for Q2 of FY 2025 which reflects the end of calendar year 2024 as we have finalized the data collection process for January – December for 2024. Data for Q3 of FY25 that cover January through March of 2025, will be included in the city’s 2025 Annual Sustainability report which will be released in April/May 2026.  Per guidance from OPI staff, the FY25 total and FY25 Q4 data has been input to match the FY25 Q2 report.', 0.14, 'Agency staff reported progress on 14% more recommendations in calendar year 2024 or a cumulative total of 71% Sustainability Plan recommendations to date (exceeding the 5% target for FY2024 and FY2025). Agency staff expect to publish the actuals report for the 2025 calendar year in spring 2026.', 0.05, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2033, 426, 2025, 0.31, NULL, 0.31, NULL, 0.31, NULL, 0.31, 'The Office of Sustainability collects and reports data annually in the city''s Sustainability Report (https://www.baltimoresustainability.org/about/achievements-2/ ). Annual reporting better accommodates our reporting process, progress and year over year comparisons for the fours measures in our service which related to the Office’s work. Performance measures 7651 through 7654 were initially only reported for Q2 of FY 2025 which reflects the end of calendar year 2024 as we have finalized the data collection process for January – December for 2024. Data for Q3 of FY25 that cover January through March of 2025, will be included in the city’s 2025 Annual Sustainability report which will be released in April/May 2026.  Per guidance from OPI staff, the FY25 total and FY25 Q4 data has been input to match the FY25 Q2 report.', 0.28, 'FY2025 is the first full year following the adoption of the Baltimore City Climate Action Plan Update in Jan. 2024. For calendar year 2024, agency staff reported progress on 18 of 64 (28%) recommendations (an increase greater than the preliminary 10% target).', 0.1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2034, 427, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 160446, 'The FY25 HFPA Funds ($160,446) were distributed in Q4 to two grantees (Maryland Hunger Solutions and Maryland Market Money).', 160446, 'Agency staff continued to meet the target by distributing the full amount of the HFPA allocation to eligible organizations. In FY2025, the program granted $60K to Maryland Hunger Solutions and $100K to Maryland Market Money.', 160446, 'This is the full amount for the HFPA Funds in the FY25 Budget Proposal.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2035, 428, 2025, 38.9, NULL, 50.3, NULL, 32.8, NULL, 36, 'Some updates are needed for the Watch Center Portal to improve tracking of Crime Analysis and Mapping requests and their completion times._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
1.	Editable completion dates for supervisors: Supervisors should be able to adjust a request’s completion date when an analyst delivers the report on time but fails to close the request in the Portal until days or even months later. For example, one request appears to have taken nearly three months, but the analyst actually completed it within a week — significantly inflating the average completion time for Q3 when it''s closed out in June._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
2.	Separate request type for Crime Intelligence requests: Since early this year, Crime Intelligence requests have been submitted under Crime Analysis and Mapping, even though they should have their own request type in the Portal. For 2025 Q4, including these requests pushes the average completion time to 66.6 hours; excluding them lowers it to 36 hours._x000D_
_x000D_', 45, 'Axon Records and other improved technology has led to a shorter turnaround time for analytics portal request.  Data pulls are not automated and take much less time.', 72, 'This is a requirement for the analytics portal submission turnaround.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2036, 429, 2025, 0.4, NULL, 0.37, NULL, 0.33, NULL, 0.56, NULL, 0.42, 'Targeted marketing and ongoing analysis of this segment of applicants in the hiring process to monitor progress towards with target throughout the year.', 0.3, 'Plan in FY25 for additional community-based outreach focused on Baltimore City Residents', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2037, 430, 2025, 0.46, NULL, 0.48, NULL, 0.48, NULL, 0.5, 'We continue to increase in our performance around proactivity. As we review this increase the department is aiming to become more specific in how we positively and proactively engage community. Next year this measure may decrease as we are removing directed patrol that doesn not encourage officer to get out of the car as much as the other practivity options (foot patrol, business checks)', 0.48, 'The FY25 target of 33% was exceeded and measured at an average of 48%. This goal was met.  A BPD member spending approximately half of their time proactively addressing crime problems is excellent and if sustained, will show dividends in future crime reduction (FY26).', 0.33, 'No longer including directed patrol after Q1 in FY24. The Patrol Budget Service is now Patrol & Community Policing Bureau so would like to rework this measure for FY25 after we determine how we want to include the community policing component.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2038, 431, 2025, 0.98, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 0.99, 'The lab was able to make improvements to backlog reduction due to additional staff and efficiency improvements including a Lean Six Sigma review of at least one process in every unit. While the goal of 125% was not attained this FY, the lab still was able to reverse backlog growth significantly, and achieve strong backlog reduction for the FY.', 0.0101, '100% indicates the lab processes more requests than it receives, reducing backlog. With most backlogs eliminated, the focus is shifting to maintaining throughput near 100% while improving turnaround times and allowing flexibility during staffing changes.', 1, 'Greater than 100% means the backlog is being reduced (accepted intake plus backlog cases is greater than 100% requests completed).  We also integrated JusticeTrax this year which tracks work more efficiently and accurately.  FY24 Q1 is nearly 100%.  We are optimistically targeting 125% in FY25.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2039, 432, 2025, 0.1, NULL, 0.1, NULL, 0.1, NULL, 0.1, NULL, 0.1, 'We continue to meet this goal, which is a policy requirement', 0.1, 'This is a Consent Decree requirement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2040, 433, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Staffed and assessed permits submitted in Opengov.', 1, 'BPD met the 7 day SLA the previous year so we will continue to aspire to that high standard.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2041, 434, 2025, 0.2, NULL, 0.2, NULL, 0.2, NULL, 0.23, NULL, 0.21, 'We met the target of 20% by achievig 21%.', 0.2, 'To follow CIT plan', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2042, 435, 2025, 0.89, NULL, 0.89, NULL, 0.89, NULL, 0.89, NULL, 0.89, 'The Monitoring Team only completed 3 assessments in 2025.  This metric is based on their assessments.', 0.95, 'This is where we want to be in terms of Consent Decree progress.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2043, 436, 2025, 1, NULL, 0.6, NULL, 0.6, NULL, 0.73, 'Watch Center is continuing the civilianization process, which includes the OID report. The slight increase in the time to completion from Q3 to Q4 is due to new hires learning the report and new units (such as OSU) are now assisting in fulfilling requests._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
For FY25 the goal has been met on average, but continued hiring and training will likely make the goal relevant for the foreseeable future._x000D_
