    (2044, 437, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'No data is available for quarterly reporting because this data is only available on an annually bases.', 0.43, 'This is the average at the end of FY25.', 0.29, 'Based on Statista NE regional clearance rate.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2045, 438, 2025, 0.22, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Scheduling conflicts, as well as other Level 3 Use of Force incidents occuring have caused PRBs not to take place as scheduled.', 1, 'a requirement to submit to Performance Review Board', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2046, 439, 2025, 0.18, NULL, 0.16, NULL, 0.26, NULL, 0.21, 'Staffing continues to be an issue with completing the cases in the required time.  We have added civilians to assist, but more staffing is needed.', 0.24, 'Increased avenues for making complaints led to more complaints received.  There was, however, a staffing shortage.', 0.6, 'We wish to continue to strive for the target set in FY 23 and believe that we meet that with the addition of the civilian investigators while expanding on our continued progress.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2047, 440, 2025, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0.647, 'NIBRS Clearance rate', 0.67, 'This is FY25 average of the end of quarter clearance rate for all four quarters in FY25', 0.42, 'Goal was changed from UCR similiar sized cities rates to Statista Regional rate as benchmark. This will also need to move to CID Service moving forward after Org chart changes', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2048, 441, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, 'Thanks to SWAT''s continued quality of training we were able to avoid any type of injuries.', 1, 'The goal of every FY is and will be to resolve all high risk warrant without injuries to all parties involved.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2049, 442, 2025, 0.59, NULL, 0.96, NULL, 0.95, NULL, 0.88, NULL, 0.85, 'Staffing challenges and the timeframe to complete the investigation reduced opportunities to dialogue with the ACC about the difference in findings and a possible alignment.', 1, 'The goal is to be in alignment at all times to so the target is to meet ACC findings.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2050, 443, 2025, 0.3188, NULL, 0.4188, NULL, 0.2813, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.81, 'Although this figure falls below the 90% target that was established, it is expected to fluctuate. This is due to the metric measuring only the number of individuals assigned for outreach/notification compared to the number of individuals who ultimately received the notification.', 1, 'Custom Notifications are part of GVRS- working with service partners to communicate with people at highest risk of involvement in gun violence. This goal was originally set without sufficient experience or data so moving forward the team would like to adjust the measure to a % to assess the activity conducted.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2051, 444, 2025, 0.21, NULL, 0.21, NULL, 0.21, NULL, 0.22, NULL, 0.21, 'goal exceded by 1%, however, a new calculation for this metric will appear to show a decreased percentage.  This isn''t a lower #of calls being diverted but a more accurate reflection of the %of calls for service being diverted from patrol. We are submitting new FY25 data with the updated formula.', 0.2, 'This assists with the patrol staffing shortage and seek to be able to reach this goal.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2052, 445, 2025, 0.9, NULL, 0.9, NULL, 0.7, NULL, 0.88, 'Watch Center developed a Help Guide in the last quarter to help give very specific guidance on how to create the reports for the new civilian staff. This guide likely led to improved scores seen from Q3 to Q4.', 0.84, 'N/A- removing this measure', 0.9, 'Goal set for new measure and accountability step for reports published by OID (Operational Intelligence Division)', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2053, 446, 2025, 0.98, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 0.97, NULL, 0.98, NULL, 0.98, 'We excedded the goal, which is why the goal was increased in 2027', 0.9, 'This is an industry best practice.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2054, 447, 2025, 1, NULL, 0.93, NULL, 0.7, NULL, 0.88, NULL, 0.87, 'Warrants are opened and served on an ongoing basis. This "% served number" represents a snapshot at the second half of the year of the fiscal year of the number of warrants homicide open at the time of end of the fisical year divided by the number of total warrants served that YTD (as of June 30th,', 0.9, 'The target was set recognizing that unforeseen circumstances may potentially impede our service endeavors.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2055, 448, 2025, 0.28, NULL, 0.34, NULL, 0.38, NULL, 0.34, NULL, 0.34, 'Targeted marketing and ongoing analysis of this segment of applicants in the hiring process to monitor progress towards with target throughout the year.', 0.3, 'Plan in FY25 for additional outreach to women applicants towards the department''s 30x30 pledge', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2056, 449, 2025, 0.68, NULL, 0.59, NULL, 0.61, NULL, 0.65, NULL, 0.63, 'Targeted marketing and ongoing analysis of this segment of applicants in the hiring process to monitor progress towards with target throughout the year.', 0.5, 'This goal is reflective of what was achieved this year, above the stated FY24 goal', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2057, 450, 2025, 35, NULL, 32, NULL, 55, NULL, 44, NULL, 166, 'Increase of High-Risk Raids due to increased number of investigations by BPD Units and Outside Jurisdictions and higher criteria qualifications requring SWAT to conduct Raids.', 125, 'The goal is based on FY23 numbers', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2058, 451, 2025, 100, NULL, 90, NULL, 72, NULL, 101, 'This information is captured by individuals entering information in a database.  The adjusted numbers reflect current information that was not previously captured.', 371, 'The FY25 outreach target of 250 hours was exceeded. Staff contributed extensive time to education and community engagement, promoting science careers and strengthening partnerships with schools, universities, and community organizations.', 250, 'Our community outreach coordinator as well as our forensic scientists routinely contribute hundreds of hours of free science education and community engagement throughout the year.  We expect to provide a similar level of service in this area in FY25.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2059, 452, 2025, 338, NULL, 174, NULL, 198, NULL, 262, NULL, 972, 'We did not reach the Target number of 1,000 calls due to fewer requests from BPD Units and Outside Jurisdictions requiring our Units to assist them.', 1000, 'The goal is based on FY23 numbers', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2060, 453, 2025, 40, NULL, 59, NULL, 66, NULL, 55, NULL, 220, 'Targeted marketing; increased staff added to Recruitment Team and Background Investigations Team to help attract and process applicant; and weekly analysis of YTD, as well as Yr-over-Yr progress towards target.', 175, 'While the national trends on hiring remain challenging, we hope increased investment and additional community partnerships will allow us to meet this goal, above what was achieved in FY24', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2061, 454, 2025, 16.3, NULL, 13, NULL, 17.5, NULL, 18.71, 'BPD does not control the number of complaints filed against officers, but with additional training and supervision the hope is that complaints will decline.', 66, 'Increased avenues for making complaints led to more complaints received. Additionally, we continue to conduct our internal audits and inspections, which may reveal policy or procedural violations that could lead to complaints against an officer.', 55, 'Regardless of how the complaint is received, we still strive to have fewer complaints per officer.  Therefore, we propose the goal remain the same for the next fiscal year.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2062, 455, 2025, 7.29, NULL, 7.61, NULL, 8.05, NULL, 7.97, 'We''ve maintaned this metric despite staffing challenges, as this remains a priority of the department', 8, 'The FY25 average time of 7.73 minutes is consistent with our ability to respond to CFS with the current staffing available.', 10, 'Set service level agreement for this measure.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2063, 456, 2025, 11649, NULL, 8245, NULL, 1697, NULL, 16902, 'Q2 and Q4 demonstrate increases attributable to the number of drug burns and gun burns that occurred during those time periods. The difference in the actual as compared to the target is a result of the process inprovements implemented, e.g., re-allocation of resources, aligning policies with industry standards.', 38493, 'The FY25 target of 33,000 items was exceeded due to strong performance by the EMU and disposition team. The division aims for a 1:1 intake-to-disposition ratio but is currently limited by a required operational relocation during HQ garage repairs.', 33000, 'We have been working on process improvements in EM and strengthening policy 1401 which dictates dispositioning.  FY24 Q1 has show an uptick as a result.  FY24 projection appears to be on target to reach 30000+.  FY25 projection is a 10% increase over FY24 as we expect to hire 5 new civilian investigators who will help with item dispositions and returning property to citizens.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2064, 457, 2025, 5394, NULL, 5383, NULL, 5389, NULL, 4205, NULL, 20371, 'N/A- replacing measure', 16000, 'Will set traget for updated metric.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2065, 458, 2025, 579, NULL, 2060, NULL, 1047, NULL, 622, 'One large driver of the increase was the training needed in order to stand up the new Digital Forensics Unit.  Nearly 2000 of the total number of training hours were as a result of bringing this service online and new hires in the unit.  Another driver of the increase was the use of grant funding to support some additional training in other units. And finally, the widespread availability of local and online training has increased our ability to deliver more forensic, quality assurance, and leadership content to our scientists.', 4308, 'The FY25 target was 3,750 hours and was exceeded. Staff were encouraged to pursue additional training opportunities, including free or low-cost options, and the division hosted training events to increase participation and reduce costs.', 3750, 'There are approximately 150 scientists and support staff who are required to obtain continuing education credits each year.  The target for FY25 allows for each of these 150 scientists to spend 25 hours per year on CE activities.  Given the dynamic nature of forensic science, ongoing education ensures that forensic scientists are equipped with the latest tools and techniques to enhance the accuracy and reliability of their work. CE in forensics also plays a vital role in maintaining the highest ethical standards, workplace hazard awareness and strong employee engagement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2066, 459, 2025, 138, NULL, 112, NULL, 116, NULL, 171, NULL, 537, 'We exceded the Target number thanks to the upgraded equipment installed and the higher number of requests for FOXTROT assistance.', 450, 'Previously goals were based on Stolen Autos & Carjacking assists only, now they are based on 10 different arrest types.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2067, 460, 2025, 33, NULL, 28, NULL, 16, NULL, 50, NULL, 127, 'Accounting for any additional events added to the calendar year that may not have been in previous years  as well as any key drivers that would increase staffing such as rise in attendance.', 125, 'Estimate was projected based on prior data.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2068, 461, 2025, 62, NULL, 69, NULL, 49, NULL, 74, NULL, 254, 'The FY25 deployment target was exceeded. While deployments depend partly on crime rates, awareness of these technologies is growing. Training, demonstrations, and conference presentations are helping expand adoption of these forensic tools.', 225, 'This is a new metric for our service and we are on track for 200 in FY24.  We hope to grow this number as we begin to normalize the use of drones and 3D mapping on scene.  We expect to validate an on-scene fuming chamber and obtain new camera equipment in FY24 which should boost this number.  Included in these metrics are drones, FARO scanning (tradtional and hand-held), on-scene CA chamber and #D mapping software.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2069, 462, 2025, 915, NULL, 908, NULL, 888, NULL, 920, NULL, 3631, 'Marketing targeted in the city and surrounding counties; Events and career fair attendance increase', 4500, 'Similar to # of recruits hired, we will continue to find new solutions to the national recruitment challenge as a way to trend this number upwards', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2070, 463, 2025, 3571, NULL, 2443, NULL, 2484, NULL, 2041, 'This will remain a priority and a focus for the department in order to bring other city agencies into supporting crime reduction. We anticipate further increases as the focus stays on this metric from BPD leadership', 10539, '311 requests were lower in Q2, most likely due to slower winter months. Further, as 311 reqeusts are appropriately addressed by City partners, less 311 requests exist to put into the system by BPD members.', 29955, 'The goal is to submit 3 311 requests for each of the 3 shifts for 365 days yielding 29955 requests per year.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2071, 464, 2025, 0.982, NULL, 0.999, NULL, 0.995, NULL, 0.991, 'The operations provided sufficient resources allocated to meet the demand of the SRs received through Salesforce._x000D_
_x000D_', 0.991, 'The operation deployed sufficient resources to meet the demand of the SRs received through Salesforce. We were able to  complete and close more stops  on time with the addition resources from the Charm City initiative', 0.9, 'Increased target by 5% to account for positive historical trends and push for an aggressive benchmark', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2072, 465, 2025, 20357, NULL, 19753, NULL, 18089, NULL, 30902, 'From July 1, 2024 to June 30, 2025, there was a daily average of 17 sweeper trucks in the garage for repair leaving 24 available for the operation—July 1, 2024 to January 1, 2025 the average daily available sweeper trucks were 17. The improvement after January 1, 2025 was due to the addition of supplemental contractor services and new sweeper trucks. The early loss of availability reduced MSS’ operational capacity._x000D_
_x000D_
Capacity was further reduced by inclement weather. In January and February 2025 there were 21 days when operations were down due to inclement weather, 516 routes were canceled over this time.  Miles swept are also impacted due to the lack of access to sweep bike lanes in addition to residents not removing their cars for scheduled sweeping days. DPW is working closely with DOT to conduct proactive scouting on scheduled posted routes to ensure sweeping services are not impacted.', 89101, 'From July 1, 2024 to June 30, 2025, there was a daily average of 17 sweeper trucks in the garage for repair leaving 24 available for the operation—July 1, 2024 to January 1, 2025 the average daily available sweeper trucks were 17. Capacity was further reduced by inclement weather.', 100000, 'No change in target...provided vehicles come from the shop target is achievable', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2073, 466, 2025, 12902, NULL, 10827, NULL, 8931, NULL, 12161, 'Service Requests (SRs) received through Salesforce are citizen-driven and not managed directly by Operations. However, we do proactively complete SRs related to graffiti removal, alley cleaning, and street cleaning (12,886 proactive SR''s for work completed which was not driven by citizen requests/complaints.) . A decrease in citizen-submitted requests may also indicate that our proactive efforts are effective, reducing the need for complaints. _x000D_
_x000D_', 44821, 'Service Requests (SRs) received through Salesforce are citizen-driven and not managed directly by Operations. However, we do proactively complete SRs related to graffiti removal, alley cleaning, and street cleaning (12,886 proactive SR''s for work completed which was not driven by citizen requests/co', 60000, 'Recommended target of 82K is not realistic, historical averages have not met that stardard._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
However, the 60k to 62k  are more inline with actuals and overall supports a decrease in the "Desired Outcome"', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2074, 467, 2025, 36252, NULL, 38021, NULL, 29040, NULL, 40404, 'The operation experienced staffing shortages and personnel on permission leave which impacted our ability to meet the targeted goal._x000D_
_x000D_', 143717, 'The operation experienced staffing shortages and personnel on permission leave, which affected our capacity to meet the targeted goal.', 144000, 'Mayor''s Fall Sprint had Rat Rubout set to 12k a month for 3 months.  Following that same standard 12 x 12,000 = 144000', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2075, 468, 2025, 4634, NULL, 3565, NULL, 4067, NULL, 6841, 'The operation experienced staffing shortages which impacted our ability to meet the targetted goal. _x000D_
_x000D_', 19107, 'The operation experienced staffing shortages which impacted our ability to meet the targeted goal.', 30000, 'No change in target and in line with historical averages. Also, with the operation focusing on the Mayor''s Sprintsby being proactive and aggressive, the expectation should result in less residents submitting request', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2076, 469, 2025, 0.999, NULL, 0.993, NULL, 0.999, NULL, 0.996, 'The operation experience an increase in % completed of on time SRs due to boarding crews exceeding their daily quota. This was accomplished with the addition of a boarding crew to meet the demands._x000D_
_x000D_', 0.997, 'We will continue to close service requests on time. The operation experience an increase in % completed of on time SRs due to boarding crews exceeding their daily quota. This was accomplished with the addition of a boarding crew to meet the demands.', 0.9, 'No change.  FY25 Target is in line regarding the operations standard since FY22 , trending in the right direction', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2077, 470, 2025, 0.715, NULL, 0.815, NULL, 0.961, NULL, 0.999, 'The operation experienced shortages that were caused by contracts being delayed due to required BOE approvals, lack of equipment, and staffing shortages._x000D_
