    (2125, 518, 2025, 0.84, NULL, 0.71, NULL, 0.76, NULL, 0.88, NULL, 0.7975, 'The type of offerings within each Therapeautic Recreation category.', 0.75, 'There are several factors which limit this target:_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
A large portion of the participants in TR Programming come from adult daycare agencies.  These agencies have struggled with staffing issues and often cancel last minute._x000D_
_x000D_
Despite most of the COVID-19 restrictions being lifted, some of the typical participants in our programs are at a greater risk for COVID-19 and are unwilling to attend in-person programs._x000D_
_x000D_
As the TR Program develops more programming opportunities, it often takes 2 – 3 programming cycles for the program to develop a client base and reach capacity.  Programs take time to grow and are not always an immediate success.  It is important to differentiate between a program that does not have the potential to grow and one that just needs time.  The majority of our programs have initially had a small number when first offered but have grown to reach maximum capacity.  It would have been a disservice to discontinue any of these programs just because of low numbers the first few sessions._x000D_
_x000D_
There are circumstances where it makes sense to conduct a program even if it is at less than 75% capacity.  For example, we conduct a social program which is primarily self-directed by the participants.  They choose whether they want to dance, play board games, shoot billiards, etc.  This program has a very low overhead and has a large capacity (100).  If only 70 participants register, it still makes sense to have the program as we are still providing a valuable service for the 70 that have registered at a low cost but would count as a negative for this measure.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2126, 519, 2025, 2692, NULL, 2066, NULL, 2030, NULL, 2893, NULL, 9681, 'Change in how attendance is calculated.', 21000, 'Due to the vulnerable nature of the participant base, they have been slower to return to in-person programming.  Additionally, due to the limited number of full-time staff assigned to the TR program and difficulties with the hiring of part-time staff, we have had to limit the numbers on most programs in order to safely conduct them.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
