    (2187, 581, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 0, 'Not aware of a case in Q4 that was heard on judicial review and returned.', 1, NULL, 0.75, '75% of appeals upheld is a good minimum target.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2188, 582, 2025, 81, NULL, 90, NULL, 58, NULL, 56, 'Fewer cases have been filed/heard by the BMZA. Potentially due to ACcela conversion, but also the economy may be leading fewer people to develop property. Additionally, changes to the Zoning Code have been implemented that reduce the need for filings for variances.', 71, 'This predated my tenure as Interm ED of BMZA, but since hearings are processed through same system that building permits are processed through, there would potentially be some hiccups there as staff and applicants adjusted.', 60, 'This number needs to be greater than about 25 (mandatory 21 day notice period + reasonable processing) but the goal should be to decrease it over time.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2189, 583, 2025, 36, NULL, 41, NULL, 31, NULL, 35.4, NULL, 36, NULL, 30, 'The Board has up to 90 days to issue a resolution, which we sometimes need for difficult cases, but we try to keep the average below 30. Even lower would be great, but it can''t reasonably be lower than about 14 days.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2190, 584, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 7.8, 'Fewer cases heard in Q4 compared to the past for reasons stated in earlier KPI.', 44, NULL, 100, 'The idea would be to increase this number, but we''ve been very understaffed for a few years, so keeping it about the same makes sense from the perspective of a reasonable workload.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2191, 638, 2025, 44, NULL, 39, NULL, 27, NULL, NULL, 'Actionable Items', 138, '1. Personnel turnover 2. Personnel training 3. Number of complaints received 4. Number of ancillary complaints derived from active investigations. 5. City''s determination to terminate the OIG''s direct access (since 2005)  to financial and other city records to complete the oversight mission._x000D_
_x000D_', 100, 'Based on SMART criteria', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2192, 639, 2025, 116, NULL, 36, NULL, 51, NULL, NULL, 'Substantial increase do to the outreach efforts of DPW investigation.', 72, '1. Amount of complaints received 2. Financial investigation training 3. Number of financial complaints from investigations 4. Large scope investigations needing community outreach for investigative leads or transparency. 5. City''s determination to terminate the OIG''s direct access (since 2005)', 25, 'Based on SMART criteria', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2193, 640, 2025, 0.8, NULL, 0.45, NULL, 0.884, NULL, NULL, 'These ar number of disclosures filed. Percentage will be determined at end of fiscal year', 0.99, '1. Notifications of disclosure requirements and filing deadlines 2. Training in disclosure process 3. Assistance provided by Ethics office', 1, 'Based on SMART criteria and to ensure that we continue to strive for mandated disclosures', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2194, 641, 2025, 6406491, NULL, 150769, NULL, 2389017, NULL, NULL, NULL, 10.9, '1. Personnel turnover 2. Personnel training 3. Types of complaints 4. Number of ancillary complaints from active investigations 5. Higher financial impact of some investigations 6. City''s determination to terminate the OIG''s direct access (since 2005)  to financial and other city records', 2, 'Based on SMART criteria', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2195, 642, 2025, 205, NULL, 235, NULL, 279, NULL, NULL, 'The are number of attendees. Final percentage will be determined at end of fiscal year.', 641, '1. City personnel turnover requiring new training 2. Training availability', 500, 'Based on SMART criteria and to demonstrate our continued commitment to providing the training, we must to comply with Ethics mandates.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2196, 643, 2025, 161, NULL, 104, NULL, 260, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1305, '1. Personnel turnover 2. Personnel training 3. Number of individuals who sought assistance 4. Marketing of Help Desk availabilit', 1000, 'Based on SMART criteria and to show the levels of assistance the office provides stakeholders on a yearly basis.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2197, 644, 2025, 178, NULL, 267, NULL, 226, NULL, NULL, NULL, 898, '1. Extent of community outreach 2. Turnover in Hotline personnel 3. Training in Hotline case analysis 4. Fluidity of yearly complaints received. 5. City''s determination to terminate the OIG''s direct access to financial and other city records required to complete the oversight mission of the office.', 700, 'Based on SMART criteria', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2198, 660, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 45410, 'Fiscal 2025 CharmTV website sessions totaled 45,410, driven primarily by residents accessing live streams of City Council meetings, hearings, and other government proceedings. Session activity is influenced by the number of proceedings livestreamed and public''s interest.', NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2199, 661, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6174, 'The FY25 programming hours dedicated to government transparency reflect full coverage of Baltimore City Council meetings and hearings, along with additional government programming. Variations in total hours are influenced by the number and length of meetings and hearings held during the fiscal year.', 6500, 'We chose this target because this is one of our top priorities and we maintain the maximum level of service.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2200, 662, 2025, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'MOCC achieved 100% coverage of all City Council meetings and hearings during the reporting period. Having dedicated staff to hearing coverage supports our ability to lly meet this requirement.', 1, 'We chose this target because this is one of our top priorities and we maintain the maximum level of service.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2201, 680, 2025, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1293, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2202, 1, 2026, 48012, NULL, 44545, NULL, 47524, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 210000, 'The 2026 target was established based upon the efficiencies that were created in 2024 and the projected launch of the new real estate system''s first phase roll out in the second quarter of fiscal year 2026. The system will be more user friendly with the ease of reviewing bills and the production of consolidated bills.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2203, 2, 2026, 0.81, NULL, 0.87, NULL, 0.82, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.75, 'The service goal has been increased from 71% to 75% with the additional staffing in several areas of the Bureau that are much needed to respond to customer inquiries. Unfortunately, the call center has no control over other Agencies when a customer''s inquiry needs a response outside of the Bureau. In addition, there may be pain points with the implementation of the new system during Fiscal 2026. Therefore, the factor was increased by a half-point to accommodate improvement and potentional hinderances in the future.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2204, 3, 2026, 1.09, NULL, 1.58, NULL, 1.56, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 7, 'In 2026, the average wait time will remain at 7 minutes in anticipation of potential pain-points with the implementation of the new real estate system.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2205, 4, 2026, 0.73, NULL, 0.91, NULL, 0.95, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.96, 'The 2026 target was repeated for the actual payments that would be collected if properties are not removed from tax sale.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2206, 5, 2026, 0.0497, NULL, 0.0497, NULL, 0.0497, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.04, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established by working with the City''s Financial Advisor, reviewing the financing needs of the City, and projecting bond issuances and structures that meet the City''s needs.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2207, 6, 2026, 2.25, NULL, 5.13, NULL, 3.57, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4, 'Procurement transformation has included onboarding training for suppliers and on-demand training for city employees. Procurement staff training through the transformation includes earning of certification which results in better understanding of procurement process leading to greater number of bids received.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2208, 7, 2026, 3622, NULL, 3522, NULL, 3178, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 12500, 'City no longer under an emergency state, procurement in midst of transformation process to improve processes. Under transformation there is an increase in staff to process incoming requisitions to purchase orders.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2209, 8, 2026, 3600, NULL, 3486, NULL, 2960, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 12000, 'City no longer under an emergency state, procurement in midst of transformation process to improve processes. Under transformation there is an increase in staff to process incoming requisitions.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2210, 9, 2026, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 0.85, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.8, 'In FY26 the BOE meets on a bi-weekly basis requiring a longer lead time to get items on the agenda.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2211, 10, 2026, 25, NULL, 39, NULL, 39, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 104, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2212, 11, 2026, 850, NULL, 965, NULL, 957, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5000, 'City departments conitnue to upgrade equipment and technology at previous rate. New aution contract awarded which will continue services.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2213, 12, 2026, 692591, NULL, 156694, NULL, 455227, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2600000, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2214, 13, 2026, 3117, NULL, 3083, NULL, 3100, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 12500, 'Digital equipment has been in service for a year and new in-line processing technology has been implemented.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2215, 14, 2026, 2, NULL, 3, NULL, 2, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2216, 15, 2026, 1404, NULL, 9831, NULL, 6929, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30000, '10k sick leave conversion payments + estimate for MOU/Bargaining unit bonus payments + routine off-cycle payments due to employee time input errors.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2217, 16, 2026, 119456, NULL, 103520, NULL, 98240, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 377000, '14,500 employees paid biweekly = 377,000', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2218, 17, 2026, 0.9794, NULL, 0.9795, NULL, 0.9785, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.99, 'A target of 99% was established acknowledging that despite the benefits, there are certain City employees that for personal preferences will continue to elect a paper payroll check.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2219, 18, 2026, 5, NULL, 5, NULL, 5, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5, '5 days is the shortest close period that can be established based on City operations.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2220, 19, 2026, 5.71, NULL, 5.75, NULL, 5.39, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 25, 'The increased severity of DPW claims for the current FY is the driving factor.  While the projected inrease is minimal, frequency and severity are alsways coupled together and both shoud see an increase_x000D_
_x000D_', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2221, 20, 2026, 0.84, NULL, 0.54, NULL, 1.04, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4.64, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2222, 21, 2026, 633, NULL, 726, NULL, 777, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2500, 'We are anticipating the implementaton of JJ Keller for the regulated screening.  This would leave the non-rgeulated testing for the BRM to (temporarily) handle. Per the proposed vendors selection procedure we should select all CDL drivers correctly, which will eliminate duplication within the BRM.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2223, 22, 2026, 723.68, NULL, 787.49, NULL, 904.07, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2500, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2224, 23, 2026, 23, NULL, 20, NULL, 148, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 120, 'This metric tracks the number of legislative items analyzed by BBMR during the fiscal year. This includes City Council legislation and General Assembly proposals. This is a workload metric driven by the amount of legislative activity at both the City and State level. Bill responses and fiscal notes serve as tools for policy makers to understand the budgetary impacts of proposed legislation. Within BBMR this process is managed by our Legislative Analyst and supported by members of our expenditure and revenue teams depending on the nature of the legislation. In Fiscal 2026 we will continue to focus on improving the turnaround time for drafting these responses.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2225, 24, 2026, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 2, 'This is an annual measure and data is not available at this time.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5, 'During the Fiscal 2026 planning process we will track operational issues that are flagged for additional follow-up. These issues will be prioritized to develop the BBMR research agenda for Fiscal 2026. The goal of management research reports is to offer recommendations to improve the efficiency or effectiveness of City services. Topics covered through these reports are wide-ranging depending on the specific issue within individual services. Past reports have included staffing studies, fee analysis, and fee analysis.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2226, 25, 2026, 0.4, NULL, 0.019, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.02, 'The proposed target for this metric is 2%, consistent with prior year targets. We are keeping the target consistent with prior years, despite prior year actuals, based on assumptions regarding less revenue volatility driven by the COVID recovery. Much of the volatility from FY22 through FY24 was driven by major swings in a handful revenues impacted by the pandemic. In FY22 and FY23 most of the variation was driven by transfer and recordation taxes driven by increased real estate activity. In FY24 the variation was driven by higher investment returns driven by higher interest rates. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The FY26 target assumes less volatility from these streams while also reflecting updates to revenue models to more accurately build revenue projections.   _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2227, 26, 2026, 5.04, NULL, 6.83, NULL, 5.16, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 3, 'The Fiscal 2026 target seeks to improve the turnaround time for BOE approvals by 1.5 days. Approval items are either generated directly by Procurement or by individual agencies. BBMR will work to reduce the turnaround time for Procurement items by continuing to partner with the Bureau of Procurement to review account information for contracts earlier in the contracting process to avoid last minute confusion. BBMR will work to reduce the turnaround time of agency submitted items by improving the internal routing process and implementing additional training for BBMR Analysts. _x000D_
_x000D_', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2228, 27, 2026, 55, NULL, 57, NULL, 54, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 300, 'The number of appraisal reviews completed for the CHAP Tax Credit is anticipated to remain stable in FY2026 due to economic reasons impacting the housing industry.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2229, 28, 2026, 235, NULL, 122, NULL, 310, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 765, 'Due to a large-scale project involving numerous properties, the number of tax credit applications for FY2026 is expected to increase.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2230, 29, 2026, 18, NULL, 24, NULL, 23, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 140, 'Based on historical trends, we anticipate a decrease in the number of rejected or revoked tax credits in FY2026.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2231, 30, 2026, 2169864, NULL, 486867, NULL, 109006, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4180000, 'FY2026 - Group 1. This group includes the northern part of the City and the Central Business District (CBD). While residential property assessments in the northern part of the City should be increasing, SDAT is likely to limit these increases based on recent changes in interest rates and uncertainty in the market following the recent Presidential election. Accordingly, while these values should be increasing, their 1/1/2025 values are unlikely to increase dramatically over their 1/1/2022 values, which captured much of the post-Covid growth in the housing market. Rents in the CBD are down, and vacancy is up. Based on the FY2023 actual of $5.89M, a 25% decline in the revenue generated is expected for FY2026.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2232, 31, 2026, 3112, NULL, 27, NULL, 7, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2915, 'While we expect an increase in tax credit applications received, the number of granted tax credits is likely to decline. This is mainly because more applications are set to expire than the expected number of new submissions.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2233, 32, 2026, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, '159 customer invoices were processed and paid from 7/1/25 thru 9/30/25. The percentage would not be accurate specifically for Q1 because all active grants have dates prior to 7.1.25.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.85, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2234, 33, 2026, 0.9, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'GMO has recently begun offering monthly grant management trainings to all city agencies. The goal of this metric is to address the City-wide need for robust and consistent grant management training by creating offerings that reach the intended audience and thereby decrease the lack of grant management knowledge.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2235, 34, 2026, 100, NULL, 100, NULL, 100, 'Q1 Total: Of the 27 Findings…_x000D_
_x000D_
·         12 CAPs marked as COMPLETE_x000D_
_x000D_
·         13 CAPs marked as IN PROGRESS_x000D_
_x000D_
·         2 CAPs marked as NOT STARTED_x000D_
_x000D_', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 100, 'The GMO plans to track this metric in order to determine the efficacy of a centralized grants management function and it''s success in addressing any audit findings with effective corrective action.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2236, 35, 2026, 284, NULL, 146, NULL, 159, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1000, 'The GMO aims to assess year over year the number of worktags it successfully processes to determine how many work tags lack required data or documentation.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2237, 36, 2026, 400056.68, NULL, 403302, NULL, 1388211, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2500000, 'Based upon prior year recoveries.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2238, 37, 2026, 5, NULL, 7, NULL, 6, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15, 'Current employees are fully independent and able to conduct reviews.  Numbers based on prior FY.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2239, 38, 2026, 15, NULL, 35, NULL, 7, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 25, 'Current employees are fully independent and able to conduct reviews.  Numbers based on prior FY.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2240, 39, 2026, 0.0478, NULL, 0.0379, NULL, 0.0352, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.03, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established by taking into account the expected interest rate cuts combined with the longer maturities of some of the existing investment portfolio.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2241, 40, 2026, 0.018, NULL, 0.015, NULL, 0.0171, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'The goal of the BCFD is preserving and protecting property by using proactive measures to prevent multiple alarm fires.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2242, 41, 2026, 0.9233, NULL, 0.8607, NULL, 0.8921, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'The target was established utilizing NFPA 1710 for Target Response times.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2243, 42, 2026, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0.35, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'The goal of the BCFD is to preserve and protect public life and safety by eliminating fire deaths through proactive measures and community outreach. Community outreach continues to be one of the most executed (non-emergency) activities of the BCFD. As such, and when combined with other (proactive) public safety activities, it shall always aspire to maintain zero fire fatalities.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2244, 43, 2026, 20115, NULL, 14273, NULL, 12858, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 12000, 'The target was established by utilizing data provided by our IT team that better identifies area that need and increased number of inspections. Data sources such as FEMA tools, 2022 Census data, data retrieved from utility providers, and local non-profit program data have all contributed to a more "data-driven" approach to service delivery.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2245, 44, 2026, 18, NULL, 44, NULL, 56, 'This quarter, OEM held one CERT class which was hosted at StillMeadow Church. 18 community members completed the training and received their certification.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 40, 'OEM is working to increase the number of available instructors for the CERT program. We are planning for quarterly CERT training in the 2025 calendar year, with at least 10 participants per training. We plan to maintain or continue to increase those opportunities through FY26.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2246, 45, 2026, 3, NULL, 3, NULL, 6, 'This quarter, OEM led a Debris Managament workshop with City Partners. OEM also supported 2 interagency Tabletop Exercises; one with Morgan State University to prepare for Homecoming Activation and Emergency response resources and one with BCIT to discuss back-up operations in the event that the Abel Wolman building was lost to services.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 10, 'We will continue to develop the training and exercise program. With available staff and ongoing interagency and public-private partnerships, our training capabilities will be able to double from FY24 to FY26. Additionally, we will be developing a training and exercise plan with input from our partners to better serve the needs of staff citywide.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.998111'),
    (2247, 46, 2026, 19, NULL, 24, NULL, 29, 'OEM on-scene responses included support for building fires, a mass casualty overdose, gas leaks, hazmat incidents, and rescue calls.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 55, 'OEM provides on-scene response to extreme emergencies where additional support or interagency coordination may be needed. Our goal is not to increase the number of responses as that would indicate more severe emergencies for the city. Instead, we plan to maintain the necessary level of support. The FY 26 target was established based on FY24 actual on-scene response numbers.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2248, 47, 2026, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'OEM will continue collaborating with local and state partners to ensure all grant funding is spent to maximize resources toward Homeland Security in the City. OEM hired a full time Fiscal Officer that started in FY25. This position will also support grant funding spend down. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
