    (2280, 79, 2026, 4.5, NULL, 4.7, NULL, 6, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 18, 'Continued aggressive approach to increased field training along with established operational policies to continue decreasing the number of line of duty injuries', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2281, 80, 2026, 42, NULL, 0, NULL, 24, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 100, 'Projections exceed the FY25 target.  FY26 target was increased based on the FY25 projections, but achieving this target goal will be driven by the number of posiion vacancies occurring within the FY.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (1761, 81, 2025, 667, NULL, 782, NULL, 1088, NULL, 1092, NULL, 3782, 'Ongoing evaluation of operational needs and successful grant award allowed for increased number of classes delivered to field members_x000D_
_x000D_', 2000, 'Goal to increase field training hours offered through Grant awards', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2283, 82, 2026, 97, NULL, 82, NULL, 106, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 275, 'Target established based on decrease in number of accidents over the past 3 years along with implementation of new program with simulator.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2284, 83, 2026, 0.68, NULL, 0.71, NULL, 0.93, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.75, 'Realistic target with increased numbers of students per class with overall goal of increasing percentage.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2285, 85, 2026, 0.032, NULL, 0.038, NULL, 0.026, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.09, 'The fiscal-year-to-date figures for FY25 are in line with ones from FY24. That is, the citywide percentage of maintenance and repair outside of regular wear and tear is at 4.1%, while the percentage within DPW-Solid Waste remains at 15.1%. Fleet expects the complete numbers for the rest of the year to be similar. We’re setting a conservative goal of 6%, which we’re fairly certain we can meet. Note that in FY25 we raised this goal to 9% due to a large amount of aging equipment, most of which has now been disposed of.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2286, 86, 2026, 0.832, NULL, 0.861, NULL, 0.837, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.85, 'Fleet is keeping the target for Public Safety Fleet Availability at 85%, unchanged from FY25. We’ve continued to bring many new vehicles into the public safety fleet during FY25. The median age of marked police vehicles is at 2.5 years as of October 2024, down from 3.0 in June 2023. _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
We expect to see a boost in public safety availability in FY26 toward 85% because the new vehicles brought into service in FY24 and FY25 will have already been upfitted and prepared for service. These vehicles will be in the section of their lifespans where availability tends to be highest, and on the strength of those new vehicles we expect to be able to meet this target.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2287, 87, 2026, 0.719, NULL, 0.822, NULL, 0.761, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.75, 'Fleet is lowering the target for Routine Services Safety Fleet Availability to 70%, 5 points down from where it was set for FY25. This is based in part on the fiscal-year-to-date figure for FY25, which is 60%. Fleet is aware of several headwinds for this category of vehicles, including higher-than-normal levels of avoidable costs, time-consuming repairs on complex heavy equipment, and problems with retaining technicians skilled enough to work on this equipment. However, Fleet needs to be around 70% for this KPI in order to meet agency-supplied availability targets.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2288, 89, 2026, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 60, 'DGS did not expect any major changes in FY2026 to impact the efficiency of the portfolio of buildings, so did not shift the target. In the future, DGS expects to see some change from the implementation of their Energy Management Information System/Building Automation System upgrade project, but it''s not expected to show results until FY27. The Abel Wolman Building HVAC project is also expected to impact the total energy use of the City, if not the median energy use intensity.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2289, 90, 2026, 791538.72, NULL, 60567.23, NULL, 83125.33, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1000000, 'MEA''s FY25 programs do not include as much total funding and expected federal grants are at risk from the new adminstration. Further, there is uncertainty on whether Direct Pay will continue, which will reduce revenue sources for electric vehicle purchases, electric vehicle charging, and renewable projects.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2290, 92, 2026, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.2, 'The goal is based on the City''s 2026 requirements under the Maryland Renewable Portfolio Standard if the City did not pay the compliance payment. For FY 2027, the City''s requirements for purchasing renewables are going to grow from 20% to 43%.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2291, 93, 2026, 0.395, NULL, 0.374, NULL, 0.295, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.55, 'The % of corrective work request completed on time is the counterpart of preventive maintenance.  We use this metric to track and measure how efficient our staff is at completing corrective maintenance work in DGS managed facilities. This KPI allows transparency on the Departments on-time completion of work request against the problem types benchmark. It is important to track this metric so staffing, vendor, and training deficiencies can be managed effectively in order to meet the demands of providing prompt response and repairs.  CM on time compliance tells the story of how well our staff responds to work order request and is a gateway to how we make decision on staffing, programming, and also sets the course for capital investment decision making. We maintaiend  FY26 target at 55% due to a number of factors. Despite FY24 and FY23 acutals msising target, FMD hopes to reverse the decline in corrective maintnance  by benefiting from staff in key managerial and technical positions meant to improve performance and division culture. Key managerial, analytical and technical positions have been filled prompting an increse in work completed on time.  Many needed contracts that have not been available or active in the past fY have been created and/or active allowing FMD to complete a higher number of work orders on time.  The introduction of new data tools and the arrival of a full-time data analyst will also allow staff and leadership to  gain a better understanding of performance.   All efforts are actively underway and will continue to be executed and developed through the next fiscal year.  We are optimistic about the improved performance.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2292, 94, 2026, 0.978, NULL, 0.981, NULL, 0.985, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'This KPI tracks daily operation of a crticical life safety/transport system in many of the core municipal buildins.  It is critical that we know what units are oprational each day to ensure transport and emergency protocols remain active. Management uses this metric to inform on which units require maintenance repair, capital investment, and also how to address programming and commnications. Current benchmark for DGS FMD is each day no less than 90% elevators are out of order each day at the start of the day.  This target percentage takes into effect the age units, industry standard uptime of elevator portfolio, and also vendor and staff availability to sustain units. The increases in target is a result of FY24 performance and the process improvement FMD has observed.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2293, 96, 2026, 0.959, NULL, 0.985, NULL, 0.972, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.6, 'Efforts to clean up our Archibus queues and maintain through process improvements continue. This effort should result in improved compliance by clearing out older, unresolved orders.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2294, 97, 2026, 0.5, NULL, 1, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.89, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established by analyzing the average performance of completed design projects over the past ten years. This method uses historical data as a benchmark, considering factors such as on-time project completion rates and other relevant metrics. By examining these trends, we were able to set a realistic and informed target for future performance, ensuring it reflects both past achievements and potential areas for improvement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2295, 98, 2026, 0.5, NULL, 0.5, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.73, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established by analyzing the average performance of completed design projects over the past ten years. This method uses historical data as a benchmark, considering factors such as on-time project completion rates and other relevant metrics. By examining these trends, we were able to set a realistic and informed target for future performance, ensuring it reflects both past achievements and potential areas for improvement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2296, 99, 2026, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established by analyzing the average performance of key metrics over the past four years, where the average consistently reached 100%. While the Fiscal 2025 target was set at 100%, the revised target of 90% for Fiscal 2026 reflects a strategic approach to set a realistic and achievable goal. This adjustment accounts for potential variability and operational challenges, ensuring the target remains ambitious yet attainable while continuing to drive continuous improvement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2297, 100, 2026, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established by analyzing the average performance of key metrics over the past four years, where the average consistently reached 100%. While the Fiscal 2025 target was set at 100%, the revised target of 90% for Fiscal 2026 reflects a strategic approach to set a realistic and achievable goal. This adjustment accounts for potential variability and operational challenges, ensuring the target remains ambitious yet attainable while continuing to drive continuous improvement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2298, 102, 2026, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.9, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established by analyzing the average performance of completed design projects over the past ten years. This method uses historical data as a benchmark, considering factors such as on-time project completion rates and other relevant metrics. By examining these trends, we were able to set a realistic and informed target for future performance, ensuring it reflects both past achievements and potential areas for improvement.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2299, 103, 2026, 1918, NULL, 2518, NULL, 3135, 'Number of unique clients visiting the SHWC during the FY 26 Q1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 6000, 'Funding cuts in FY25 have impacted staffing size and operational hours at the clinics.  In addition, there are currently several vacancies in the clinic.								_x000D_
_x000D_', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2300, 104, 2026, 113, NULL, 124, NULL, 138, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1150, 'Looking ahead to FY26 we anticipate that our 2 vacant contractual provider postions will be filled, but we also anticipate the retirement of one of our dentists during FY26. We are conservatively estimating that we will serve an average of 24 patients/wk over 49wks which is how we got to our FY26 target. 								_x000D_
