_x000D_
The service delivery model for the FLEX program was designed to be sensitive to the immediate and long-term needs of TCA recipients. The program recognizes that each participant’s journey to long-term employment and self-sufficiency will involve career counseling, skill building, work supports, and on-going interventions to achieve program deliverables. As a result, while more participants will receive services, we expect that fewer will gain and retain employment within the first full year of implementation.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2513, 382, 2026, 0.2, NULL, 0.17, NULL, 0.18, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.5, 'The target for Fiscal Year 2026 was established based on several program enhancements and additions. Starting in FY 2026, the FLEX program will be fully implemented, offering expanded services that include a dedicated mental health and substance use provider. The program will also expand to serve two new customer groups: non-custodial parents and justice-involved youth. The inclusion of these non-TANF customer groups is expected to increase the number of individuals served at the Workforce Reception Center. _x000D_
