    (2634, 504, 2026, 5.74, NULL, 3.3, NULL, 1.37, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15, '15 miles is the target goal every year', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2635, 505, 2026, 0.74, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.93, 'Pool Technicians have been hired to address maintenance issues year-round. DigiQuatics has been updated to send alerts directly to managers'' cell phones, ensuring a quicker response to service requests. A service request will be submitted immediately upon receiving an alert, reducing pool closure times by resolving issues promptly. Additionally, three neighborhood pools are scheduled to return to the BCRP inventory this year.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2636, 506, 2026, 124714, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 200000, 'Coldstream, Walter P. Carter, Towanda, and Chick Webb will reopen this summer, increasing attendance by offering more locations. To further engage the community, we are planning diverse programs designed to attract a broader audience.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2637, 507, 2026, 0.0869, NULL, 0.12, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'The Fiscal 2026 target was established due to the ARPA funding that allowed BCRP Playground program to increase the number of playground replacements throughout the city.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2638, 508, 2026, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'No impact to this service', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2639, 509, 2026, 932, NULL, 552, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4000, 'The Fiscal Year 2026 target was set with the expectation of a 10% increase in youth sports programming participation. Targeted outreach efforts, along with subsidized fees and scholarships, will support the growth of participants served', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2640, 510, 2026, 342, NULL, 399, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1965, 'The Fiscal Year 2026 target was set with the expectation of a 20% increase in adult sports participation. This projection is driven by the introduction of new adult sports offerings, which are key to achieving the anticipated growth', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2641, 511, 2026, 2829, NULL, 2172, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 4600, 'The projected goal is a 10% increase compared to the Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2642, 512, 2026, 4699, NULL, 3457, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 13080, 'Efforts are focused on achieving a minimum number of recreation leader-led programs designed to boost participation at recreation facilities. The projected goal is a 10% increase compared to the Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2643, 513, 2026, 2780, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2500, 'The projected goal is a 10% increase compared to the Fiscal 2024 actual data.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2644, 514, 2026, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.8, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2645, 515, 2026, 11503, NULL, 13872, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 44000, 'At Cylburn Arboretum, the proposed target is flat for FY26 based on the actuals from FY24. Experience shows that the first year a facility is open it has very high attendance and that attendance tends to level off in years 2 and 3. Secondly, the NEC is not managed by BCRP and we do not necessarily have control over that success (or failure). Additionally, there is limited parking and a finite number of weekends; at some point the attendance curve will flatten at Cylburn.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2646, 516, 2026, 8356, NULL, 9498, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 5000, 'Due to the anticipated construction at the Conservatory, it is likely the faclity will be completely closed for a large portion of the year and partially closed part of the year so there will be minimal visitors.  The current construction timeline is to begin in June of 2025 and will likely take a full year.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2647, 517, 2026, 1145, NULL, 2253, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 20355, 'The performance measure calculates the total number of participants attending city-wide programs, community-based activities, and special events. Health promotion remains a main goal of our programming with most providing participants with the opportunity to improve their physical endurance, balance, cardiovascular and muscular system through physical activity.  Bowl for Your Heart, Walk the Zoo for a Healthier You, Senior Splash, Fall Brawl and Spring Swing tournaments are just a few events held to keep seniors mentally, physically and socially fit. Seniors who stay active and engaged through activities such as hobbies, regular exercise, travel and relaxation report feeling happier and healthier overall, and countless studies have backed their claims. Keeping the mind active and intellectually engaged seems to help reduce the development and progress of many memories related conditions and may improve cognition. Furthermore, seniors who stay physically active typically have greater overall energy and strength in addition to reduced risks for diabetes, heart disease and other health related conditions according to the "National Institute on Aging” https://www.seniorliving.org/leisure/_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Positive:  The Senior Division partnered with Baltimore City Health Department and Eating Together in Baltimore to offer three new events:  Western Cabaret, Summercize Carnival and The Great Gatsby.  This kept our program fresh and exciting. By combining resources, we can serve more seniors and keep prices low._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Negative: Kurtz Beach, an annual favorite event of the seniors, had to be revamped from an eight-day event to a one-day event. We also had to change the venue due to cost.  The event served 200-300 different groups of seniors each day.  _x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Community Partners:  The Senior Division has worked with the following community partners throughout the year to serve seniors and cut cost:  Eating Together in Baltimore, Baltimore City Health Department, Senior Legal Services, Maryland Pro Bono Resource Center, Sage Health, University of Maryland, Enoch Pratt Free Library, Maryland Volunteer Lawyer._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
Target:  The division experienced an increase in participation numbers due to combining of resources, adding on new events, tournaments and classes.  With the allocation of funds and rising programming cost, the division felt this was a realistic number of seniors we could serve._x000D_
_x000D_', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2648, 518, 2026, 0.82, NULL, 0.7957, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.75, 'The target of having 75% of programs operating at 75% capacity or greater was successfully met in Fiscal 2024. This was a positive achievement, indicating that the program was running efficiently, with a good balance between available resources and participant demand. However, in Fiscal 2025, the program is projected to not meet the target. This decline is attributed to factors like reduced staff and fewer program offerings (as discussed earlier). With fewer full-time staff, the program''s capacity was limited, leading to lower participation rates and programs that couldn''t operate at full capacity, thereby falling short of the 75% target._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The target of 75% of programs operating at 75% capacity or greater is a strategic goal aimed at ensuring program efficiency. The goal helps avoid the waste of time and resources. If programs are running with low attendance or underutilized, it suggests that resources (such as staff time, space, and materials) may be underused, and that more effort should be put into marketing, outreach, or adjusting program offerings to meet demand. Maintaining programs at or above 75% capacity ensures that the programs are delivering maximum impact, serving as many participants as possible, while not overextending resources. It''s a measure of both effectiveness (reaching participants) and efficiency (maximizing resources). This target supports long-term sustainability._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The Fiscal 2026 target is therefore built on the understanding that, with restored staff and expanded staffing, expanded program offerings, and better resource management, the program should be able to meet or exceed the 75% capacity benchmark in the coming fiscal year.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2649, 519, 2026, 510, NULL, 663, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 18900, 'The Fiscal 2026 target for Therapeutic Recreation programs was established based on several key factors, primarily reflecting the expected growth and expansion of the program after a challenging FY25. Here''s how the target was determined: Going into FY26, the team is back to full strength, with three full-time staff members. This staffing increase allows for more program offerings, increased capacity, and a stronger ability to serve participants. With a fully staffed team, the program has the infrastructure needed to begin meeting higher demand._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The FY26 target reflects a strategic effort to expand program offerings. This includes programs being offered on more days and times as well as at more locations across Baltimore.  The programs will be available on additional days and at more convenient times, making it easier for participants to access them. By offering programs at more locations, the team can reach a broader audience, especially in areas where access to such programs might have been limited in the past._x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
_x000D_
The FY26 target was set to be measurable, attainable, and to provide clear direction for program growth. The target includes specific numbers or performance indicators that can be tracked throughout the year. Given the full staff, expanded schedule, and additional locations, the target is realistic and achievable. It takes into account the challenges faced in FY25, while also positioning the program for recovery and growth. The target is not just about returning to previous levels; it''s about growing beyond them. It gives the team a clear goal to work toward as they expand their offerings and improve program accessibility._x000D_
_x000D_
In summary, the FY26 target is rooted in a return to full staffing, a strategic expansion of program offerings, and a realistic expectation of growth based on the lessons learned from FY25. This target provides a clear and achievable roadmap for increasing participation and improving the overall impact of the Therapeutic Recreation programs.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2650, 520, 2026, 16, NULL, 12, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30, 'Our target for Fiscal 2026 has been set at 30 because our goal is to we refine and grow the existing events and programs that we have in our portfolio vs.  increase the number of events and programs that we offer.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2651, 521, 2026, 0.4922, NULL, 0.4308, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.5, 'Forestry is staying with the same goal for FY26. Meeting a higher percentage is more likely a product of having many duplicate SRs and urgents (because they can be closed out quickly) than it is responding to routine maintenance requests, which are typically not completed within the 30-day SLA for completing the inspection.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2652, 522, 2026, 0, NULL, 3800, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 7000, 'Although their numbers can also fluctuate, our planting partners have been consistent with how many trees they plant per year over recent years. Forestry will also have a planting contract active during this fiscal year, so we can anticipate a higher overall number of trees planted.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
