    (2709, 579, 2026, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2710, 580, 2026, 0.89, NULL, 0.76, NULL, 0.85, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2711, 581, 2026, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.75, 'The goal of having 75% of appeals upheld through judicial review remains unchanged, as it is a reasonable and achievable metric. Historically, we have consistently met or come close to this target. Cases that proceed to judicial review are often complex, time-consuming, and involve significant opposition, making them less representative of typical appeals. While the Board strives for accuracy, a 100% success rate is unrealistic given the nature of these cases. A 75% target reflects a balance between high performance and practical expectations.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2712, 582, 2026, 35, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 75, 'The Fiscal 2026 target of 75 days for the average time between filing an appeal and the public hearing was established with the aim of improving on the FY2024 actual number of 100 days. While we aim to reduce this timeline, the target reflects the understanding that several factors—such as appellant responsiveness, fluctuations in the real estate market, and interest rate changes—are outside our control. This balanced target acknowledges these challenges while striving for greater efficiency.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2713, 583, 2026, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 25, 'The target for the average number of days from public hearing to written resolution has been reduced from 30 to 25 days in an effort to issue resolutions more quickly while maintaining realistic expectations. Ideally, resolutions would be issued around or before the next set of hearings, usually 2 weeks later; however, this is not always feasible due to the complexity of the resolutions and the review process. The new target aims to strike a balance between efficiency and thoroughness.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
    (2714, 584, 2026, 5, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 75, 'The Fiscal 2026 target of 75 days was set to improve upon the previous year’s metric while remaining realistic in the post-consent docket context. Without the expedited processing enabled by the consent docket, each appeal now requires more thorough review, making it essential to balance efficiency with fairness. The target reflects this shift, aiming for incremental progress that is both achievable and aligned with the Board’s commitment to meaningful appeal consideration.', 2, '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486', '2026-06-26T16:54:00.999486'),
